{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"hindi-motiv","displayName":"प्रेरणा — हिंदी","displayNameEnglish":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","version":"1.0","language":"Hindi","languageCode":"hi","script":"Devanagari","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"edition":"Public Domain & Curated / Hindi Wikiquote","primaryCategory":"Philosophy & Spirituality","subcategory":"Hindi Wisdom","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"groupingLevels":[],"groupingLabels":[],"sortPriority":53,"contentRating":"general","audienceTags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"itemCount":1204,"dataPath":"Data/Collections/HindiMotivational.json"},"data":[{"id":"hindi-motiv-0001","text":"महात्मा ने जो दृष्टि अपनाई है, वह हिन्दू की अपेक्षा ईसाई ही है। एक ईसाई के लिए आत्मावनति, दीनता, मानवता अथवा ईश्वर की सेवा के लिए निम्न स्थिति को स्वीकार कर लेना ऐसी चीजें हैं, जो उत्कृष्ट रूप से आध्यात्मिक और आत्मा का गौरवशाली विशेषाधिकार हैं। -- अरविन्द घोष, १९३६ में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0002","text":"उनके सारे उपदेश ईसाई धर्म से लिए गए हैं और यद्यपि बाह्य वेष भारतीय है, तो भी मूल भावना ईसाई है। वे ईसा मसीह न भी हों, तो भी वे हर हालत में उसी आवेग की परंपरा में आते हैं। वे टॉल्सटॉय, बाइबिल से बहुत अधिक प्रभावित हैं और उनकी शिक्षाओं में सुदृढ़ जैनी रंगत है, कम से कम भारतीय शास्त्रों, उपनिषदों अथवा गीता से कहीं अधिक, जिसकी व्याख्या उन्होंने अपनी धारणाओं के प्रकाश में ही की है। -- सन १९२६","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0003","text":"महात्मा जी किसी अभियान का प्रारम्भ शानदार ढंग से करते हैं, वे उसे निपुणतापूर्वाग आगे बढ़ाते हैं, उन्हें एक के बाद एक सफलता मिलती जाती है, यहाँ तक की वे अपने अभियान के चरम शिखर पहुँच जाते हैं, परन्तु इसके बाद उनकी हिम्मत टूट जाती और वे लड़खड़ाने लगते हैं। -- चित्तरंजन दास, असहयोग आन्दोलन को स्थगित करने पर अपनी तीव्र प्रतिक्रिया व्यक्त करते हुए (उस समय वे जेल में थे)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0004","text":"भविष्य की पीढ़ियों को इस बात पर विश्वास करने में मुश्किल होगी कि हाड़-मांस से बना ऐसा कोई व्यक्ति भी कभी धरती पर आया था। --अल्बर्ट आइंस्टीन","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0005","text":"गांधी हमेशा मुझे एक प्रेरणा-पुंज की तरह रास्ता दिखाते रहे। -- नेल्सन मान्डेला","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0006","text":"ईसा मसीह ने हमें लक्ष्य दिए और महात्मा गांधी ने हमें उन्हें प्राप्त करने के तरीके बताए। -- मार्टिन लूथर किंग जूनियर","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0007","text":"दशकों के अभियान में गांधी ने जो हासिल नहीं किया था, बोस की आजाद हिन्द फौज ने दो साल से भी कम समय में हासिल कर लिया और अंग्रेजों को भारत छोड़ने का फैसला करना पड़ा। और उसकी यह उपलब्धि वास्तव में बहुत अधिक गोलियां चलाए बिना मिल गयी। यदि आप शक्ति विकीर्ण करते हैं, तो आपको अक्सर इसका उपयोग करने की आवश्यकता नहीं होती है। दरबारी इतिहासकारों ने हमेशा आजाद हिन्द फौज की भूमिका को कमतर आंका है और स्वतंत्रता की उपलब्धि का श्रेय महात्मा गांधी को दिया है। -- के एल्स्ट (Elst, K.), 'सुभाष बोस विन्डिकेटेद' में (हिन्दू ह्यूमन राइट्स, प्रयाग तथा स्वराज्य, अप्रैल 2019)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0008","text":"मेरा अपना विचार है कि महापुरुष अपने देश के लिए महान सेवा के होते हैं, लेकिन वे निश्चित समय के बाद कभी कभी देश की प्रगति में बाधा भी बनते हैं। मि० गांधी इस देश के लिए एक निश्चित खतरा बन गए थे। उन्होंने सभी के विचारों को घुट कर रख दिया था। वह कांग्रेस के साथ खड़े हुए थे, वो काँग्रेस, जो समाज के सभी बुरे और स्वार्थसेवी तत्वों का एक संयोजन है, जो सिवाय प्रशंसा और चापलूसी के, समाज-जीवन को नियंत्रित करने वाले किसी भी सामाजिक या नैतिक सिद्धांत पर सहमत नहीं हैं। इस तरह की संस्था किसी भी देश पर शासन करने के लिए अयोग्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0009","text":"गांधी कभी भी महात्मा नहीं थे, मैं उन्हें महात्मा नहीं मानता। -- भीमराव अम्बेडकर, सन 1955 में BBC से साक्षात्कार में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0010","text":"मेरी तरह किसी को भी गांधीजी के प्रति एक प्रकार की सौन्दर्यपरक अरुचि महसूस हो सकती है, कोई उनकी ओर से किए गए संतत्व के दावों को अस्वीकार कर सकता है, कोई आदर्श के रूप में संतत्व को भी अस्वीकार कर सकता है और इसलिए महसूस कर सकता है कि गांधी के मूल उद्देश्य मानव-विरोधी और प्रतिक्रियावादी थे। लेकिन यदि उन्हें उन्हें केवल एक राजनेता के रूप में देखा जाय, और हमारे समय के अन्य प्रमुख राजनीतिक हस्तियों की तुलना में, वह कितनी साफ गंध छोड़ने में कामयाब रहे! -- जॉर्ज ओरवेल, गांधी के बारे में लिखते हुए, १९४९","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — महात्मा गांधी पर महापुरुषों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0011","text":"अनुशासन केवल सैनिक के लिए नहीं होता है बल्कि जीवन के हर क्षेत्र के लिए होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अनुशासन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0012","text":"अनुशासन के बिना न तो राष्ट्र, न ही कोई संस्था और न ही कोई परिवार चल सकता है। अनुशासन इन सबको बांधे रखता है और इनके प्रगति की सीढ़ी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अनुशासन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0013","text":"बाहरी दुनिया की तरह अपने मन और शरीर को भी अनुशासन में रखना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अनुशासन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0014","text":"किसी भी राष्ट्र का परिचय वहां के अनुशासित लोगो से पता चलता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अनुशासन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0015","text":"अनुशासन शारीरिक और मानसिक दोनों तरह के होते है। ये दोनों ही किसी भी व्यक्ति के प्रशिक्षण के लिए ज़रूरी होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अनुशासन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0016","text":"अगर आत्मा और इस्वर एक है तो फिर अछूत और अस्पृश्य कोई हो ही नहीं सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अस्पृश्यता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0017","text":"अस्पृश्य वह है जो झूठ बोलता है और पाखंड करता हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अस्पृश्यता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0018","text":"मै पूवर्जन्म की इच्छा नहीं रखता पर मुझे अगर फिर से जन्म लेना हो तो मै एक अछूत के घर जन्म लेना चाहूंगा, जिससे मै उनके कष्ट को बाँट सकूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अस्पृश्यता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0019","text":"हिन्दुस्तान सबसे पहले अपनी पोशाक और भाषा को अपनाये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — खादी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0020","text":"गांव की जरुरत की हर चीज़ गांव में ही बननी चाहिए। खादी इसकी पहली सीढ़ी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — खादी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0021","text":"खादी का मतलब है देश के सभी लोगो की आर्थिक समानता और स्वतन्त्रा का आरंभ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — खादी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0022","text":"जब यह शरीर नश्वर है और आत्मा अमर है तो भय किसका और किसलिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — डर और अभय","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0023","text":"अभय रहने से मनुष्य का कोई भी, कुछ भी नहीं बिगाड़ सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — डर और अभय","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0024","text":"बल तो निडरता में है, आपके शरीर से इसका कोई मतलब नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — डर और अभय","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0025","text":"अगर इस शरीर से ममता छूट जाय तो आसानी से हम अभय को उपलब्ध हो जायेगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — डर और अभय","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0026","text":"जो भगवान पर विश्वास रखते है वे अभय हो जाते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — डर और अभय","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0027","text":"संसार में आधे से अधिक लोग इस लिए सफल नहीं हो पाते है। क्योकि उनमें साहस का संचार नहीं हो पता है और वे भयभीत हो जाते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — डर और अभय","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0028","text":"हमें यह सोचने की ग़लती नहीं करनी चाहिए कि हम कभी भूल नहीं कर सकते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ग़लती","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0029","text":"ग़लती मान लेना, झाड़ू लगाने के समान है। यह गंदगी को बहारकर, सतह को साफ़ कर देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ग़लती","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0030","text":"भूल करके आदमी सीखता तो है पर इसका यह मतलब नहीं कि जीवन भर भूल ही करता जाय और कहे कि हम सीख रहे है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ग़लती","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0031","text":"अपनी गलती से इन्सान बहुत कुछ सीख सकता है, बशर्ते वह इसके लिए तैयार हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ग़लती","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0032","text":"सच्चा मनुष्य वही है, जो अपनी ग़लती को मान ले और फिर उसे त्याग कर अपने में सुधार करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ग़लती","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0033","text":"गाय जैसे निरीह और उपयोगी पशु का वध करना राष्ट्र के लिए आत्मधात के समान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — गो-सेवा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0034","text":"गो-सेवा करना अपने आप की सेवा करने के समान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — गो-सेवा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0035","text":"गाय हिन्दू-जीवन की अहिंसकता और सादगी का प्रतीक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — गो-सेवा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0036","text":"असहयोग एक बड़ा अस्त्र है। असहयोग का पालन तलवार की धार पर चलने के समान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — असहयोग","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0037","text":"असहयोग कोई निष्क्रिय (आलसी) की स्थिति नहीं है बल्कि एक सक्रिय स्थिति है। यह हिंसा से कही अधिक क्रियाशील है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — असहयोग","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0038","text":"मैं काम करने के तरीकों, पद्धतियों और प्रणालियो से असहयोग करता हु, न की मनुष्य से।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — असहयोग","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0039","text":"असहयोग में तो इतनी शक्ति है की छोटी से छोटी इकाइयो (परिवार) को भी भंग कर सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — असहयोग","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0040","text":"चिंता एक डायन है जो शरीर को खा जाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चिन्ता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0041","text":"चिंता मुक्ति पूर्ण समपर्ण से संभव है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चिन्ता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0042","text":"चिंता मनुष्य की शक्तियो को शून्य कर देती है, इसलिए इसे त्याग देना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चिन्ता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0043","text":"तप से संसार बड़ी से बड़ी सिद्धि प्राप्त की जा सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — तपस्या","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0044","text":"तप के बिना त्याग अधूरा ही रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — तपस्या","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0045","text":"तप से मनुष्य मन के उच्च स्तर तक पहुंच सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — तपस्या","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0046","text":"उस जीवन को नष्ट करने का हमें कोई अधिकार नहीं है जिसके बनाने की शक्ति हम में न हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0047","text":"अहिंसा का नियम है कि मर्यादा पर कायम रहना चाहिए। कभी भी अभिमान नहीं करनी चाहिए और हमेशा नर्म रहना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0048","text":"अहिंसा प्रेम की पराकाष्ठा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0049","text":"जहां अहिंसा है, वहां धीरज, भीतरी शांति, भले बुरे का ज्ञान और जानकारी भी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0050","text":"अहिंसा निर्बल और डरपोक का नहीं, वीर का धर्म है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0051","text":"किसी को कभी भी नहीं मारना और किसी को कभी नहीं सताना ही अहिंसा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0052","text":"अहिंसा में इतनी ताकत है कि यह आपके विरोधियों को भी मित्र बना लेती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0053","text":"अहिंसा और कायरता परस्पर विरोधी शब्द है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0054","text":"जहां दया नहीं वहां अहिंसा नहीं हो सकती है। जितना ज्यादा दया होगी उतनी ज्यादा अहिंसा होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0055","text":"बिना अहिंसा के सत्य की खोज असंभव है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0056","text":"जो अहिंसा पर अंत तक डटा रहेगा, उसकी विजय निश्चित है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0057","text":"हिंसा का परिणाम जल्दी आता है जबकि अहिंसा का परिणाम देर से आता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0058","text":"कमज़ोर कभी माफ नहीं कर सकता; क्षमा करना ताकतवर की पहचान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — अहिंसा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0059","text":"उपवास का धमकी के रूप में उपयोग करना बुरा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — उपवास","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0060","text":"उपवास तो आखरी हथियार है वह अपनी या दूसरों की तलवार की जगह लेता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — उपवास","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0061","text":"उपवास शारीरिक और आत्मिक शुद्धि के लिए आवश्यक सहयोग है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — उपवास","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0062","text":"अगर भारत को शांतिपूर्ण सच्ची प्रगति करनी है तो पैसे वाले यह समझ ले कि किसानों में ही भारत की आत्मा बसती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — किसान","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0063","text":"किसानों का शहर की ओर भागना उसकी असफलता का ढिंढोरा है। ऐसा करके वह न तो घर का रहेगा न घाट का।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — किसान","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0064","text":"किसान देश की रीढ़ की हड्डी है; उसकी उन्नति ही भारत की उन्नति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — किसान","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0065","text":"कृषि केवल आजीविका नहीं, एक साधना है, यह धरती माँ से हमारा सीधा संबंध है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — किसान","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0066","text":"आहार संतुलित और विवेकपूर्ण हो तो शरीर में कोई रोग हो ही नहीं सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0067","text":"आहार शरीर के लिए है न कि शरीर आहार के लिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0068","text":"पशु-पक्षी स्वाद के लिए भोजन नहीं करते है, न ही वे इतना खाते कि पेट फटने लगे। वे भोजन को स्वयं नहीं पकाते है । प्रकृति जैसा देती है वैसे ग्रहण कर लेते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0069","text":"संसार में जितने लोग भूख से नहीं मरते उससे ज्यादा लोग अधिक भोजन करने से मरते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0070","text":"इंसान की शारीरिक बनावट देखने से यह पता चलता है प्रकृति ने मनुष्य को शाकाहारी बनाया है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0071","text":"अगर हम आहार विवेकपूर्ण नहीं करेंगे तो हममें और पशु में कोई अंतर नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0072","text":"जब तक आहार में स्वाद की प्रधानता रहेगी तब तक उसमे सात्विकता आ ही नहीं सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0073","text":"\"आप जो बदलाव दुनिया में देखना चाहते हैं, वह पहले खुद में लाएं।\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0074","text":"जहाँ प्रेम है, वहाँ जीवन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0075","text":"स्वयं को पाने का सबसे अच्छा तरीका है, खुद को दूसरों की सेवा में खो देना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0076","text":"हमारे विचार ही हमारे शब्द बनते हैं, हमारे शब्द कर्म बनते हैं, और कर्म ही हमारा भाग्य तय करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0077","text":"जो व्यक्ति अपने मन को जीत लेता है, वह दुनिया को जीत सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — आहार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0078","text":"मै उच्च शिक्षा उसी को कहूंगा जिसे पाकर इन्सान विनम्र, परोपकारी, सेवाभावी और कार्यतत्पर बन जाय।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — शिक्षा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0079","text":"क्रन्तिकारी की प्रशंसा मै तभी करूँगा, यदि वह अहिंसक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रांति","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0080","text":"क्रांति तो युगों के बाद आती है और वह मनुष्य को सजग कराने और सुधारने के लिए आती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रांति","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0081","text":"मनुष्य को प्रयत्न करना चाहिए और ईश्वर पर भरोसा रखना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0082","text":"जिसको ईश्वर बचाना चाहता है, उसे कौन मिटा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0083","text":"जिस ईश्वर ने अपने लाखों लोगों की सहायता की है, वह क्या तुम्हें छोड़ देगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0084","text":"ईश्वर की इस दुनियाँ में कहीं भी सदा रात नहीं रहती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0085","text":"जब तक ईश्वर हमारी रक्षा करता है, मारनेवाला कितना भी बलवान हो, हमें मार नहीं सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0086","text":"हम सोते है तब भी ईश्वर हमारी चौकीदारी करता है। फिर हम क्यों डरे?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0087","text":"जो ईश्वर में विश्वास रखता है, वह बीमारी का भी सद्पयोग कर लेता है। वह बीमारी से कभी नहीं हारता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0088","text":"जहां प्रेम है, वहीं ईश्वर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0089","text":"मै मानवता की सेवा के माध्यम से ही ईश्वर का साक्षात्कार का प्रयास कर रहा हु। क्योकि मै जानता हुं कि ईश्वर न तो स्वर्ग में है और न ही पाताल में है, वह हर किसी के दिल में मौजूद है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — ईश्वर","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0090","text":"गीता तो रत्नों की खान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — गीता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0091","text":"मन पर निंयत्रण करना सबसे कठिन काम है। इसके लिए उत्तम उपाय गीता का अध्ययन करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — गीता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0092","text":"अगर मुझे संसार की एक सर्वश्रेष्ठ पुस्तक चुनना हो तो मै गीता को चुनुँगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — गीता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0093","text":"देशभक्ति मनुष्य का पहला गुण है। इसके बिना वह दुनियाँ में सिर उठाकर नहीं चल सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — देशभक्ति","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0094","text":"दुनिया में देशभक्तो ने आज़ादी का मार्ग प्रशस्त किया है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — देशभक्ति","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0095","text":"क्रोध से बदले की भावना बढ़ती है और उसके भयंकर परिणाम होते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0096","text":"क्रोध पाप का मूल कारण है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0097","text":"हम जन्तुओ को तो मार डालते है पर अपने सीने में छिपे क्रोध को नहीं मारते, जो सचमुच मारने की चीज़ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0098","text":"क्रोध को जीतने में ही सच्ची मर्दानगी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0099","text":"क्रोध ख़ुद को तो जलाता ही है आसपास के संबद्ध लोगो भी पीड़ित कर देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0100","text":"क्रोध एक प्रकार का रोग है जिसे क्षणिक पागलपन भी कह सकते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0101","text":"क्रोध के बिना मनुष्य देवता के सामान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — क्रोध","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0102","text":"देश के युवक अगर चाहें तो वे बड़े से बड़े सत्कार्य आसानी से सम्पन्न कर सकते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नवयुवकों","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0103","text":"युवकों को अपने जोश का उपयोग होश के साथ करना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नवयुवकों","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0104","text":"अगर कोई मनुष्य अपना काम नियमित रूप से नहीं करता है, तो उसे सफ़लता नहीं मिल सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नियमितता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0105","text":"नियमितता सफलता की जननी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नियमितता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0106","text":"नियमितता जीवन की एक कसौटी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नियमितता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0107","text":"बूंद-बूंद से तालाब इसलिए भरता है क्योकि यह काम नियमित रूप से होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नियमितता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0108","text":"नियमितता के द्वारा मनुष्य बड़े से बड़ा सम्पन्न कर सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नियमितता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0109","text":"चरखा भारत की आर्थिक आज़ादी का प्रतीक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरखा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0110","text":"चरखे के बिना दूसरे उद्योग नहीं चल सकते है, वैसे ही जैसे यदि सूरज डूब जाए तो दूसरे ग्रह भी डूब जायेगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरखा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0111","text":"चरखा तो लंगड़े की लाठी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरखा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0112","text":"चरखा अहिंसा का प्रतीक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरखा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0113","text":"खेती किसान का धड़ है और चरखा हाथ-पैर।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरखा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0114","text":"मेरे लिए चरखे से अधिक प्रिय वस्तु कोई नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरखा","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0115","text":"चरित्र की संपत्ति दुनिया की सारी दौलत से बढ़कर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरित्र-निर्माण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0116","text":"चरित्र की रक्षा किसी भी मूल्य पर होनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरित्र-निर्माण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0117","text":"चरित्र की सीढ़ी है सदाचरण।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरित्र-निर्माण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0118","text":"चरित्र जीवन की सबसे मूल्यवान वस्तु है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरित्र-निर्माण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0119","text":"वयक्ति के चरित्र से ही राष्ट्र का अंदाजा लगाया जा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरित्र-निर्माण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0120","text":"शिक्षा का उद्देश्य चरित्र-निर्माण होना चाहिए। शिक्षा वही है जिसके द्वारा साहस का विकास हो, गुणों में वृद्धि हो और ऊंचे उदेश्यों के प्रति लगन जागे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — चरित्र-निर्माण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0121","text":"धर्म की परीक्षा दुःख में ही होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — धर्म","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0122","text":"जो धर्म सत्य और अहिंसा का विरोधी है, वह धर्म नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — धर्म","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0123","text":"धर्म तो उत्कृठ श्रद्धा का नाम है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — धर्म","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0124","text":"संकट के समय धर्म ही मनुष्य को उबार सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — धर्म","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0125","text":"धर्म भगवान तक पहुँचने का सेतु है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — धर्म","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0126","text":"धर्महीन मनुष्य बिना पतवार की नाव के समान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — धर्म","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0127","text":"प्रार्थना जीभ से नहीं होता है, ह्रदय से होता है। जो गूंगे और मूढ़ है, वे भी प्रार्थना कर सकते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0128","text":"प्रार्थना धर्म का प्राण और सार है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0129","text":"प्रार्थना के बिना भीतरी शांति नहीं मिल सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0130","text":"प्रार्थना अपनी योग्यता और दुर्बलता को स्वीकार करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0131","text":"प्रार्थना आत्मा की खुराक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0132","text":"प्रार्थना में असीम शक्ति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0133","text":"प्रार्थना याचना करना नहीं है, वह तो आत्मा की पुकार है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0134","text":"प्रार्थना तभी प्रार्थना है, जब वह अपने आप से निकलती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0135","text":"प्रार्थना पश्चाताप का एक चिन्ह है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0136","text":"मै अपना कोई काम, बिना प्रार्थना किये नहीं करता हु।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0137","text":"प्रार्थना आत्मशुद्धि का सहज और सरल साधन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0138","text":"मुझे शांति और सफलता प्रार्थना के द्वारा ही मिली है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0139","text":"प्रार्थना में तल्लीन हो जाना ही असली उपासना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रार्थना","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0140","text":"नम्रता से मनुष्य के ऐसे बहुत से काम बन सकते है, जो कठोरता से नहीं होते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नम्रता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0141","text":"नम्रता मनुष्य का आभूषण है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नम्रता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0142","text":"नम्रता अहिंसा का ही हिस्सा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नम्रता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0143","text":"नम्रता के पीछे स्वार्थ हो तो वह एक ढोंग है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — नम्रता","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0144","text":"पुस्तकों का मूल्य रत्नो से भी अधिक है। क्योकि बाहरी चमक-दमक दिखाते है जबकि पुस्तकें अंतकरण को प्रकाशित है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — पुस्तकें","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0145","text":"कुछ पुस्तकें मेरे जीवन के लिए मार्गदर्शिका बन गई, उनमे से एक एमर्सन की “अंटू डी लॉस्ट” है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — पुस्तकें","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0146","text":"गीता का मेर ऊपर काफी प्रभाव रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — पुस्तकें","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0147","text":"मेरे लिए तुलसी दास की रामायण भक्तिरस का बेस्ट ग्रन्थ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — पुस्तकें","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0148","text":"जहां प्रेम है वहां परमात्मा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रेम","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0149","text":"जहां प्रेम है, वहां डर का स्थान कहां ?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रेम","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0150","text":"प्रेम की गंथि से ही जगत बंधा हुआ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Mahatma Gandhi — प्रेम","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0151","text":"जीवन लम्बा होने की बजाय महान होना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0152","text":"हर व्यक्ति जो मिल का सिद्धान्त जानता हो कि एक देश दूसरे देश पर राज करने में फिट नहीं है, उसे ये भी स्वीकार करना चाहिये कि एक वर्ग दूसरे वर्ग पर राज करने में फिट नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0153","text":"उदासीनता लोगों को प्रभावित करने वाली सबसे खराब किस्म की बीमारी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0154","text":"यदि मुझे लगा कि संविधान का दुरुपयोग किया जा रहा है, तो मैं इसे सबसे पहले जलाऊंगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0155","text":"समानता एक कल्पना हो सकती है, लेकिन फिर भी इसे एक गवर्निंग सिद्धान्त रूप में स्वीकार करना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0156","text":"एक सुरक्षित सेना एक सुरक्षित सीमा से बेहतर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0157","text":"लोग और उनके धर्म, सामाजिक नैतिकता के आधार पर सामाजिक मानकों द्वारा परखे जाने चाहिए। अगर धर्म को लोगों के भले के लिये आवश्यक वस्तु मान लिया जायेगा तो और किसी मानक का मतलब नहीं होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0158","text":"बुद्धि का विकास मानव के अस्तित्व का अंतिम लक्ष्य होना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0159","text":"मैं ऐसे धर्म को मानता हूँ जो स्वतंत्रता, समानता, और भाई-चारा सिखाये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0160","text":"यह जरूरी है कि हम अपना दृष्टिकोण और हृदय जितना सभव हो अच्छा करें। इसी से हमारे और अन्य लोगों के जीवन में, अल्पकाल और दीर्घकाल दोनों में ही खुशियाँ आएगीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0161","text":"मैं एक समुदाय की प्रगति का माप महिलाओं द्वारा हासिल प्रगति के माप से करता हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0162","text":"एक महान व्यक्ति एक प्रख्यात व्यक्ति से एक ही बिंदु पर भिन्न हैं कि, महान व्यक्ति समाज का सेवक बनने के लिए तत्पर रहता हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0163","text":"मनुष्य नश्वर हैं। ऐसे विचार भी होते हैं। एक विचार को प्रचार-प्रसार की जरूरत है जैसे एक पौधे में पानी की जरूरत की जरूरत होती है। अन्यथा दोनों मुरझा जायेंगे और मर जायेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0164","text":"इतिहास बताता है कि जहाँ नैतिकता और अर्थशास्त्र के बीच संघर्ष होता है वहां जीत हमेशा अर्थशास्त्र की होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0165","text":"निहित स्वार्थों को तब तक स्वेच्छा से नहीं छोड़ा   गया है जब तक कि मजबूर करने के लिए पर्याप्त बल ना लगाया गया हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0166","text":"एक सफल क्रांति के लिए सिर्फ असंतोष का होना काफी नहीं है। जिसकी आवश्यकता है वो है राजनीतिक और सामाजिक अधिकारों के महत्व, जरुरत व न्याय में पूर्णतया गहराई से दोष।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0167","text":"जब तक आप सामाजिक स्वतंत्रता नहीं हासिल कर लेते, कानून आपको जो भी स्वतंत्रता देता है वो आपके लिये बेमानी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0168","text":"हम आदि से अन्त तक भारतीय हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0169","text":"सागर में मिलकर अपनी पहचान खो देने वाली पानी की एक बूँद के विपरीत, इंसान जिस समाज में रहता है वहां अपनी पहचान नहीं खोता। मानव का जीवन स्वतंत्र है। वो सिर्फ समाज के विकास के लिए नहीं पैदा हुआ है, बल्कि स्वयं के विकास के लिए पैदा हुआ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0170","text":"पति-पत्नी के बीच का सम्बन्ध घनिष्ट मित्रों के सम्बन्ध के समान होना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0171","text":"हिंदू धर्म में, विवेक, कारण, और स्वतंत्र सोच के विकास के लिए कोई गुंजाइश नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0172","text":"मनुष्य एवम उसके धर्म को समाज के द्वारा नैतिकता के आधार पर चयन करना चाहिये। अगर धर्म को ही मनुष्य के लिए सब कुछ मान लिया जायेगा तो किन्ही और मानको का कोई मूल्य नहीं रह जायेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0173","text":"एक सफल क्रांति के लिए सिर्फ असंतोष का होना ही काफी नहीं है, बल्कि इसके लिए न्याय, राजनीतिक और सामाजिक अधिकारों में गहरी आस्था का होना भी बहुत आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0174","text":"इतिहास गवाह है कि जहाँ नैतिकता और अर्थशास्त्र के बीच संघर्ष होता है वहां जीत हमेशा अर्थशास्त्र की होती है। निहित स्वार्थों को तब तक स्वेच्छा से नहीं छोड़ा गया है जब तक कि मजबूर करने के लिए पर्याप्त बल ना लगाया गया हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0175","text":"किसी भी कौम का विकास उस कौम की महिलाओं के विकास से मापा जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0176","text":"एक महान व्यक्ति एक प्रख्यात व्यक्ति से एक ही बिंदु पर भिन्न हैं कि महान व्यक्ति समाज का सेवक बनने के लिए तत्पर रहता हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0177","text":"जो व्यक्ति अपनी मौत को हमेशा याद रखता है वह सदा अच्छे कार्य में लगा रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0178","text":"जिस तरह मनुष्य नश्वर है ठीक उसी तरह विचार भी नश्वर हैं। जिस तरह पौधे को पानी की जरूरत पड़ती है उसी तरह एक विचार को प्रचार-प्रसार की जरुरत होती है वरना दोनों मुरझा कर मर जाते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0179","text":"जिस तरह हर एक व्यक्ति यह सिधांत दोहराता हैं कि एक देश दुसरे देश पर शासन नहीं कर सकता उसी प्रकार उसे यह भी मानना होगा कि एक वर्ग दुसरे पर शासन नहीं कर सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0180","text":"आज भारतीय दो अलग-अलग विचारधाराओं द्वारा शासित हो रहे हैं। उनके राजनीतिक आदर्श जो संविधान के प्रस्तावना में इंगित हैं वो स्वतंत्रता, समानता, और भाई-चारे को स्थापित करते हैं और उनके धर्म में समाहित सामाजिक आदर्श इससे इनकार करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0181","text":"एक महान व्यक्ति एक प्रतिष्ठित व्यक्ति से अलग है क्योंकि वह समाज का सेवक बनने के लिए तैयार रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0182","text":"क़ानून और व्यवस्था राजनीति रूपी शरीर की दवा है और जब राजनीति रूपी शरीर बीमार पड़ जाएँ तो दवा अवश्य दी जानी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0183","text":"जो समाज समानता नहीं जानता, वह सभ्य नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0184","text":"जब तक आप सामाजिक स्वतंत्रता नहीं हांसिल कर लेते, क़ानून आपको जो भी स्वतंत्रता देता है वो आपके किसी काम की नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0185","text":"यदि हम एक संयुक्त एकीकृत आधुनिक भारत चाहते हैं, तो सभी धर्मों के धर्मग्रंथों की संप्रभुता का अंत होना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0186","text":"राजनीतिक अत्याचार सामाजिक अत्याचार की तुलना में कुछ भी नहीं है और एक सुधारक जो समाज को खारिज कर देता है वो सरकार को खारिज कर देने वाले राजनीतिज्ञ से ज्यादा साहसी हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0187","text":"लोग और उनके धर्म, सामाजिक नैतिकता के आधार पर, सामाजिक मानकों द्वारा परखे जाने चाहिए। अगर धर्म को लोगों के भले के लिये आवश्यक वस्तु मान लिया जायेगा तो और किसी मानक का मतलब नहीं होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0188","text":"समानता एक कल्पना हो सकती है, लेकिन फिर भी इसे एक गवर्निंग सिद्धांत रूप में स्वीकार करना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0189","text":"हमारे पास यह स्वतंत्रता किस लिए है? हमारे पास ये स्वत्नत्रता इसलिए है ताकि हम अपने सामाजिक व्यवस्था, जो असमानता, भेद-भाव और अन्य चीजों से भरी है, जो हमारे मौलिक अधिकारों से टकराव में है, को सुधार सकें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0190","text":"मेरे नाम की जय-जयकार करने से अच्‍छा है, मेरे बताए हुए रास्‍ते पर चलें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0191","text":"रात रातभर मैं इसलिये जागता हूँ क्‍योंकि मेरा समाज सो रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0192","text":"जो कौम अपना इतिहास नहीं जानती, वह कौम कभी भी इतिहास नहीं बना सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0193","text":"अपने भाग्य के बजाय अपनी मजबूती पर विश्वास करो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0194","text":"मैं राजनीति में सुख भोगने नहीं बल्कि अपने सभी दबे-कुचले भाईयों को उनके अधिकार दिलाने आया हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0195","text":"मनुवाद को जड़ से समाप्‍त करना मेरे जीवन का प्रथम लक्ष्‍य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0196","text":"जो धर्म जन्‍म से एक को श्रेष्‍ठ और दूसरे को नीच बनाए रखे, वह धर्म नहीं, गुलाम बनाए रखने का षड़यंत्र है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0197","text":"राष्‍ट्रवाद तभी औचित्‍य ग्रहण कर सकता है, जब लोगों के बीच जाति, नरल या रंग का अन्‍तर भुलाकर उसमें सामाजिक भ्रातृत्‍व को सर्वोच्‍च स्‍थान दिया जाये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0198","text":"मैं तो जीवन भर कार्य कर चुका हूँ अब इसके लिए नौजवान आगे आए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0199","text":"अच्छा दिखने के लिए मत जिओ बल्कि अच्छा बनने के लिए जिओ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0200","text":"जो झुक सकता है वह सारी दुनिया को झुका भी सकता है!","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0201","text":"लोकतंत्र सरकार का महज एक रूप नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0202","text":"एक इतिहासकार, सटीक, ईमानदार और निष्‍पक्ष होना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0203","text":"संविधान, यह एक मात्र वकीलों का दस्‍तावेज नहीं। यह जीवन का एक माध्‍यम है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0204","text":"किसी का भी स्‍वाद बदला जा सकता है लेकिन जहर को अमृत में परिवर्तित नही किया जा सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0205","text":"न्‍याय हमेशा समानता के विचार को पैदा करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0206","text":"मन की स्‍वतंत्रता ही वास्‍तविक स्‍वतंत्रता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0207","text":"ज्ञान व्‍‍यक्ति के जीवन का आधार हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0208","text":"शिक्षा जितनी पुरूषों के लिए आवशयक है उतनी ही महिलाओं के लिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0209","text":"जो लोग ये सोचते हैं कि शिक्षा व्यर्थ है, वे खुद को ही गुलाम बनाए रखते हैं (स्रोत: शिक्षा पर संबोधन, भीमराव अंबेडकर, 1942)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0210","text":"महात्‍मा आये और चले गये परन्‍तु अछुत, अछुत ही बने हुए हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0211","text":"स्‍वतंत्रता का रहस्‍य, साहस है और साहस एक पार्टी में व्‍यक्तियों के संयोजन से पैदा होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0212","text":"इस दुनिया में महान प्रयासों से प्राप्‍त किया गया को छोडकर और कुछ भी बहुमूल्‍य नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0213","text":"इतिहास गवाह है कि अधिकार कभी मांगने से नहीं, बल्कि छीनने से मिलते हैं (स्रोत: बंबई सम्मेलन, भीमराव अंबेडकर, 1935)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — सुवचन","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0214","text":"मुस्लिम आक्रान्ता निःसंदेह हिन्दुओं के विरुद्ध घृणा के गीत गाते हुए आए थे। परन्तु वे घृणा का गीत गाकर और मार्ग में कुछ मंदिरों को आग लगाकर ही वापस नहीं लौटे। ऐसा होता तो वरदान माना जाता। वे इतने ही नकारात्मक परिणाम से संतुष्ट नहीं थे। उन्होंने तो भारत में इस्लाम का पौधा रोपा। इस पौधे का विकास बखूबी हुआ और यह एक बड़ा ओक का पेड़ बन गया।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0215","text":"मुसलमान कभी भी मातृभूमि के भक्त नहीं हो सकते। हिन्दुओं से कभी उनके दिल मिल नहीं सकते। देश में रह कर शत्रुता पालते रहने की अपेक्षा उन्हें अलग राष्ट्र दे देना चाहिए। भारतीय मुसलमानों का यह कहना है कि वे पहले मुसलमान हैं और फिर भारतीय हैं। उनकी निष्ठाएं देश-बाह्य होती हैं। देश से बाहर के मुस्लिम राष्ट्रों की सहायता लेकर भारत में इस्लाम का वर्चस्व स्थापित करने की उनकी तैयारी है। जिस देश में मुस्लिम राज्य नहीं हो, वहाँ यदि इस्लामी कानून और उस देश के कानून में टकराव पैदा हुआ तो इस्लामी कानून ही श्रेष्ठ समझा जाना चाहिए। देश का कानून झटक कर इस्लामी कानून मानना मुसलमान समर्थनीय समझते हैं। -- ‘पाकिस्तान अथवा भारत का विभाजन’","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0216","text":"ब्राह्मण, क्षत्रिय, वैश्य और शूद्र आदि प्रकार के भेद सिर्फ हिन्दू धर्म में ही हैं, ऐसी बात नहीं। इस तरह के भेद ईसाई और इस्लाम में भी दिखाई देते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0217","text":"यदि मैं इस्लाम स्वीकार करूँगा तो इस देश में मुसलमानों की संख्या दूनी हो जाएगी और मुस्लिम प्रभुत्व का खतरा उत्पन्न हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0218","text":"जो कोई भी व्यक्ति एशिया के नक्शे को देखेगा उसे यह ध्यान में आ जाएगा कि किस तरह यह देश दो पाटों के बीच फंस गया है। एक ओर चीन व जापान जैसे भिन्न संस्कृतियों के राष्ट्रों का फंदा है तो दूसरी ओर तुर्की, पर्शिया और अफगानिस्तान जैसे तीन मुस्लिम राष्ट्रों का फंदा पड़ा हुआ है। इन दोनों के बीच फंसे हुए इस देश को बड़ी सतर्कता से रहना चाहिए, ऐसा हमें लगता है... इन परिस्थितियों में चीन एवं जापान में से किसी ने यदि हमला किया तो... उनके हमले का सब लोग एकजुट होकर सामना करेंगे। मगर स्वाधीन हो चुके हिन्दुस्थान पर यदि तुर्की, पर्शिया या अफगानिस्तान जैसे तीन मुस्लिम राष्ट्रों में से किसी एक ने भी हमला किया तो क्या कोई इस बात की आश्वस्ति दे सकता है कि इस हमले का सब लोग एकजुटता से सामना करेंगे? हम तो यह आश्वस्ति नहीं दे सकते। -- 18 जनवरी, 1929 को ‘नेहरू कमेटी की योजना और हिन्दुस्थान का भविष्य’ शीर्षक से 'बहिष्कृत भारत' में एक अग्रलेख","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0219","text":"इस्लाम एक क्लोज कॉर्पोरेशन है और इसकी विशेषता ही यह है कि मुस्लिम और गैर मुस्लिम के बीच वास्तविक भेद करता है। इस्लाम का बंधुत्व मानवता का सार्वभौम बंधुत्व नहीं है। यह बंधुत्व केवल मुसलमान का मुसलमान के प्रति है। दूसरे शब्दों में इस्लाम कभी एक सच्चे मुसलमान को ऐसी अनुमति नहीं देगा कि आप भारत को अपनी मातृभूमि मानो और किसी हिन्दू को अपना आत्मीय बंधु।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0220","text":"मुसलमानों में एक और उन्माद का दुर्गुण है। जो कैनन लॉ या जिहाद के नाम से प्रचलित है। एक मुसलमान शासक के लिए जरूरी है कि जब तक पूरी दुनिया में इस्लाम की सत्ता न फैल जाए तब तक चैन से न बैठे। इस तरह पूरी दुनिया दो हिस्सों में बंटी है दार-उल-इस्लाम (इस्लाम के अधीन) और दार-उल-हर्ब (युद्ध के मुहाने पर)। चाहे तो सारे देश एक श्रेणी के अधीन आयें अथवा अन्य श्रेणी में। तकनीकी तौर पर यह मुस्लिम शासकों का कर्तव्य है कि कौन ऐसा करने में सक्षम है। जो दार-उल-हर्ब को दर उल इस्लाम में परिवर्तित कर दे। भारत में मुसलमान हिजरत में रुचि लेते हैं तो वे जिहाद का हिस्सा बनने से भी हिचकेंगे नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0221","text":"प्रत्येक हिन्दू के मन में यह प्रश्न उठ रहा था कि पाकिस्तान बनने के बाद हिन्दुस्तान से साम्प्रदायिकता का मामला हटेगा या नहीं, यह एक जायज प्रश्न था और इस पर विचार किया जाना जरूरी था। यह भी स्वीकारना पड़ेगा कि पाकिस्तान के बन जाने से हिन्दुस्तान साम्प्रदायिक प्रश्न से मुक्त नहीं हो पाया। पाकिस्तान की सीमाओं की पुनर्रचना कर भले ही इसे सजातीय राज्य बना दिया गया हो लेकिन भारत को तो एक मिश्रित राज्य ही बना रहेगा। हिन्दुस्तान में मुसलमान सभी जगह बिखरे हुए हैं, इसलिए वे ज्यादातर कस्बों में एकत्रित होते हैं। इसलिए इनकी सीमाओं की पुनर्रचना और सजातीयता के आधार पर निर्धारण सरल नहीं है। हिन्दुस्तान को सजातीय बनाने का एक ही रास्ता है कि जनसंख्या की अदला-बदली सुनिश्चित हो, जब तक यह नहीं किया जाता तब तक यह स्वीकारना पड़ेगा कि पाकिस्तान के निर्माण के बाद भी, बहुसंख्यक बनाम अल्पसंख्यक की समस्या और हिन्दुस्तान की राजनीति में असंगति पहले की तरह बनी रहेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0222","text":"मुसलमानों में इन बुराइयों का होना दुःखद है। किन्तु उससे भी अधिक दुःखद तथ्य यह है कि भारत के मुसलमानों में समाज सुधार का ऐसा कोई संगठित आंदोलन नहीं उभरा जो इन बुराइयों का सफलतापूर्वक उन्मूलन कर सके। हिंदुओं में भी अनेक सामाजिक बुराइयां हैं, परन्तु संतोष की बात यह है कि उनमें से अनेक इनकी विद्यमानता के प्रति सजग हैं और उनमें से कुछ उन बुराइयों के उन्मूलन हेतु सक्रिय तौर पर आन्दोलन भी चला रहे हैं। दूसरी ओर मुसलमान यह महसूस ही नहीं करते कि ये बुराइयां हैं, परिणामतः वे उनके निवारण हेतु सक्रियता भी नहीं दर्शाते। इसके विपरीत, अपनी मौजूदा प्रथाओं में किसी भी परिवर्तन का विरोध करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0223","text":"मुसलमानों की सोच में लोकतंत्र प्रमुखता नहीं है। उनकी सोच को प्रभावित करने वाला तत्व यह है कि लोकतंत्र प्रमुख नहीं है। उनकी सोच को प्रभावित करने वाला तत्व यह है कि लोकतंत्र, जिसका मतलब बहुमत का शासन है, हिन्दुओं के विरुद्ध संघर्ष में मुसलमानों पर क्या असर डालेगा। क्या उससे वे मजबूत होंगे अथवा कमजोर? यदि लोकतंत्र से वे कमजोर पड़ते हैं तो वे लोकतंत्र नहीं चाहेंगे। वे किसी मुस्लिम रियासत में हिंदू प्रजा का मुस्लिम शासक की पकड़ कमजोर करने के बजाए अपने निकम्मे राज्य को वरीयता देंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0224","text":"मुस्लिम संप्रदाय में राजनीतिक और सामाजिक गतिरोध का केवल ही कारण बताया जा सकता है। मुसलमान सोचते हैं कि हिंदुओं और मुसलमानों को सतत संघर्षरत रहना चाहिए। हिंदू मुसलमानों पर अपना प्रभुत्व स्थापित करने का प्रयास करते हैं, और मुसलमान अपनी शासक होने की ऐतिहासिक हैसियसत बनाए रखने का।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0225","text":"मुसलमानों द्वारा राजनीति में अपराधियों के तौर-तरीके अपनाया और दंगे इस बात के पर्याप्त संकेत हैं कि गुंडागर्दी उनकी राजनीति का एक स्थापित तरीका हो गया है। चेकों के विरुद्ध सुडेटेन जर्मनों ने जिन तौर-तरीकों को अपनाया था वे उसका जानबूझकर तथा समझते हुए अनुकरण करते प्रतीत हो रहे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0226","text":"पर्दा प्रथा की वजह से मुस्लिम महिलाएं अन्य जातियों की महिलाओं से पिछड़ जाती हैं। वो किसी भी तरह की बाहरी गतिविधियों में भाग नहीं ले पातीं हैं जिसके चलते उनमें एक प्रकार की दासता और हीनता की मनोवृत्ति बनी रहती है। उनमें ज्ञान प्राप्ति की इच्छा भी नहीं रहती क्योंकि उन्हें यही सिखाया जाता है कि वो घर की चारदीवारी के बाहर वे अन्य किसी बात में रुचि न लें। पर्दे वाली महिलाएं प्रायः डरपोक, निस्साहय, शर्मीली और जीवन में किसी भी प्रकार का संघर्ष करने के अयोग्य हो जाती हैं। भारत में पर्दा करने वाली महिलाओं की विशाल संख्या को देखते हुए कोई भी आसानी से ये समझ सकता है कि पर्दे की समस्या कितनी व्यापक और गंभीर है। -- 'पाकिस्तान, अथवा भारत का विभाजन'","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0227","text":"पर्दा प्रथा ने मुस्लिम पुरुषों की नैतिकता पर विपरीत प्रभाव डाला है। पर्दा प्रथा के कारण कोई मुसलमान अपने घर-परिवार से बाहर की महिलाओं से कोई परिचय नहीं कर पाता। घऱ की महिलाओं से भी उसका संपर्क यदा-कदा बातचीत तक ही सीमित रहता है। बच्चों और वृद्धों के अलावा पुरुष अन्य महिलाओं से हिल-मिल नहीं सकता, अपने अंतरंग साथी से भी नहीं मिल पाता। महिलाओं से पुरुषों की ये पृथकता निश्चित रूप से पुरुष के नैतिक बल पर विकृत प्रभाव डालती है। ये कहने के लिए किसी मनोवैज्ञानिक विश्लेषण की आवश्यकता नहीं कि ऐसी सामाजिक प्रणाली से जो पुरुषों और महिलाओं के बीच के संपर्क को काट दे उससे यौनाचार के प्रति ऐसी अस्वस्थ प्रवृत्ति का सृजन होता है जो आप्राकृतिक और अन्य गंदी आदतों और साधनों को अपनाने के लिए प्रेरित करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0228","text":"ऐसी पृथकता का मुस्लिम महिलाओं के स्वास्थ्य पर बुरा असर पड़ता है। वो खून की कमी, टीबी, पायरिया और कई अन्य रोगों से पीड़ित हो जाती हैं। उनका शरीर भी मजबूत नहीं रह पाता और उनकी कमर भी झुकती जाती है, उनकी हड्डियां निकल आती हैं, हाथ और पांव में खम पड़ जाता है, वे कुरूप हो जाती हैं। पसलियों, जो़ड़ों और ज्यादातर सभी हडिड्यों में दर्द रहता है। उनमें हृदय की धड़कन बढ़ने का सिलसिला भी प्राय: पाया जाता है। इन सभी कमजोरियों के फलस्वरूप प्रसूति काल (डिलिवरी) के दौरान अधिकांश की मृत्यु हो जाती है। पर्दाप्रथा के कारण मुस्लिम महिलाओं का मानसिक और नैतिक विकास भी नहीं हो पाता। स्वस्थ्य सामाजिक जीवन से वंचित रहने से उनमें गलत प्रवृत्ति आ जाती है। बाहरी दुनिया से बिल्कुल अलग-थलग रहने के कारण उनका ध्यान तुच्छ पारिवारिक झगड़ों में ही उलझा रहता है। इसका परिणाम संकीर्ण सोच और संकुचित दृष्टिकोण के रूप में सामने आता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0229","text":"ऐसा नहीं है कि पर्दा और ऐसी ही अन्य बुराइयां देश के कुछ भागों में हिंदुओं के कई वर्गों में प्रचलित नहीं हैं। परन्तु अन्तर केवल यही है कि मुसलमानों में पर्दा-प्रथा को एक धार्मिक आधार पर मान्यता दी गई है, लेकिन हिन्दुओं में ऐसा नहीं है। हिन्दुओं की तुलना में मुसलमानों में पर्दा-प्रथा की जड़े गहरी हैं। मुसलमानों में पर्दाप्रथा एक वास्तविक समस्या है और जबकि हिंदुओं में ऐसा नहीं है। मुसलमानों ने इसे समाप्त करने का कभी प्रयास किया हो इसका भी कोई साक्ष्य नहीं मिलता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इस्लाम और मुसलमान पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0230","text":"जब मुस्लिम आक्रमण होने लगे, तब हमें सिंध का उदाहरण मिलता है, जहां पर उत्पीड़न । अत्याचार ही निस्संदेह बौद्ध धर्म के पतन का कारण बना। यह अत्याचार तथा उत्पीड़न मुसलमानों के आक्रमण तक जारी रहा। -- डॉ. अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी) भाग 7, पेज नंबर 102","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0231","text":"इसमें कोई संदेह नहीं है कि भारत में बौद्ध धर्म का पतन मुसलमानों के आक्रमणों के कारण हुआ था। -- डॉ. अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी) भाग 7, पेज नंबर 92","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0232","text":"इस्लाम की तलवार ने बौद्धों के पुरोहितो को बुरी तरह नष्ट कर दिया। -- डॉ. अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय(हिंदी) भाग 7, पेज नंबर 93","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0233","text":"मुसलमान विचारकों की दृष्टि में मूर्तिपूजा और बौद्ध धर्म,दोनों एक-दूसरे के पर्याय हैं।मुसलमानों के लिए मूर्तिपूजा तथा बौद्ध धर्म एक जैसे ही थे।इस प्रकार मूर्तिभंजन करने का लक्ष्य, बौद्ध धर्म को नष्ट करने का लक्ष्य बन गया। -- डॉ. अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिन्दी) भाग 7, पेज  92","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0234","text":"मुसलमान सेनापत्तियों ने बहुत बड़ी संख्या में भिक्षुओं को मौत के घाट उतार दिया।बौद्ध भिक्षुओं को मुसलमान आक्रमणकारियों ने अपनी तलवार से किस प्रकार नष्ट किया,इसका वर्णन स्वयं मुस्लिम इतिहासकारों ने किया है। -- डॉ.अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी) भाग 7, पेज 95","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0235","text":"बौद्ध पुजारियों का मुसलमान आक्रमणकारियों द्वारा संहार किया गया।उन्होंने जड़ पर ही कुल्हाड़ी मारी।धम्मोपदेष्टा की हत्या कर इस्लाम ने बौद्ध धर्म की ही हत्या कर दी।यह एक घोर संकट था,जो भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के लिए विनाशकारी सिद्ध हुआ। -- डॉ.अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी), भाग 7, पेज 96","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0236","text":"इस्लाम धर्म के अस्तित्व में आने से पहले बौद्ध धर्म बैक्ट्रिया, पार्थिया, अफगानिस्तान, गांधार तथा चीनी तुर्किस्तान का धर्म था और एक प्रकार से यह धर्म समूचे एशिया में फैला हुआ था। इन सब देशों में इस्लाम ने बौद्ध धर्म को नष्ट किया। -- डॉ० अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी) भाग 7, पेज  92","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0237","text":"इस्लाम की तलवार ने पुजारियों पर भारी आघात किया। इससे वह या तो नष्ट हो गया या भारत के बाहर चला गया। बौद्ध धर्म के दीपक को प्रज्वलित रखने के लिए कोई भी जीवित नहीं बचा। -- डॉ. अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी) भाग 7, पृष्ठ संख्या 96","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0238","text":"इस्लाम ने बौद्ध धर्म को केवल भारत में ही नष्ट नहीं किया, बल्कि वह जहां भी गया, वहीं उसने बौद्ध धर्म को मिटाने में कोई कोर-कसर नहीं छोड़ी। -- डॉ. अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिंदी) भाग 7, पेज नंबर 92","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0239","text":"मुसलमान आक्रमणकारियों ने जिन बौद्ध विश्वविद्यालयों को लूटा, इनमें कुछ नाम नालंदा, विक्रमशिला, जगद्दल, ओदंतपूरी के विश्वविद्यालय हैं। उन्होंने बौद्ध मठों को भी तहस-नहस कर दिया, जो सारे देश में स्थित थे। हजारों की संख्या में भिक्षु भारत से बाहर भागकर नेपाल, तिब्बत और कई स्थानों में चले गए। मुसलमान सेनापतियों ने बहुत बड़ी संख्या में भिक्षुओं को मौत के घाट उतार दिया। -- डॉ० अम्बेडकर सम्पूर्ण वाड्मय (हिन्दी), भाग 7, पृष्ठ संख्या 95","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — भारत में बौद्ध धर्म के ह्रास के कारणों पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0240","text":"योगेन्द्र नाथ मंडल","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — B.R. Ambedkar — इन्हें भी देखें","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0241","text":"तुम मुझे खून दो और मैं तुम्हें आज़ादी दूँगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0242","text":"जब हम खड़े हों, तब आज़ाद हिन्द फौज को एक ग्रेनाइट की दीवार के समान होना होगा; जब हम आगे बढ़ें, तब आज़ाद हिन्द फौज को एक स्ट्रीमरोलर के समान होना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0243","text":"संघर्ष में मनुष्य का चरित्र आकार लेता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0244","text":"याद रखिए सबसे बड़ा अपराध अन्याय सहना और गलत के साथ समझौता करना हैं ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0245","text":"एक सच्चे सैनिक को सैन्य और अध्यात्मिक दोनों प्रशिक्षण की जरुरत होती हैं ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0246","text":"इतिहास में कभी भी विचार-विमर्श से कोई ठोस परवर्तन नहीं हासिल किया गया हैं ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0247","text":"राष्ट्रवाद मानव जाति के उच्चतम आदर्शों सत्यम, शिवम्, सुन्दरम् से प्रेरित हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0248","text":"मेरे मन में कोई संदेह नहीं है कि हमारे देश की प्रमुख समस्याएं गरीबी,अशिक्षा, बीमारी, कुशल उत्पादन एवं वितरण सिर्फ समाजवादी तरीके से ही की जा सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0249","text":"किसी एक विचार के लिए यदि कोई मरता है तो वह विचार उसके मरने के बाद भी हजारों लोगों में जीवित रहती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0250","text":"आज हमारे अन्दर बस एक ही इच्छा होनी चाहिए, मरने की इच्छा ताकि भारत जी सके! एक शहीद की मौत मरने की इच्छा ताकि स्वतंत्रता का मार्ग शहीदों के खून से प्रशस्त हो सके.","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0251","text":"एक सच्चे सैनिक को सैन्य और आध्यात्मिक दोनों ही प्रशिक्षण की ज़रुरत होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0252","text":"देशभक्ति के बिना जीवन अधूरा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0253","text":"अगर संघर्ष न रहे, किसी भी भय का सामना न करना पड़े, तब जीवन का आधा स्वाद ही समाप्त हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0254","text":"याद रखें – अन्याय सहना और गलत के साथ समझौता करना सबसे बड़ा अपराध है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0255","text":"मैंने जीवन में कभी भी खुशामद नहीं की है। दूसरों को अच्छी लगने वाली बातें करना मुझे नहीं आता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0256","text":"कष्टों का, निसंदेह एक आंतरिक नैतिक मूल्य होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0257","text":"मुझे यह नहीं मालूम कि स्वतंत्रता के इस युद्ध में हम में से कौन कौन जीवित बचेंगे। परन्तु मैं यह जानता हूँ कि अंत में विजय हमारी ही होगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0258","text":"ये हमारा कर्तव्य है कि हम अपनी स्वतंत्रता का मोल अपने खून से चुकाएं। हमें अपने बलिदान और परिश्रम से जो आज़ादी मिलेगी, हमारे अन्दर उसकी रक्षा करने की ताकत होनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0259","text":"तुम मुझे खून दो, मैं तुम्हें आजादी दूंगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0260","text":"मेरे मन में कोई संदेह नहीं है कि हमारे देश की प्रमुख समस्याओं जैसे गरीबी, अशिक्षा, बीमारी, कुशल उत्पादन एवं वितरण का समाधान सिर्फ समाजवादी तरीके से ही किया जा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0261","text":"व्यर्थ की बातों में समय खोना मुझे जरा भी अच्छा नहीं लगता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0262","text":"आज हमारे अन्दर बस एक ही इच्छा होनी चाहिए – मरने की इच्छा ताकि भारत जी सके। एक शहीद की मौत मरने की इच्छा ताकि स्वतंत्रता का मार्ग शहीदों के खून से प्रशस्त हो सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0263","text":"राष्ट्रवाद मानव जाति के उच्चतम आदर्श सत्य, शिव और सुन्दर से प्रेरित है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0264","text":"भारत में राष्ट्रवाद ने एक ऐसी सृजनात्मक शक्ति का संचार किया है जो सदियों से लोगों के अन्दर सुसुप्त पड़ी थी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0265","text":"यदि आपको अस्थायी रूप से झुकना पड़े, तब वीरों की भांति झुकना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0266","text":"समझौतापरस्ती सबसे बड़ी अपवित्र वस्तु है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0267","text":"संघर्ष ने मुझे मनुष्य बनाया है। मुझमे आत्मविश्वास उत्पन्न हुआ, जो पहले नहीं था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0268","text":"मुझ में जन्मजात प्रतिभा तो नहीं थी, परन्तु कठोर परिश्रम से बचने की प्रवृति मुझ में कभी नहीं रही।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0269","text":"जीवन में प्रगति का आशय यह है कि शंका संदेह उठते रहें और उनके समाधान के प्रयास का क्रम चलता रहे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0270","text":"हम संघर्षों और उनके समाधानों द्वारा ही आगे बढ़ते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0271","text":"श्रद्धा की कमी ही सारे कष्टों और दुखों की जड़ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0272","text":"मैं संकट एवं विपदाओं से भयभीत नहीं होता। संकटपूर्ण दिन आने पर भी मैं भागूँगा नहीं, वरन आगे बढकर कष्टों को सहन करूँगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0273","text":"इतना तो आप भी मानेंगे कि एक न एक दिन तो मैं जेल से अवश्य मुक्त हो जाऊँगा, क्योंकि प्रत्येक दुःख का अंत होना अवश्यम्भावी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0274","text":"हमें अधीर नहीं होना चहिये। न ही यह आशा करनी चाहिए कि जिस प्रश्न का उत्तर खोजने में न जाने कितने ही लोगों ने अपना सम्पूर्ण जीवन समर्पित कर दिया, उसका उत्तर हमें एक-दो दिन में प्राप्त हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0275","text":"जहाँ शहद का अभाव हो वहां गुड़ से ही शहद का कार्य निकालना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0276","text":"असफलताएं कभी-कभी सफलता की स्तम्भ होती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0277","text":"सुबह से पहले अँधेरी घडी अवश्य आती है। बहादुर बनो और संघर्ष जारी रखो ,क्योंकि स्वतंत्रता निकट है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0278","text":"समय से पूर्व की परिपक्वता अच्छी नहीं होती, चाहे वह किसी वृक्ष की हो, या व्यक्ति की। उसकी हानि आगे चल कर भुगतनी ही होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0279","text":"साथियों! आपने स्वेच्छा से उस मिशन को स्वीकार किया है, जो उतना महान है, जिसकी मानव ह्रदय कल्पना भी नहीं कर सकता है। ऐसे मिशन की पूर्ति के लिए कोई भी बलिदान बहुत महान नहीं होता है, किसी के जीवन का बलिदान भी नहीं। आप आज भारत के राष्ट्रीय सम्मान के संरक्षक और भारत की आशाओं एवं आकांक्षाओं के प्रतीक हैं। इसलिए ऐसे पेश आओ कि आपके देशवासी आपको आशीर्वाद दे सकें और आप पर गर्व कर सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0280","text":"अपने कॉलेज जीवन की देहलीज पर खड़े होकर मुझे अनुभव हुआ, कि जीवन का कोई अर्थ और उद्देश्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0281","text":"स्वामी विवेकानंद का यह कथन बिलकुल सत्य है, यदि तुम्हारे पास लोह शिराएं हैं और कुशाग्र बुद्धि है, तो तुम सारे विश्व को अपने चरणों में झुका सकते हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0282","text":"मुझे जीवन में एक निश्चित लक्ष्य को पूरा करना है। मेरा जन्म उसी के लिए हुआ है। मुझे नैतिक विचारों की धारा में नहीं बहना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0283","text":"निसंदेह बचपन और युवावस्था में पवित्रता और संयम अतिआवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0284","text":"मैं जीवन की अनिश्चितता से जरा भी नहीं घबराता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0285","text":"मैंने अमूल्य जीवन का इतना समय व्यर्थ ही नष्ट कर दिया। यह सोच कर बहुत ही दुःख होता है। कभी कभी यह पीड़ा असह्य हो उठती है। मनुष्य जीवन पाकर भी जीवन का अर्थ समझ में नहीं आया। यदि मैं अपनी मंजिल पर नहीं पहुँच पाया, तो यह जीवन व्यर्थ है। इसकी क्या सार्थकता है?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0286","text":"भविष्य अब भी मेरे हाथ में है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0287","text":"मेरे जीवन के अनुभवों में एक यह भी है कि मुझे यह आशा है कि कोई-न-कोई किरण उबार लेती है और जीवन से दूर भटकने नहीं देती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0288","text":"चरित्र निर्माण ही छात्रों का मुख्य कर्तव्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0289","text":"मैं चाहता हूँ चरित्र, ज्ञान और कार्य।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0290","text":"हमें केवल कार्य करने का अधिकार है। कर्म ही हमारा कर्तव्य है। कर्म के फल का स्वामी वह (भगवान) है, हम नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0291","text":"कर्म के बंधन को तोडना बहुत कठिन कार्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0292","text":"मैंने अपने छोटे से जीवन का बहुत सारा समय व्यर्थ में ही खो दिया है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0293","text":"माँ का प्यार सबसे गहरा होता है, स्वार्थ रहित होता है। इसको किसी भी प्रकार नापा नहीं जा सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0294","text":"जिस व्यक्ति में सनक नहीं होती, वह कभी भी महान नहीं बन सकता। परन्तु सभी पागल व्यक्ति महान नहीं बन जाते क्योंकि सभी पागल व्यक्ति प्रतिभाशाली नहीं होते। आखिर क्यों ? कारण यह है कि केवल पागलपन ही काफी नहीं है। इसके अतिरिक्त कुछ और भी आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0295","text":"भावना के बिना चिंतन असंभव है। यदि हमारे पास केवल भावना की पूंजी है तो चिंतन कभी भी फलदायक नहीं हो सकता। बहुत सारे लोग आवश्यकता से अधिक भावुक होते हैं। परन्तु वह कुछ सोचना नहीं चाहते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0296","text":"मेरी सारी की सारी भावनाएं मृतप्राय हो चुकी हैं और एक भयानक कठोरता मुझे कसती जा रही है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0297","text":"एक सैनिक के रूप में आपको हमेशा तीन आदर्शों को संजोना और उन पर जीना होगा – निष्ठा, कर्तव्य और बलिदान। जो सिपाही हमेशा अपने देश के प्रति वफादार रहता है, जो हमेशा अपना जीवन बलिदान करने को तैयार रहता है, वो अजेय है। अगर तुम भी अजेय बनना चाहते हो तो इन तीन आदर्शों को अपने ह्रदय में समाहित कर लो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0298","text":"हमारी राह भले ही भयानक और पथरीली हो, हमारी यात्रा चाहे कितनी भी कष्टदायक हो, फिर भी हमें आगे बढ़ना ही है। सफलता का दिन दूर हो सकता है, पर उसका आना अनिवार्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0299","text":"परीक्षा का समय निकट देख कर हम बहुत घबराते हैं। लेकिन एक बार भी यह नहीं सोचते कि जीवन का प्रत्येक पल परीक्षा का है। यह परीक्षा ईश्वर और धर्म के प्रति है। स्कूल की परीक्षा तो दो दिन की है, परन्तु जीवन की परीक्षा तो अनंत काल के लिए देनी होगी। उसका फल हमें जन्म-जन्मान्तर तक भोगना पड़ेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0300","text":"अपनी ताकत पर भरोसा करो, उधार की ताकत हमेशा घातक होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0301","text":"आजादी मिलती नहीं, बल्कि इसे छीनना पड़ता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0302","text":"जीवन के हर पल में आशा की कोई ना कोई किरण जरुर आती है जो हमें आगे बढ़ने के लिए प्रेरित करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0303","text":"अच्छे विचारों से कमजोरियां दूर होती हैं, हमें हमेशा अपनी आत्मा को उच्च विचारों से प्रेरित करते रहना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0304","text":"जो भी तुम कुछ करते हो यह तुम्हारा कर्म है। इसमें किसी भी प्रकार का कोई बंटवारा नही होता है। इसका फल भी तुम्हे ही भोगना होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0305","text":"सफल होने के लिए आपको अकेले चलना होगा। लोग तो तब आपके साथ आते हैं जब आप सफल हो जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0306","text":"एक व्यक्ति एक विचार के लिए मर सकता है, लेकिन वह विचार उसकी मृत्यु के बाद, एक हजार व्यक्तियों के जीवन में खुद को अवतार ले लेता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0307","text":"आज़ादी मांगने से नहीं, छीनने से मिलेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0308","text":"इतिहास के इस अभूतपूर्व मोड़ पर मैं आपसे यह कहना चाहता हूं कि अपनी अस्थायी हार से निराश न हों, हंसमुख और आशावादी बनें। इन सबसे बढ़कर, भारत के भाग्य में अपना विश्वास कभी ना खोयें। पृथ्वी पर ऐसी कोई शक्ति नहीं है जो भारत को बंधन में रख सके। भारत आजाद होगा और वह भी जल्द ही। जय हिंद।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0309","text":"राजनीतिक सौदेबाजी की कूटनीति यह है कि आप जो भी हैं, उससे ज्यादा शक्तिशाली दिखें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0310","text":"केवल पूर्ण राष्ट्रवाद, पूर्ण न्याय और निष्पक्षता के आधार पर ही भारतीय सेना का निर्माण किया जा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0311","text":"केवल रक्त ही आज़ादी की कीमत चुका सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0312","text":"शाश्वत नियम याद रखें -: यदि आप कुछ पाना चाहते हैं, तो आपको कुछ देना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0313","text":"गुलाम लोगों के लिए आज़ादी की सेना में पहला सैनिक होने से बड़ा कोई गौरव, कोई सम्मान नहीं हो सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0314","text":"एक ऐसी सेना, जिसके पास साहस, निर्भयता और अजेयता की कोई परंपरा नहीं है, वह एक शक्तिशाली दुश्मन के साथ संघर्ष में अपनी खुद की पकड़ नहीं बना सकती। इसलिए स्वतंत्रता के इस युद्ध के दौरान आपको अनुभव प्राप्त करना होगा और सफलता प्राप्त करनी होगी। यह अनुभव और सफलता ही हमारी सेना के लिए एक राष्ट्रीय परंपरा का निर्माण कर सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0315","text":"उन कार्यों के लिए अपनी कमर कस लें, जो सामने हैं। मैंने आपसे पुरुष, धन और सामग्री के लिए कहा था। मैंने उन्हें बहुतायत में पा लिया है। अब मैं आपसे और मांग करता हूँ। पुरुष, धन और सामग्री स्वयं जीत या स्वतंत्रता नहीं ला सकती है। हमारे पास उद्देश्य को पूर्ण करने की शक्ति होनी चाहिए, जो हमें बहादुरी के कार्यों और वीरतापूर्ण कारनामों के लिए प्रेरित करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0316","text":"भारत पुकार रहा है, रक्त रक्त को पुकार रहा है। उठो, हमारे पास व्यर्थ के लिए समय नहीं है। अपने हथियार उठा लो, हम अपने दुश्मनों के माध्यम से ही अपना मार्ग बना लेंगे या अगर भगवान की इच्छा रही, तो हम एक शहीद की मौत मरेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0317","text":"दिल्ली की सड़क स्वतंत्रता की सड़क है। दिल्ली चलो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0318","text":"मुझे आपको याद दिलाना है कि आपको दो गुना कार्य करने हैं। हथियारों के बल और अपने खून की कीमत पर आपको स्वतंत्रता हासिल करनी होगी। फिर, जब भारत स्वतंत्र होगा, तो आपको स्वतंत्र भारत की स्थायी सेना को संगठित करना होगा। जिसका कार्य हर समय अपनी स्वतंत्रता को बनाए रखना होगा। हमें अपनी राष्ट्रीय रक्षा ऐसी अटल नींव पर बनानी होगी, ताकि हम इतिहास में फिर कभी अपनी स्वतंत्रता न खोयें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0319","text":"तुम मुझे खून दो ,मैं तुम्हें आजादी दूंगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0320","text":"ये हमारा कर्तव्य है कि हम अपनी स्वतंत्रता का मोल अपने खून से चुकाएं. हमें अपने बलिदान और परिश्रम से जो आज़ादी मिलेगी, हमारे अन्दर उसकी रक्षा करने की ताकत होनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0321","text":"आज हमारे अन्दर बस एक ही इच्छा होनी चाहिए, मरने की इच्छा ताकि भारत जी सके। एक शहीद की मौत मरने की इच्छा ताकि स्वतंत्रता का मार्ग शहीदों के खून से प्रशश्त हो सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0322","text":"मुझे यह नहीं मालूम की स्वतंत्रता के इस युद्ध में हममे से कौन कौन जीवित बचेंगे। परन्तु में यह जानता हूँ ,अंत में विजय हमारी ही होगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0323","text":"राष्ट्रवाद मानव जाति के उच्चतम आदर्श सत्य, शिव और सुन्दर से प्रेरित है ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0324","text":"भारत में राष्ट्रवाद ने एक ऐसी सृजनात्मक शक्ति का संचार किया है जो सदियों से लोगों के अन्दर से सुसुप्त पड़ी थी ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0325","text":"मेरे मन में कोई संदेह नहीं है कि हमारे देश की प्रमुख समस्यायों जैसे गरीबी ,अशिक्षा , बीमारी , कुशल उत्पादन एवं वितरण का समाधान सिर्फ समाजवादी तरीके से ही की जा सकती है ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0326","text":"यदि आपको अस्थायी रूप से झुकना पड़े तब वीरों की भांति झुकना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0327","text":"समझोतापरस्ती बड़ी अपवित्र वस्तु है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0328","text":"मध्या भावे गुडं दद्यात -- अर्थात जहाँ शहद का अभाव हो वहां गुड से ही शहद का कार्य निकालना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0329","text":"संघर्ष ने मुझे मनुष्य बनाया। मुझमे आत्मविश्वास उत्पन्न हुआ ,जो पहले नहीं था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0330","text":"कष्टों का निसंदेह एक आंतरिक नैतिक मूल्य होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0331","text":"मुझमे जन्मजात प्रतिभा तो नहीं थी ,परन्तु कठोर परिश्रम से बचने की प्रवृति मुझमे कभी नहीं रही।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0332","text":"जीवन में प्रगति का आशय यह है की शंका संदेह उठते रहें और उनके समाधान के प्रयास का क्रम चलता रहे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0333","text":"हमारी राह भले ही भयानक और पथरीली हो ,हमारी यात्रा चाहे कितनी भी कष्टदायक हो , फिर भी हमें आगे बढ़ना ही है। सफलता का दिन दूर हो सकता है ,पर उसका आना अनिवार्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0334","text":"अगर संघर्ष न रहे ,किसी भी भय का सामना न करना पड़े ,तब जीवन का आधा स्वाद ही समाप्त हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0335","text":"मैं संकट एवं विपदाओं से भयभीत नहीं होता। संकटपूर्ण दिन आने पर भी मैं भागूँगा नहीं वरन आगे बढकर कष्टों को सहन करूँगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0336","text":"इतना तो आप भी मानेंगे ,एक न एक दिन तो मैं जेल से अवश्य मुक्त हो जाऊँगा ,क्योंकि प्रत्येक दुःख का अंत होना अवश्यम्भावी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0337","text":"असफलताएं कभी कभी सफलता की स्तम्भ होती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0338","text":"सुबह से पहले अँधेरी घडी अवश्य आती है। बहादुर बनो और संघर्ष जारी रखो ,क्योंकि स्वतंत्रता निकट है।।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0339","text":"समय से पूर्व की परिपक्वता अच्छी नहीं होती ,चाहे वह किसी वृक्ष की हो ,या व्यक्ति की और उसकी हानि आगे चल कर भुगतनी ही होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0340","text":"अपने कॉलेज जीवन की देहलीज पर खड़े होकर मुझे अनुभव हुआ ,जीवन का कोई अर्थ और उद्देश्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0341","text":"निसंदेह बचपन और युवावस्था में पवित्रता और संयम अति आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0342","text":"में जीवन की अनिश्चितता से जरा भी नहीं घबराता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0343","text":"मैंने अमूल्य जीवन का इतना समय व्यर्थ ही नष्ट कर दिया। यह सोच कर बहुत ही दुःख होता है। कभी कभी यह पीड़ा असह्य हो उठती है। मनुष्य जीवन पाकर भी जीवन का अर्थ समझ में नहीं आया। यदि मैं अपनी मंजिल पर नहीं पहुँच पाया ,तो यह जीवन व्यर्थ है। इसकी क्या सार्थकता है ?।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0344","text":"परीक्षा का समय निकट देख कर हम बहुत घबराते हैं। लेकिन एक बार भी यह नहीं सोचते की जीवन का प्रत्येक पल परीक्षा का है। यह परीक्षा ईश्वर और धर्म के प्रति है। स्कूल की परीक्षा तो दो दिन की है ,परन्तु जीवन की परीक्षा तो अनंत काल के लिए देनी होगी। उसका फल हमें जन्म-जन्मान्तर तक भोगना पड़ेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0345","text":"मुझे जीवन में एक निश्चित लक्ष्य को पूरा करना है। मेरा जन्म उसी के लिए हुआ है। मुझे नेतिक विचारों की धारा में नहीं बहना है।।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0346","text":"मेरे जीवन के अनुभवों में एक यह भी है। मुझे आशा है की कोई-न-कोई किरण उबार लेती है और जीवन से दूर भटकने नहीं देती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0347","text":"मैं चाहता हूँ चरित्र ,ज्ञान और कार्य....।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0348","text":"हमें केवल कार्य करने का अधिकार है। कर्म ही हमारा कर्तव्य है। कर्म के फल का स्वामी वह (भगवान ) है ,हम नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0349","text":"एक सैनिक की सबसे बड़ी पहचान है उसका साहस और निष्ठा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0350","text":"माँ का प्यार सबसे गहरा होता है। स्वार्थ रहित होता है। इसको किसी भी प्रकार नापा नहीं जा सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0351","text":"जिस व्यक्ति में सनक नहीं होती ,वह कभी भी महान नहीं बन सकता। परन्तु सभी पागल व्यक्ति महान नहीं बन जाते। क्योंकि सभी पागल व्यक्ति प्रतिभाशाली नहीं होते। आखिर क्यों ? कारण यह है की केवल पागलपन ही काफी नहीं है। इसके अतिरिक्त कुछ और भी आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0352","text":"हमें अधीर नहीं होना चहिये। न ही यह आशा करनी चाहिए की जिस प्रश्न का उत्तर खोजने में न जाने कितने ही लोगों ने अपना सम्पूर्ण जीवन समर्पित कर दिया ,उसका उत्तर हमें एक-दो दिन में प्राप्त हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0353","text":"एक सैनिक के रूप में आपको हमेशा तीन आदर्शों को संजोना और उन पर जीना होगा निष्ठा कर्तव्य और बलिदान। जो सिपाही हमेशा अपने देश के प्रति वफादार रहता है, जो हमेशा अपना जीवन बलिदान करने को तैयार रहता है, वो अजेय है. अगर तुम भी अजेय बनना चाहते हो तो इन तीन आदर्शों को अपने ह्रदय में समाहित कर लो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0354","text":"याद रखें अन्याय सहना और गलत के साथ समझौता करना सबसे बड़ा अपराध है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0355","text":"स्वामी विवेकानंद का यह कथन बिलकुल सत्य है ,यदि तुम्हारे पास लोह शिराएं हैं और कुशाग्र बुद्धि है ,तो तुम सारे विश्व को अपने चरणों में झुक सकते हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0356","text":"स्वतंत्रता बलिदान माँगती है, और यह बलिदान हमें देना ही होगा (स्रोत: रेडियो सिंगापुर भाषण, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1942)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0357","text":"केवल बातें करने से स्वतंत्रता नहीं मिलती, उसके लिए शक्ति अर्जित करनी पड़ती है (स्रोत: आज़ाद हिंद फौज का भाषण, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1943)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0358","text":"सैनिकों को युद्ध के मैदान में अपना कर्तव्य निभाना होता है, चाहे परिणाम कुछ भी हो (स्रोत: आज़ाद हिंद रेडियो, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1943)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0359","text":"गुलामी की ज़िंदगी से स्वतंत्रता की मौत बेहतर है (स्रोत: कलकत्ता विश्वविद्यालय सभा, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0360","text":"सच्चा नेता वही है जो अपने अनुयायियों से पहले कष्ट झेले (स्रोत: आज़ाद हिंद फौज कैम्प, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1943)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0361","text":"इतिहास वे नहीं बनाते जो डरते हैं, इतिहास वे बनाते हैं जो सब कुछ दांव पर लगाते हैं (स्रोत: टोक्यो रेडियो इंटरव्यू, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1944)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0362","text":"अगर हम एकजुट हैं तो हमें कोई भी शक्ति गुलाम नहीं बना सकती (स्रोत: आज़ाद हिंद रेडियो, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1943)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0363","text":"मेरे लिए सबसे बड़ा धर्म है देशसेवा (स्रोत: व्यक्तिगत विचार, जेल डायरी, सुभाष चंद्र बोस, 1931)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0364","text":"रक्तेन भाव्यं स्वातन्त्र्ययज्ञम् न भिक्षया वा सत्याग्रहेण ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — सुभाष चन्द्र बोस के बारे में मंतव्य","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0365","text":"\"सुभाष चन्द्र बोस राष्ट्रभक्तों के राजा हैं….\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — सुभाष चन्द्र बोस के बारे में मंतव्य","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0366","text":"\"नेताजी सुभाष भारत को एक स्वाधीन व गौरवशाली देश बनने के लिए प्रेरणा दी थी । भारत की धरती पर स्वाधीन सरकार बनाने वाले वे पहले व्यक्ति थे ।\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — सुभाष चन्द्र बोस के बारे में मंतव्य","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0367","text":"\"नेताजी कटक के धरती पुत्र हैं । कटक भूमि उनके प्राण में सेवा, संघर्ष और त्याग का मंत्र जागृत की।\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — सुभाष चन्द्र बोस के बारे में मंतव्य","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0368","text":"आज पराक्रम दिवस पर मैं नेताजी सुभाष चंद्र बोस को श्रद्धांजलि अर्पित करता हूं और देश के इतिहास में उनके अतुल्नीय योगदान को याद कर रहा हूं। वह  अंग्रेजी शासन का उग्र प्रतिरोध करने के लिए जाने जाएंगे। उनके विचारों से मैं बेहद प्रभावित हूं, हम भारत के लिए उनके विजन को हकीकत बनाने के लिए काम कर रहे हैं। -- नरेद्र मोदी, २३ जनवरी २०२३","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — सुभाष चन्द्र बोस के बारे में मंतव्य","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0369","text":"अपनी अद्वितीय नेतृत्व क्षमता से नेताजी ने लोगों को संगठित किया और ‘आजाद हिंद फौज’ बनाकर आजादी के लिए सशस्त्र आंदोलन किया। उनके साहस और संघर्ष को पूरा देश नमन करता है।--  -- अमित शाह, २३ जनवरी २०२३","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Subhas Chandra Bose — सुभाष चन्द्र बोस के बारे में मंतव्य","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0370","text":"उठो, जागो और तब तक नहीं रुको जब तक लक्ष्य ना प्राप्त हो जाये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0371","text":"जो सत्य है, उसे साहसपूर्वक निर्भीक होकर लोगों से कहो–उससे किसी को कष्ट होता है या नहीं, इस ओर ध्यान मत दो। दुर्बलता को कभी प्रश्रय मत दो। सत्य की ज्योति ‘बुद्धिमान’ मनुष्यों के लिए यदि अत्यधिक मात्रा में प्रखर प्रतीत होती है, और उन्हें बहा ले जाती है, तो ले जाने दो–वे जितना शीघ्र बह जाएँ उतना अच्छा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0372","text":"तुम अपनी अंतःस्थ आत्मा को छोड़ किसी और के सामने सिर मत झुकाओ। जब तक तुम यह अनुभव नहीं करते कि तुम स्वयं देवों के देव हो, तब तक तुम मुक्त नहीं हो सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0373","text":"ईश्वर ही ईश्वर की उपलब्धि कर सकता है। सभी जीवंत ईश्वर हैं–इस भाव से सब को देखो। मनुष्य का अध्ययन करो, मनुष्य ही जीवन्त काव्य है। जगत में जितने ईसा या बुद्ध हुए हैं, सभी हमारी ज्योति से ज्योतिष्मान हैं। इस ज्योति को छोड़ देने पर ये सब हमारे लिए और अधिक जीवित नहीं रह सकेंगे, मर जाएंगे। तुम अपनी आत्मा के ऊपर स्थिर रहो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0374","text":"ज्ञान स्वयमेव वर्तमान है, मनुष्य केवल उसका आविष्कार करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0375","text":"मानव-देह ही सर्वश्रेष्ठ देह है, एवं मनुष्य ही सर्वोच्च प्राणी है, क्योंकि इस मानव-देह तथा इस जन्म में ही हम इस सापेक्षिक जगत् से संपूर्णतया बाहर हो सकते हैं–निश्चय ही मुक्ति की अवस्था प्राप्त कर सकते हैं, और यह मुक्ति ही हमारा चरम लक्ष्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0376","text":"अंग्रेजी अनुवाद (English Translation): The human body is the highest body in the universe, and man is the highest being... It is the only body through which he can become perfect, can attain to freedom, and this is the one and only goal.","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0377","text":"जो मनुष्य इसी जन्म में मुक्ति प्राप्त करना चाहता है, उसे एक ही जन्म में हजारों वर्ष का काम करना पड़ेगा। वह जिस युग में जन्मा है, उससे उसे बहुत आगे जाना पड़ेगा, किन्तु साधारण लोग किसी तरह रेंगते-रेंगते ही आगे बढ़ सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0378","text":"जो महापुरुष प्रचार-कार्य के लिए अपना जीवन समर्पित कर देते हैं, वे उन महापुरुषों की तुलना में अपेक्षाकृत अपूर्ण हैं, जो मौन रहकर पवित्र जीवनयापन करते हैं और श्रेष्ठ विचारों का चिन्तन करते हुए जगत् की सहायता करते हैं। इन सभी महापुरुषों में एक के बाद दूसरे का आविर्भाव होता है–अंत में उनकी शक्ति का चरम फलस्वरूप ऐसा कोई शक्तिसम्पन्न पुरुष आविर्भूत होता है, जो जगत् को शिक्षा प्रदान करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0379","text":"अंग्रेजी अनुवाद (English Translation): The great men who are living with the sole object of preaching divine knowledge are in a sense lower than those who live in silence, perfecting themselves for the good of the world. A man may be a great preacher, but he is not the last of the great men. One of these appears from time to time; and in the ripeness of time a power comes down, which is so great that it teaches the whole world.","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0380","text":"आध्यात्मिक दृष्टि से विकसित हो चुकने पर धर्मसंघ में बना रहना अवांछनीय है। उससे बाहर निकलकर स्वाधीनता की मुक्त वायु में जीवन व्यतीत करो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0381","text":"मुक्ति-लाभ के अतिरिक्त और कौन सी उच्चावस्था का लाभ किया जा सकता है? देवदूत कभी कोई बुरे कार्य नहीं करते, इसलिए उन्हें कभी दंड भी प्राप्त नहीं होता, अतएव वे मुक्त भी नहीं हो सकते। सांसारिक धक्का ही हमें जगा देता है, वही इस जगत्स्वप्न को भंग करने में सहायता पहुँचाता है। इस प्रकार के लगातार आघात ही इस संसार से छुटकारा पाने की अर्थात् मुक्ति-लाभ करने की हमारी आकांक्षा को जाग्रत करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0382","text":"हमारी नैतिक प्रकृति जितनी उन्नत होती है, उतना ही उच्च हमारा प्रत्यक्ष अनुभव होता है, और उतनी ही हमारी इच्छा शक्ति अधिक बलवती होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0383","text":"मन का विकास करो और उसका संयम करो, उसके बाद जहाँ इच्छा हो, वहाँ इसका प्रयोग करो–उससे अति शीघ्र फल प्राप्ति होगी। यह है यथार्थ आत्मोन्नति का उपाय। एकाग्रता सीखो, और जिस ओर इच्छा हो, उसका प्रयोग करो। ऐसा करने पर तुम्हें कुछ खोना नहीं पड़ेगा। जो समस्त को प्राप्त करता है, वह अंश को भी प्राप्त कर सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0384","text":"पहले स्वयं संपूर्ण मुक्तावस्था प्राप्त कर लो, उसके बाद इच्छा करने पर फिर अपने को सीमाबद्ध कर सकते हो। प्रत्येक कार्य में अपनी समस्त शक्ति का प्रयोग करो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0385","text":"सभी मरेंगे- साधु या असाधु, धनी या दरिद्र- सभी मरेंगे। चिर काल तक किसी का शरीर नहीं रहेगा। अतएव उठो, जागो और संपूर्ण रूप से निष्कपट हो जाओ। भारत में घोर कपट समा गया है। चाहिए चरित्र, चाहिए इस तरह की दृढ़ता और चरित्र का बल, जिससे मनुष्य आजीवन दृढ़व्रत बन सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0386","text":"संन्यास का अर्थ है, मृत्यु के प्रति प्रेम। सांसारिक लोग जीवन से प्रेम करते हैं, परन्तु संन्यासी के लिए प्रेम करने को मृत्यु है। लेकिन इसका मतलब यह नहीं है कि हम आत्महत्या कर लें। आत्महत्या करने वालों को तो कभी मृत्यु प्यारी नहीं होती है। संन्यासी का धर्म है समस्त संसार के हित के लिए निरंतर आत्मत्याग करते हुए धीरे-धीरे मृत्यु को प्राप्त हो जाना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0387","text":"हे सखे, तुम क्यों रो रहे हो? सब शक्ति तो तुम्हीं में है। हे भगवन्, अपने ऐश्वर्यमय स्वरूप को विकसित करो। ये तीनों लोक तुम्हारे पैरों के नीचे हैं। जड़ की कोई शक्ति नहीं, प्रबल शक्ति आत्मा की है। हे विद्वन! डरो मत; तुम्हारा नाश नहीं है, संसार-सागर से पार उतरने का उपाय है। जिस पथ के अवलम्बन से यती लोग संसार-सागर के पार उतरे हैं, वही श्रेष्ठ पथ मैं तुम्हें दिखाता हूँ!","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0388","text":"बड़े-बड़े दिग्गज बह जाएँगे। छोटे-मोटे की तो बात ही क्या है! तुम लोग कमर कसकर कार्य में जुट जाओ। हुंकार मात्र से हम दुनिया को पलट देंगे। अभी तो केवल मात्र प्रारम्भ ही है। किसी के साथ विवाद न कर हिल-मिलकर अग्रसर हो - यह दुनिया भयानक है, किसी पर विश्वास नहीं है। डरने का कोई कारण नहीं है, माँ मेरे साथ हैं - इस बार ऐसे कार्य होंगे कि तुम चकित हो जाओगे। भय किस बात का? किसका भय? वज्र जैसा हृदय बनाकर कार्य में जुट जाओ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0389","text":"तुमने बहुत बहादुरी की है। शाबाश! हिचकने वाले पीछे रह जाएँगे और तुम कूदकर सबके आगे पहुँच जाओगे। जो अपना उद्धार में लगे हुए हैं, वे न तो अपना उद्धार ही कर सकेंगे और न दूसरों का। ऐसा शोर-गुल मचाओ कि उसकी आवाज़ दुनिया के कोने-कोने में फैल जाए। कुछ लोग ऐसे हैं, जो कि दूसरों की त्रुटियों को देखने के लिए तैयार बैठे हैं, किन्तु कार्य करने के समय उनका पता नहीं चलता है। जुट जाओ, अपनी शक्ति के अनुसार आगे बढ़ो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0390","text":"तमाम संसार हिल उठता। क्या करूँ धीरे-धीरे अग्रसर होना पड रहा है। तूफ़ान मचा दो तूफ़ान!","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0391","text":"किसी बात से तुम उत्साहहीन न होओ; जब तक ईश्वर की कृपा हमारे ऊपर है, कौन इस पृथ्वी पर हमारी उपेक्षा कर सकता है? यदि तुम अपनी अन्तिम साँस भी ले रहे हो तो भी न डरना। सिंह की शूरता और पुष्प की कोमलता के साथ काम करते रहो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0392","text":"लोग तुम्हारी स्तुति करें या निन्दा, लक्ष्मी तुम्हारे ऊपर कृपालु हो या न हो, तुम्हारा देहान्त आज हो या एक युग में, तुम न्यायपथ से कभी भ्रष्ट न हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0393","text":"आत्मा अजर और अमर है, उसे न कोई जला सकता है, न काट सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0394","text":"श्रेयांसि बहुविघ्नानि (अच्छे कर्मों में कितने ही विघ्न आते हैं)। प्रलय मचाना ही होगा, इससे कम में किसी तरह नहीं चल सकता। कुछ परवाह नहीं। दुनिया भर में प्रलय मच जाएगा, वाह! गुरु की फतह! अरे भाई, श्रेयांसि बहुविघ्नानि, उन्हीं विघ्नों की रेल-पेल में आदमी तैयार होता है... सभी कामों में एक दल शत्रुता ठानता है; अपना काम करते जाओ। किसी की बात का जवाब देने से क्या काम? सत्यमेव जयते नानृतं, सत्येनैव पन्था विततो देवयानः (सत्य की ही विजय होती है, मिथ्या की नहीं; सत्य के ही बल से देवयानमार्ग की गति मिलती है)... धीरे-धीरे सब होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0395","text":"वीरता से आगे बढ़ो। एक दिन या एक साल में सिद्धि की आशा न रखो। उच्चतम आदर्श पर दृढ़ रहो। स्थिर रहो। स्वार्थपरता और ईर्ष्या से बचो। आज्ञा-पालन करो। सत्य, मनुष्य-जाति और अपने देश के पक्ष पर सदा के लिए अटल रहो, और तुम संसार को हिला दोगे। याद रखो - व्यक्ति और उसका जीवन ही शक्ति का स्रोत है, इसके सिवाय अन्य कुछ भी नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0396","text":"इस तरह का दिन क्या कभी होगा कि परोपकार के लिए जान जाएगी? दुनिया बच्चों का खिलवाड़ नहीं है -- बड़े आदमी वे हैं जो अपने हृदय-रुधिर से दूसरों का रास्ता तैयार करते हैं। यही सदा से होता आया है -- एक आदमी अपना शरीर-पात करके सेतु निर्माण करता है, और हजारों आदमी उसके ऊपर से नदी पार करते हैं। एवमस्तु एवमस्तु, शिवोऽहम् शिवोऽहम् (ऐसा ही हो, ऐसा ही हो- मैं ही शिव हूँ, मैं ही शिव हूँ)।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0397","text":"मैं चाहता हूँ कि मेरे सब बच्चे, मैं जितना उन्नत बन सकता था, उससे सौगुना उन्नत बनें। तुम लोगों में से प्रत्येक को महान शक्तिशाली बनना होगा- मैं कहता हूँ, अवश्य बनना होगा। आज्ञा-पालन, ध्येय के प्रति अनुराग तथा ध्येय को कार्यरूप में परिणत करने के लिए सदा प्रस्तुत रहना -- इन तीनों के रहने पर कोई भी तुम्हें अपने मार्ग से विचलित नहीं कर सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0398","text":"मन और मुँह को एक करके भावों को जीवन में कार्यान्वित करना होगा। इसी को श्री रामकृष्ण कहा करते थे, \"भाव के घर में किसी प्रकार की चोरी न होने पाये।\" सब विषयों में व्यावहारिक बनना होगा। लोगों या समाज की बातों पर ध्यान न देकर वे एकाग्र मन से अपना कार्य करते रहेंगे। क्या तुमने नहीं सुना, कबीरदास के दोहे में है- \"हाथी चले बाजार में, कुत्ता भोंके हजार, साधुन को दुर्भाव नहिं, जो निंदै संसार।\" ऐसे ही चलना है। दुनिया के लोगों की बातों पर ध्यान नहीं देना होगा। उनकी भली-बुरी बातों को सुनने से जीवन भर कोई किसी प्रकार का महत् कार्य नहीं कर सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0399","text":"अन्त में प्रेम की ही विजय होती है। हैरान होने से काम नहीं चलेगा- ठहरो- धैर्य धारण करने पर सफलता अवश्यम्भावी है... कोई बाहरी अनुष्ठान-पद्धति आवश्यक न हो- बहुत्व में एकत्व, सार्वजनीन भाव में किसी तरह की बाधा न हो... मैं मरूँ चाहे बचूँ, देश जाऊँ या न जाऊँ, तुम लोग अच्छी तरह याद रखना कि, सार्वजनीनता- हम लोग केवल इसी भाव का प्रचार नहीं करते कि, \"दूसरों के धर्म का द्वेष न करना\"; नहीं, हम सब लोग सब धर्मों को सत्य समझते हैं और उनका ग्रहण भी पूर्ण रूप से करते हैं... सावधान रहना, दूसरे के अत्यन्त छोटे अधिकार में भी हस्तक्षेप न करना - इसी भँवर में बड़े-बड़े जहाज डूब जाते हैं। पूरी भक्ति, परन्तु कट्टरता छोड़कर, दिखानी होगी, याद रखना उनकी कृपा से सब ठीक हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0400","text":"जिस तरह हो, इसके लिए हमें चाहे जितना कष्ट उठाना पड़े- चाहे कितना ही त्याग करना पड़े, यह भाव (भयानक ईर्ष्या) हमारे भीतर न घुसने पाए- हम दस ही क्यों न हों- दो क्यों न रहें- परवाह नहीं, परन्तु जितने हों सम्पूर्ण शुद्धचरित्र हों।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0401","text":"नीतिपरायण तथा साहसी बनो, अंतःकरण पूर्णतया शुद्ध रहना चाहिए। पूर्ण नीतिपरायण तथा साहसी बनो -- प्राणों के लिए भी कभी न डरो। कायर लोग ही पापाचरण करते हैं, वीर पुरुष कभी भी पापानुष्ठान नहीं करते -- यहाँ तक कि कभी वे मन में भी पाप का विचार नहीं लाते। प्राणिमात्र से प्रेम करने का प्रयास करो। बच्चों, तुम्हारे लिए नीतिपरायणता तथा साहस को छोड़कर और कोई दूसरा धर्म नहीं। इसके सिवाय और कोई धार्मिक मत-मतान्तर तुम्हारे लिए नहीं है। कायरता, पाप, असदाचरण तथा दुर्बलता तुममें एकदम नहीं रहनी चाहिए, बाकी आवश्यकीय वस्तुएँ अपने आप आकर उपस्थित होंगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0402","text":"शक्तिमान, उठो तथा सामर्थ्यशाली बनो। कर्म, निरन्तर कर्म; संघर्ष, निरन्तर संघर्ष! अलमिति। पवित्र और निःस्वार्थी बनने की कोशिश करो -- सारा धर्म इसी में है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0403","text":"क्या संस्कृत पढ़ रहे हो? कितनी प्रगति हुई है? आशा है कि प्रथम भाग तो अवश्य ही समाप्त कर चुके होंगे। विशेष परिश्रम के साथ संस्कृत सीखो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0404","text":"शत्रु को पराजित करने के लिए ढाल तथा तलवार की आवश्यकता होती है। इसलिए अंग्रेज़ी और संस्कृत का अध्ययन मन लगाकर करो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0405","text":"बच्चों, धर्म का रहस्य आचरण से जाना जा सकता है, व्यर्थ के मतवाद entry that should replace the old version.","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0406","text":"बच्चों, धर्म का रहस्य आचरण से जाना जा सकता है, व्यर्थ के मतवादों से नहीं। सच्चा बनना तथा सच्चा बर्ताव करना, इसमें ही समग्र धर्म निहित है। जो केवल प्रभु-प्रभु की रट लगाता है, वह नहीं, किन्तु जो उस परम पिता के इच्छानुसार कार्य करता है वही धार्मिक है। यदि कभी-कभी तुमको संसार का थोड़ा-बहुत धक्का भी खाना पड़े, तो उससे विचलित न होना, मुहूर्त भर में वह दूर हो जाएगा तथा सारी स्थिति पुनः ठीक हो जाएगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0407","text":"बालकों, दृढ़ बने रहो, मेरी सन्तानों में से कोई भी कायर न बने। तुम लोगों में जो सबसे अधिक साहसी है - सदा उसी का साथ करो। बिना विघ्न-बाधाओं के क्या कभी कोई महान कार्य हो सकता है? समय, धैर्य तथा अदम्य इच्छा-शक्ति से ही कार्य हुआ करता है। मैं तो लोहे के सदृश दृढ़ इच्छा-शक्ति सम्पन्न हृदय चाहता हूँ, जो कभी कम्पित न हो। दृढ़ता के साथ लगे रहो, प्रभु तुम्हें आशीर्वाद दे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0408","text":"\"जब तक जीना, तब तक सीखना\"— अनुभव ही जगत में सर्वश्रेष्ठ शिक्षक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0409","text":"जिस प्रकार स्वर्ग में, उसी प्रकार इस नश्वर जगत में भी तुम्हारी इच्छा पूर्ण हो, क्योंकि अनन्त काल के लिए जगत में तुम्हारी ही महिमा घोषित हो रही है एवं सब कुछ तुम्हारा ही राज्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0410","text":"पवित्रता, दृढ़ता तथा उद्यम- ये तीनों गुण मैं एक साथ चाहता हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0411","text":"भाग्य बहादुर और कर्मठ व्यक्ति का ही साथ देता है। पीछे मुड़कर मत देखो। आगे, अपार शक्ति, अपरिमित उत्साह, अमित साहस और निस्सीम धैर्य की आवश्यकता है- और तभी महान कार्य निष्पन्न किये जा सकते हैं। हमें पूरे विश्व को उद्दीप्त करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0412","text":"पवित्रता, धैर्य तथा प्रयत्न के द्वारा सारी बाधाएँ दूर हो जाती हैं। इसमें कोई सन्देह नहीं कि महान कार्य सभी धीरे धीरे होते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0413","text":"साहसी होकर काम करो। धीरज और स्थिरता से काम करना -- यही एक मार्ग है। आगे बढ़ो और याद रखो धीरज, साहस, पवित्रता और अनवरत कर्म। जब तक तुम पवित्र होकर अपने उद्देश्य पर डटे रहोगे, तब तक तुम कभी निष्फल नहीं होओगे -- माँ तुम्हें कभी न छोड़ेगी और पूर्ण आशीर्वाद के तुम पात्र हो जाओगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0414","text":"बच्चों, जब तक तुम लोगों को भगवान तथा गुरू में, भक्ति तथा सत्य में विश्वास रहेगा, तब तक कोई भी तुम्हें नुक़सान नहीं पहुँचा सकता। किन्तु इनमें से एक के भी नष्ट हो जाने पर परिणाम विपत्तिजनक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0415","text":"महाशक्ति का तुम में संचार होगा -- कदापि भयभीत मत होना। पवित्र होओ, विश्वासी होओ, और आज्ञापालक होओ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0416","text":"बिना पाखण्डी और कायर बने सबको प्रसन्न रखो। पवित्रता और शक्ति के साथ अपने आदर्श पर दृढ़ रहो और फिर तुम्हारे सामने कैसी भी बाधाएँ क्यों न हों, कुछ समय बाद संसार तुमको मानेगा ही।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0417","text":"धीरज रखो और मृत्युपर्यन्त विश्वासपात्र रहो। आपस में न लड़ो! रुपये-पैसे के व्यवहार में शुद्ध भाव रखो। हम अभी महान कार्य करेंगे। जब तक तुम में ईमानदारी, भक्ति और विश्वास है, तब तक प्रत्येक कार्य में तुम्हें सफलता मिलेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0418","text":"जो पवित्र तथा साहसी है, वही जगत् में सब कुछ कर सकता है। माया-मोह से प्रभु सदा तुम्हारी रक्षा करें। मैं तुम्हारे साथ काम करने के लिए सदैव प्रस्तुत हूँ एवं हम लोग यदि स्वयं अपने मित्र रहें तो प्रभु भी हमारे लिए सैकड़ों मित्र भेजेंगे, आत्मैव ह्यात्मनो बन्धुः (आत्मा ही आत्मा का मित्र है)।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0419","text":"ईर्ष्या तथा अहंकार को दूर कर दो -- संगठित होकर दूसरों के लिए कार्य करना सीखो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0420","text":"पूर्णतः निःस्वार्थ रहो, स्थिर रहो, और काम करो। एक बात और है। सबके सेवक बनो और दूसरों पर शासन करने का तनिक भी यत्न न करो, क्योंकि इससे ईर्ष्या उत्पन्न होगी और इससे हर चीज बर्बाद हो जाएगी। आगे बढ़ो... हम अपने भीतर से ही सहायता लेंगे, अन्य सहायता के लिए हम प्रतीक्षा नहीं करते। मेरे बच्चे, आत्मविश्वास रखो, सच्चे और सहनशील बनो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0421","text":"यदि तुम स्वयं ही नेता के रूप में खड़े हो जाओगे, तो तुम्हें सहायता देने के लिए कोई भी आगे न बढ़ेगा। यदि सफल होना चाहते हो, तो पहले 'अहं' ही नाश कर डालो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0422","text":"पक्षपात ही सब अनर्थों का मूल है, यह न भूलना। अर्थात् यदि तुम किसी के प्रति अन्य की अपेक्षा अधिक प्रीति-प्रदर्शन करते हो, तो याद रखो उसी से भविष्य में कलह का बीजारोपण होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0423","text":"यदि कोई तुम्हारे समीप अन्य किसी साथी की निन्दा करना चाहे, तो तुम उस ओर बिल्कुल ध्यान न दो। इन बातों को सुनना भी महान् पाप है, उससे भविष्य में विवाद का सूत्रपात होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0424","text":"गम्भीरता के साथ शिशु सरलता को मिलाओ। सबके साथ मेल से रहो। अहंकार के सब भाव छोड़ दो और साम्प्रदायिक विचारों को मन में न लाओ। व्यर्थ विवाद महापाप है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0425","text":"बच्चे, जब तक तुम्हारे हृदय में उत्साह एवं गुरू तथा ईश्वर में विश्वास- ये तीनों वस्तुएँ रहेंगी -- तब तक तुम्हें कोई भी दबा नहीं सकता। मैं दिनोदिन अपने हृदय में शक्ति के विकास का अनुभव कर रहा हूँ। हे साहसी बालकों, कार्य करते रहो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0426","text":"किसी को उसकी योजनाओं में हतोत्साह नहीं करना चाहिए। आलोचना की प्रवृत्ति का पूर्णतः परित्याग कर दो। जब तक वे सही मार्ग पर अग्रेसर हो रहे हैं; तब तक उनके कार्य में सहायता करो; और जब कभी तुमको उनके कार्य में कोई ग़लती नज़र आये, तो नम्रतापूर्वक ग़लती के प्रति उनको सजग कर दो। एक दूसरे की आलोचना ही सब दोषों की जड़ है। किसी भी संगठन को विनष्ट करने में इसका बहुत बड़ा हाथ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0427","text":"क्या तुम नहीं अनुभव करते कि दूसरों के ऊपर निर्भर रहना बुद्धिमानी नहीं है। बुद्धिमान् व्यक्ति को अपने ही पैरों पर दृढ़तापूर्वक खड़ा होकर कार्य करना चाहिए। धीरे धीरे सब कुछ ठीक हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0428","text":"आओ हम नाम, यश और दूसरों पर शासन करने की इच्छा से रहित होकर काम करें। काम, क्रोध एवं लोभ -- इस त्रिविध बन्धन से हम मुक्त हो जाएँ और फिर सत्य हमारे साथ रहेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0429","text":"न टालो, न ढूँढों -- भगवान अपनी इच्छानुसार जो कुछ भेजें, उसके लिए प्रतीक्षा करते रहो, यही मेरा मूलमंत्र है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0430","text":"शक्ति और विश्वास के साथ लगे रहो। सत्य निष्ठा, पवित्र और निर्मल रहो, तथा आपस में न लड़ो। हमारी जाति का रोग ईर्ष्या ही है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0431","text":"एक ही आदमी मेरा अनुसरण करे, किन्तु उसे मृत्युपर्यन्त सत्य और विश्वासी होना होगा। मैं सफलता और असफलता की चिन्ता नहीं करता। मैं अपने आन्दोलन को पवित्र रखूँगा, भले ही मेरे साथ कोई न हो। कपटी कार्यों से सामना पड़ने पर मेरा धैर्य समाप्त हो जाता है। यही संसार है कि जिन्हें तुम सबसे अधिक प्यार और सहायता करो, वे ही तुम्हें धोखा देंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0432","text":"मेरा आदर्श अवश्य ही थोड़े से शब्दों में कहा जा सकता है - मनुष्य जाति को उसके दिव्य स्वरूप का उपदेश देना, तथा जीवन के प्रत्येक क्षेत्र में उसे अभिव्यक्त करने का उपाय बताना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0433","text":"जब कभी मैं किसी व्यक्ति को उस उपदेशवाणी (श्री रामकृष्ण की वाणी) के बीच पूर्ण रूप से निमग्न पाता हूँ, जो भविष्य में संसार में शान्ति की वर्षा करने वाली है, तो मेरा हृदय आनन्द से उछलने लगता है। ऐसे समय मैं पागल नहीं हो जाता हूँ, यही आश्चर्य की बात है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0434","text":"\"बसन्त की तरह लोगों का हित करते हुए\" - यही मेरा धर्म है। \"मुझे मुक्ति और भक्ति की चाह नहीं। लाखों नरकों में जाना मुझे स्वीकार है, बसन्तवल्लोकहितं चरन्तः (बसन्त की तरह संसार का कल्याण करते हुए) - यही मेरा धर्म है।\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0435","text":"हर काम को तीन अवस्थाओं में से गुज़रना होता है - उपहास, विरोध और स्वीकृति। जो मनुष्य अपने समय से आगे विचार करता है, लोग उसे निश्चय ही ग़लत समझते हैं। इसलिए विरोध और अत्याचार हम सहर्ष स्वीकार करते हैं; परन्तु मुझे दृढ़ और पवित्र होना चाहिए और भगवान् में अपरिमित विश्वास रखना चाहिए, तब ये सब लुप्त हो जाएँगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0436","text":"यदि कोई भंगी हमारे पास भंगी के रूप में आता है, तो छुतही बीमारी की तरह हम उसके स्पर्श से दूर भागते हैं। परन्तु जब उसके सिर पर एक कटोरा पानी डालकर कोई पादरी प्रार्थना के रूप में कुछ गुनगुना देता है... तब चाहे वह किसी कट्टर से कट्टर हिन्दू के कमरे के भीतर पहुँच जाय, उसके लिए कहीं रोक-टोक नहीं! ... मैं उन बेचारों को क्यों दोष दूँ?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0437","text":"प्रायः देखने में आता है कि अच्छे से अच्छे लोगों पर कष्ट और कठिनाइयाँ आ पडती हैं... परन्तु वस्तु मात्र के अन्तरकाल में प्रेम एवं कल्याण का अनन्त भण्डार है। ...एक बार उस शान्ति-मण्डल में प्रवेश करने पर फिर चाहे आँधी और तूफान के जितने तुमुल झकोरे आयें, वह मकान, जो सदियों की पुरानि चट्टान पर बना है, हिल नहीं सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0438","text":"यही दुनिया है! यदि तुम किसी का उपकार करो, तो लोग उसे कोई महत्व नहीं देंगे, किन्तु ज्यों ही तुम उस कार्य को वन्द कर दो, वे तुरन्त तुम्हें बदमाश प्रमाणित करने में नहीं हिचकिचायेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0439","text":"मेरी केवल यह इच्छा है कि प्रतिवर्ष यथेष्ठ संख्या में हमारे नवयुवकों को चीन जापान में आना चाहिए। ... और तुम लोग क्या कर रहे हो? ... तीस रुपये की मुंशीगीरी के लिए... जी-जान से तड़प रहे हो -- यही तो भारतवर्ष के नवयुवकों की सबसे बड़ी महत्वाकांक्षा है। ... क्या समुद्र में इतना पानी भी न रहा कि तुम उसमें विश्वविद्यालय के डिप्लोमा, गाउन और पुस्तकों के समेत डूब मरो? आओ, मनुष्य बनो!","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0440","text":"न संख्या-शक्ति, न धन, न पाण्डित्य, न वाक चातुर्य, कुछ भी नहीं, बल्कि पवित्रता, शुद्ध जीवन, एक शब्द में अनुभूति, आत्म-साक्षात्कार को विजय मिलेगी! ... सिंह जैसी शक्तिमान दस-बारह आत्माएँ ... ही संसार को हिला डालने के लिए पर्याप्त होंगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0441","text":"योग प्रवर्तक पतंजलि कहते हैं, \"जब मनुष्य समस्त अलौकिक दैवी शक्तियों के लोभ का त्याग करता है, तभी उसे धर्म-मेघ नामक समाधि प्राप्त होती है।\" वह परमात्मा का दर्शन करता है, वह परमात्मा बन जाता है और दूसरों को तदरूप बनने में सहायता करता है। मुझे इसी का प्रचार करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0442","text":"एक महान रहस्य का मैंने पता लगा लिया है -- वह यह कि केवल धर्म की बातें करने वालों से मुझे कुछ भय नहीं है। और जो सत्यद्रष्टा महात्मा हैं, वे कभी किसी से बैर नहीं करते। ... हम धर्मोपलब्धि, ब्रह्मलाभ एवं ब्रह्म होने के लिए ही दृढ़व्रत होंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0443","text":"जो सबका दास होता है, वही उनका सच्चा स्वामी होता है। जिसके प्रेम में ऊँच-नीच का विचार होता है, वह कभी नेता नहीं बन सकता। ... उसके चरणों में सारा संसार लोट जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0444","text":"वत्स, धीरज रखो, काम तुम्हारी आशा से बहुत ज्यादा बढ़ जाएगा। हर एक काम में सफलता प्राप्त करने से पहले सैकड़ों कठिनाइयों का सामना करना पड़ता है। ... जो प्रतीक्षा करता है, उसे सब चीजें मिलती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0445","text":"अकेले रहो, अकेले रहो। जो अकेला रहता है, उसका किसी से विरोध नहीं होता, वह किसीकी शान्ति भंग नहीं करता, न दूसरा कोई उसकी शान्ति भंग करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0446","text":"मेरी दृढ धारणा है कि तुममें अन्धविश्वास नहीं है। तुममें वह शक्ति विद्यमान है, जो संसार को हिला सकती है। ... उठो! उठो! संसार दुःख से जल रहा है। क्या तुम सो सकते हो? ... जीवन में और क्या है? इससे महान कर्म क्या है?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0447","text":"एक समस्या आती है, तब मनुष्य अनुभव करता है की थोड़ी-सी मनुष्य की सेवा करना लाखो जप-ध्यान से कही बढ़कर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0448","text":"किसी की निंदा ना करें। अगर आप मदद के लिए हाथ बढ़ा सकते हैं, तो ज़रुर बढाएं। अगर नहीं बढ़ा सकते, तो अपने हाथ जोड़िये, अपने भाइयों को आशीर्वाद दीजिये, और उन्हें उनके मार्ग पे जाने दीजिये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0449","text":"उठो मेरे शेरो, इस भ्रम को मिटा दो कि तुम निर्बल हो, तुम एक अमर आत्मा हो, स्वच्छंद जीव हो, धन्य हो, सनातन हो, तुम तत्व नहीं हो, ना ही शरीर हो, तत्व तुम्हारा सेवक है तुम तत्व के सेवक नहीं हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0450","text":"एक शब्द में, यह आदर्श है कि तुम परमात्मा हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0451","text":"उस व्यक्ति ने अमरत्त्व प्राप्त कर लिया है, जो किसी सांसारिक वस्तु से व्याकुल नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0452","text":"हम वो हैं जो हमें हमारी सोच ने बनाया है, इसलिए इस बात का धयान रखिये कि आप क्या सोचते हैं। शब्द गौण हैं। विचार रहते हैं, वे दूर तक यात्रा करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0453","text":"बाहरी स्वभाव केवल अंदरूनी स्वभाव का बड़ा रूप है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0454","text":"एक विचार लो। उस विचार को अपना जीवन बना लो – उसके बारे में सोचो, उसके सपने देखो, उस विचार को जियो। अपने मस्तिष्क, मांसपेशियों, नसों, शरीर के हर हिस्से को उस विचार में डूब जाने दो, और बाकी सभी विचारों को किनारे रख दो। यही सफल होने का तरीका है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0455","text":"जब कोई विचार अनन्य रूप से मस्तिष्क पर अधिकार कर लेता है तब वह वास्तविक भौतिक या मानसिक अवस्था में परिवर्तित हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0456","text":"एक समय में एक काम करो, और ऐसा करते समय अपनी पूरी आत्मा उसमे डाल दो और बाकी सब कुछ भूल जाओ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0457","text":"कुछ सच्चे, इमानदार और उर्जावान पुरुष और महिलाएं; जितना कोई भीड़ एक सदी में कर सकती है उससे अधिक एक वर्ष में कर सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0458","text":"कभी मत सोचिये कि आत्मा के लिए कुछ असंभव है। ऐसा सोचना सबसे बड़ा विधर्म है।अगर कोई पाप है, तो वो यही है; ये कहना कि तुम निर्बल हो या अन्य निर्बल हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0459","text":"जिस दिन आपके सामने कोई समस्या न आये – आप यकीन कर सकते हैं कि आप गलत रास्ते पर सफर कर रहे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0460","text":"कुछ मत पूछो, बदले में कुछ मत मांगो। जो देना है वो दो; वो तुम तक वापस आएगा, पर उसके बारे में अभी मत सोचो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0461","text":"धन्य हैं वो लोग जिनके शरीर दूसरों की सेवा करने में नष्ट हो जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0462","text":"वेदान्त दर्शन भारत के प्राचीन दर्शनों में से सबसे महत्त्वपूर्ण दर्शन है, जिसका विश्वास है कि केवल परमात्मा ही सत्य है। और दृष्टिगोचर विश्व असत्य है तथा व्यक्ति की आत्मा का सर्वोच्य आत्मा अर्थात् परमात्मा में लीन होना ही प्रत्येक मानव का लक्ष्य है। इसे मुक्ति कहा गया और सत्य ज्ञान से ही प्राप्त की जा सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0463","text":"हमें जो कुछ चाहिए वह यह श्रद्धा ही है। दुर्भाग्यवश भारत से इसका प्रायः लोप ही हो गया है, और हमारी वर्तमान दुर्दशा का कारण भी यही है। एकमात्र इस श्रद्धा के भेद से ही मनुष्य-मनुष्य में अन्तर पाया जाता है। ... यह श्रद्धा ही है, जो एक मनुष्य को बड़ा और दूसरे को दुर्बल और छोटा बना देती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0464","text":"हमारे जातीय शोणित में एक प्रकार के भयानक रोग का बीज समा रहा है और वह है प्रत्येक विषय को हँसकर उड़ा देना – गाम्भीर्य का अभाव। इस दोष का सम्पूर्ण रूप से त्याग करो। वीर होओ, श्रद्धा-सम्पन्न होओ, दूसरी बातें उनके पीछे आप ही आयेंगी – उन्हें उनका अनुसरण करना ही होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0465","text":"अपने से निम्न श्रेणिवालों के प्रति हमारा एकमात्र कर्तव्य है – उनको शिक्षा देना, उनके खोये हुए व्यक्तित्व के विकास के लिए सहायता करना। उनमें विचार पैदा कर दो – बस, उन्हें उसी एक सहायता का प्रयोजन है, और शेष सब काल इसके फलस्वरूप आप ही आ जायगा। यदि ग़रीब लड़का शिक्षा के मन्दिर तक न जा सके तो शिक्षा को ही उसके पास जाना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0466","text":"शिक्षा क्या वह है जिसने निरन्तर इच्छाशक्ति को बल-पूर्वक पीढ़ी-दर-पीढ़ी रोक कर प्रायः नष्ट कर दिया है... जो मनुष्य को धीरे धीरे यन्त्र बना रही है? अपनी स्वतन्त्र इच्छाशक्ति और बुद्धि के बल से अनुचित कर्म करनेवाला मेरे विचार से धन्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0467","text":"आज हमें आवश्यकता है वेदान्तयुक्त पाश्चात्य विज्ञान की, ब्रह्मचर्य के आदर्श और श्रद्धा तथा आत्मविश्वास की। … वेदान्त का सिद्धान्त है कि मनुष्य के अन्तर में–एक अबोध शिशु में भी–ज्ञान का समस्त भण्डार निहित है, केवल उसके जागृत होने की आवश्यकता है, और यही आचार्य का काम है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0468","text":"देखो, एकमात्र ब्रह्मचर्य का ठीक ठीक पालन कर सकने पर सभी विद्याएँ बहुत ही कम समय में हस्तगत हो जाती हैं – मनुष्य श्रुतिधर, स्मृतिधर बन जाता है। ब्रह्मचर्य के अभाव से ही हमारे देश का सब कुछ नष्ट हो गया।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0469","text":"मेरा विश्वास है कि गुरु के साक्षात् सम्पर्क रखते हुए, गुरु-गृह में निवास करने से ही यथार्थ शिक्षा की प्राप्ति होती है। गुरु से साक्षात् सम्पर्क हुए बिना किसी प्रकार की शिक्षा नहीं हो सकती। ... हमारे वर्तमान विश्वविद्यालयों की ही बात लीजिए... वे एक भी मौलिक-भाव-संपन्न व्यक्ति उत्पन्न नहीं कर सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0470","text":"सत्य, प्राचीन अथवा आधुनिक किसी समाज का सम्मान नहीं करता। समय को ही सत्य का सम्मान करना पड़ेगा, अन्यथा समाज ध्वंस हो जाय, कोई हानि नहीं। ... वही समाज सब से श्रेष्ठ है, जहाँ सर्वोच्च सत्यों को कार्य में परिणत किया जा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0471","text":"प्रत्येक मनुष्य एवं प्रत्येक राष्ट्र को बड़ा बनाने के लिए तीन बातें आवश्यक हैं– १. सौजन्य की शक्ति में दृढ़ विश्वास ,२. ईर्ष्या और सन्देह का अभाव, ३. जो सन्मार्ग पर चलने में और सत्कर्म करने में संलग्न हों, उनकी सहायता करना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0472","text":"यदि आपका आदर्श जड़ है, तो आप भी जड़ हो जायेंगे। स्मरण रहे हमारा आदर्श है, परमात्मा। एकमात्र वे ही अविनाशी हैं – अन्य किसी का अस्तित्व नहीं है, और उन परमात्मा की भाँति हम भी सदा विनाशहीन हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0473","text":"हिन्दू का खाना धार्मिक, उसका पीना धार्मिक, उसकी नींद धार्मिक उसकी चाल-ढाल धार्मिक, उसके विवाहादि धार्मिक, यहाँ तक कि उसकी डकैती करने की प्रेरणा भी धार्मिक है। … हरएक राष्ट्र का विश्व के लिए एक विशिष्ट कार्य होता है और जब तक वह आक्रान्त नहीं होता, तब तक वह राष्ट्र जीवित रहता है – चाहे कोई भी संकट क्यों न आये। पर ज्यों ही कार्य नष्ट हुआ कि राष्ट्र भी ढह जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0474","text":"क्या तुमने इतिहास में नहीं पढ़ा है कि देश के मृत्यु का चिह्न अपवित्रता या चरित्रहीनता के भीतर से होकर आया है – जब यह किसी जाति में प्रवेश कर जाती है, तो समझना कि उसका विनाश निकट आ गया है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0475","text":"इस समय हम पशुओं की अपेक्षा कोई अधिक नीतिपरायण नहीं हैं। केवल समाज के अनुशासन के भय से हम कुछ गड़बड़ नहीं करते। यदि समाज आज कह दे कि चोरी करने से अब दण्ड नहीं मिलेगा, तो हम इसी समय दूसरे की सम्पत्ति लूटने को छूट पड़ेंगे। पुलिस ही हमें सच्चरित्र बनाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0476","text":"अधिकांश सम्प्रदाय अल्पजीवी और पानी के बुदबुदे के समान क्षणभंगुर होते हैं, क्योंकि बहुधा उनके प्रणेताओं में चरित्र-बल नहीं होता। पूर्ण प्रेम और प्रतिक्रिया न करनेवाले हृदय से चरित्र का निर्माण होता है। जब नेता में चरित्र नहीं होता, तब उसमें निष्ठा की सम्भावना नहीं होती। चरित्र की पूर्ण पवित्रता से स्थायी विश्वास और निष्ठा अवश्य उत्पन्न होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0477","text":"हमसे पूछा जाता है कि ‘आपके धर्म से समाज का क्या लाभ है?’ समाज को सत्य की कसौटी बनाया गया है। यह तो बड़ी तर्कहीनता है। समाज केवल विकास की एक अवस्था है, जिसमें होकर हम गुज़र रहे हैं। ... मेरे गुरुदेव श्री रामकृष्ण परमहंस कहा करते थे, “तुम स्वयं अपने कमल के फूल को खिलने में सहायता क्यों नहीं देते? भौरे तब अपने आप आयेंगे।\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0478","text":"दूसरों में बुराई न देखो। बुराई अज्ञान है, दुर्बलता है। लोगों को यह बताने से क्या लाभ कि वे दुर्बल हैं। आलोचना और खण्डन से कोई लाभ नहीं होता। हमें उन्हें कुछ ऊँची वस्तु देनी चाहिए; उन्हें उनके गरिमामयी स्वरूप की, उनके जन्मसिद्ध अधिकार की बात बताओ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0479","text":"और किसी बात की आवश्यकता नहीं, आवश्यकता है केवल प्रेम, अकपटता एवं धैर्य की। जीवन का अर्थ ही वृद्धि, अर्थात् विस्तार, यानी प्रेम है। इसलिए प्रेम ही जीवन है, यही जीवन का एकमात्र गतिनियामक है और स्वार्थपरता ही मृत्यु है। परोपकार ही जीवन है, परोपकार न करना ही मृत्यु है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0480","text":"एक ओर नया भारत कहता है कि “पाश्चात्य भाव, भाषा, खान-पान, वेश-भूषा और रीति का अवलम्बन करने से ही हम लोग पाश्चात्य जातियों की शक्तिमान हो सकेंगे।” दूसरी ओर प्राचीन भारत कहता है कि “मूर्ख। नक़ल से भी कहीं दूसरों का भाव अपना हुआ है? क्या सिंह की खाल पहनकर गधा कहीं सिंह हुआ है?\"","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0481","text":"एक ओर नवीन भारत कहता है कि “पाश्चात्य जातियाँ जो कुछ करें वही अच्छा है। अच्छा न होता तो वे ऐसी बलवान हुई कैसे?” दूसरी ओर प्राचीन भारत कहता है कि “बिजली की चमक तो खूब होती है, पर क्षणिक होती है। रुको! तुम्हारी आँखें चौंधिया रही हैं, सावधान!","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0482","text":"उपनिषद्युगीन सुदूर अतीत में, हमने इस संसार को एक चुनौती दी थी – न प्रजया धनेन त्यागेनैके अमृतत्वमानशुः – “न तो सन्तति द्वारा और न सम्पत्ति द्वारा, वरन केवल त्याग द्वारा ही अमृतत्व की उपलब्धि होती है।” ... हमारा समाधान है : असांसारिकता – त्याग।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0483","text":"मुझे एक ऐसा उदाहरण बताओ, जहाँ बाहर से इन प्रार्थनाओं का उत्तर मिला हो। जो भी उत्तर पाते हो, वह अपने हृदय से ही। तुम जानते हो कि भूत नहीं होते, किन्तु अन्धकार में जाते ही शरीर कुछ काँप सा जाता है। इन सबको जीत लो। धर्म के विषय में विश्व-ब्रह्माण्ड के एकत्व और आत्मविश्वास के अतिरिक्त और क्या शिक्षा आवश्यक है? शिक्षा केवल इतनी ही देनी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0484","text":"सभी शक्तियाँ तुम्हारे भीतर हैं, तुम कुछ भी कर सकते हो (स्रोत: कर्म योग, स्वामी विवेकानंद, 1896)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0485","text":"हमें ऐसी शिक्षा की आवश्यकता है जिससे चरित्र-निर्माण हो, मानसिक शक्ति बढ़े, बुद्धि विकसित हो, और मनुष्य अपने पैरों पर खड़ा होना सीखे। -- (विवेकानंद जी के सान्निध्य में, ४९-५०)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0486","text":"जिस अभ्यास से मनुष्य की इच्छाशक्ति, और प्रकाश संयमित होकर फलदाई बने उसी का नाम है शिक्षा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0487","text":"समस्त ज्ञान चाहे वो लोकिक हो या आध्यात्मिक, मनुष्य के मन में है परन्तु प्रकाशित ना होकर वह ढका रहता है । अध्ययन से वह धीरे धीरे उजागर होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0488","text":"विद्यार्थी की आवश्यकता के अनुसार शिक्षा में परिवर्तन होना चाहिए ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0489","text":"ज्ञान की प्राप्ति के लिए केवल एक ही मार्ग है और वह है ‘एकाग्रता’ ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0490","text":"एकाग्रता की शक्ति ही ज्ञान के खजाने की एकमात्र कुंजी है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0491","text":"ज्ञान का दान मुक्तहस्ट होकर, बिना कोई दाम लिए करना चाहिए ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0492","text":"गुरु के प्रति विश्वास, नम्रता, विनय, और श्रद्धा के बिना हममें धर्म का भाव पनप नहीं सकता ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0493","text":"अधिकांश महापुरुषों को सुख की अपेक्षा दुख और संपत्ति की अपेक्षा दरिद्रता ने अधिक शिक्षा दी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0494","text":"हम स्वयं अपने भाग्य का निर्माण करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0495","text":"जब मन को एकाग्र करके अपने ऊपर लगाया जाता है तो हमारे भीतर के सभी हमारे नोकर बन जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0496","text":"मनुष्य जैसा सोचता है वैसा बन जाता है ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0497","text":"आत्मविश्वास मानवता का एक शक्तिशाली अंग है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0498","text":"शिक्षक अर्थात गुरु के व्यक्तिगत जीवन के बिना कोई शिक्षा नहीं हो सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0499","text":"शिष्य के लिए आवश्यकता है शुद्धता, ज्ञान की सच्ची लगन के साथ परिश्रम की।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0500","text":"मस्तिष्क में अनेक तरह का ज्ञान भर लेना, उससे कुछ काम न लेना और जन्म भर वाद विवाद करते रहने का नाम शिक्षा नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0501","text":"शिक्षा और मेहनत एक सुनहरी चाबी होती है जो बंद भाग्य के दरवाजों को आसानी से खोल देती है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0502","text":"यदि गरीब लड़का शिक्षा के लिए नहीं आ सकता है, तो शिक्षा उसके पास जानी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0503","text":"ज्ञान स्वयं में वर्तमान है, मनुष्य केवल उसका आविष्कार करता है ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0504","text":"जब तक जीना, तब तक सीखना, अनुभव ही जगत में सर्वश्रेष्ठ शिक्षक है ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0505","text":"तब तक आपको कोई शिक्षित नहीं कर पायेगा जब तक आप स्वयं प्रयास नहीं करते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0506","text":"मैं कहता हूँ – मुक्त करो; जहाँ तक हो सके लोगों के बन्धन खोल दो। … जब तुम सुख की कामना समाज के लिए त्याग सकोगे तब तुम भगवान बुद्ध बन जाओगे, तब तुम मुक्त हो जाओगे। -- (स्वामी विवेकानंद की पत्रावली २, २९२)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0507","text":"महिलाओ को ऐसी शिक्षा मिलनी चाहिए की वे आत्मनिर्भर बन सके और अपनी समस्या खुद हल करने में समर्थ बन सके। उनमे एक आदर्श चरित्र का विकास हो सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0508","text":"किसी धर्म को विशेष शिक्षा से जोड़ना उचित नहीं है। सभी धर्मो की आवश्यक सामग्री को शिक्षा से जोड़ना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0509","text":"शिक्षा का अर्थ है उस पूर्णता को व्यक्त करना जो सब मनुष्यों में पहले से विद्यमान है। -- (स्वामी विवेकानन्द की पत्रावली १, ११४)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0510","text":"शिक्षा क्या है? क्या वह पुस्तक-विद्या है? नहीं! क्या वह नाना प्रकार का ज्ञान है? नहीं, यह भी नहीं। जिस संयम के द्वारा इच्छाशक्ति का प्रवाह और विकास वश में लाया जाता है और वह फलदायक होता है, वह शिक्षा कहलाती है। -- (स्वामी विवेकानन्द की पत्रावली २, २९०-९१)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0511","text":"मेरे विचार से तो शिक्षा का सार मन की एकाग्रता प्राप्त करना है, तथ्यों का संकलन नहीं। यदि मुझे फिर से अपनी शिक्षा आरम्भ करनी हो और इसमें मेरा वश चले, तो मैं तथ्यों का अध्ययन कदापि न करूँ। मैं मन की एकाग्रता और अनासक्ति का सामर्थ्य बढ़ाता और उपकरण के पूर्णतया तैयार होने पर उससे इच्छानुसार तथ्यों का संकलन करता। -- (भगवान बुद्ध का संसार को संदेश एवं अन्य व्याख्यान और प्रवचन, ७१)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0512","text":"जो शिक्षा साधारण व्यक्ति को जीवन-संग्राम में समर्थ नहीं बना सकती, जो मनुष्य में चरित्र-बल, परहित-भावना तथा सिंह के समान साहस नहीं ला सकती, वह भी कोई शिक्षा है? जिस शिक्षा के द्वारा जीवन में अपने पैरों पर खड़ा हुआ जाता है, वही है शिक्षा। -- (विवेकानन्द जी के संग में, १७५)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0513","text":"शिक्षा का मतलब यह नहीं है कि तुम्हारे दिमाग़ में ऐसी बहुत सी बातें इस तरह ठूँस दी जायँ, जो आपस में, लड़ने लगें और तुम्हारा दिमाग़ उन्हें जीवन भर में हज़म न कर सके। जिस शिक्षा से हम अपना जीवन-निर्माण कर सकें, मनुष्य बन सकें, चरित्र-गठन कर सकें और विचारों का सामंजस्य कर सकें, वही वास्तव में शिक्षा कहलाने योग्य है। यदि तुम पाँच ही भावों को हज़म कर तदनुसार जीवन और चरित्र गठित कर सके हो तो तुम्हारी शिक्षा उस आदमी की अपेक्षा बहुत अधिक है, जिसने एक पूरी की पूरी लाइब्रेरी ही कण्ठस्थ कर ली है। -- (भारत में विवेकानन्द – भारत का भविष्य)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0514","text":"ज्ञान मनुष्य में अन्तर्निहित ही है। कोई भी ज्ञान बाहर से नहीं आता, सब अन्दर ही है। … हम कहते है कि न्यूटन ने गुरुत्वाकर्षण का आविष्कार किया। तो क्या वह आविष्कार कहीं एक कोने में बैठा हुआ न्यूटन की प्रतीक्षा कर रहा था? नहीं, वह उसके मन में ही था। जब समय आया तो उसने उसे ढूँढ निकाला। संसार ने जो कुछ ज्ञान लाभ किया है, वह मन से ही निकला है। विश्व का असीम पुस्तकालय तुम्हारे मन में ही विद्यमान है। बाह्य जगत् तो तुम्हें अपने मन को अध्ययन में लगाने के लिए उद्दीपक तथा सहायक मात्र है; परन्तु प्रत्येक समय तुम्हारे अध्ययन का विषय तुम्हारा मन ही है। -- (कर्मयोग २-३)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0515","text":"हरएक व्यक्ति हुकूमत जताना चाहता है, पर आज्ञा पालन करने के लिए कोई भी तैयार नहीं है। और यह सब इसलिए है कि प्राचीन काल के उस अद्भुत ब्रह्मचर्य आश्रम का अब पालन नहीं किया जाता। पहले आदेश पालन करना सीखो, आदेश देना फिर स्वयं आ जायगा। पहले सर्वदा दास होना सीखो, तभी तुम प्रभु हो सकोगे। -- (वेदान्त : जाफना में दिया भाषण)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0516","text":"केवल शिक्षा! शिक्षा! शिक्षा! यूरोप के बहुतेरे नगरों में घूमकर और वहाँ के ग़रीबों के भी अमन-चैन और विद्या को देखकर हमारे ग़रीबों की बात याद आती थी और मैं आँसू बहाता था। यह अन्तर क्यों हुआ? जवाब पाया – शिक्षा! -- (स्वामी विवेकानन्द की पत्रावली २, ७४)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Swami Vivekananda — शिक्षा पर विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0517","text":"'प्रगतिशील लेखक संघ' यह नाम ही मेरे विचार से गलत है। साहित्यकार या कलाकार स्वभावतः प्रगतिशील होता है। अगर वो इसका स्वभाव न होता तो शायद वो साहित्यकार ही नहीं होता। उसे अपने अंदर भी एक कमी महसूस होती है, इसी कमी को पूरा करने के लिए उसकी आत्मा बेचैन रहती है। -- प्रेमचन्द, १९३६ में लखनऊ में हुए प्रगतिशील लेखक संघ के प्रथम अधिवेशन में अपने भाषण में अपने भाषण में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0518","text":"हिंदू अपनी संस्कृति को कयामत तक सुरक्षित रखना चाहता है, मुसलमान अपनी संस्कृति को। दोनों ही अभी तक अपनी-अपनी संस्कृति को अछूती समझ रहे हैं, यह भूल गए हैं कि अब न कहीं हिंदू संस्कृति है, न मुस्लिम संस्कृति और न कोई अन्य संस्कृति। अब संसार में केवल एक संस्कृति है और वह है आर्थिक संस्कृति, मगर आज भी हिंदू और मुस्लिम संस्कृति का रोना रोए चले जाते हैं, हालांकि संस्कृति का धर्म से कोई संबंध नहीं। -- प्रेमचन्द, अपने एक लेख में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0519","text":"संसार में हिंदू ही एक जाति है, जो गोमांस को अखाद्य या अपवित्र समझती है तो क्या इसलिए हिंदुओं को समस्त विश्व से धर्मसंग्राम छेड़ देना चाहिए? हिंदू गाय की पूजा स्वयं कर सकते हैं, पर उन्हें दूसरों को भी ऐसे ही करने को बाध्य करने का तो कोई अधिकार नहीं है। -- प्रेमचन्द","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0520","text":"अधिकार में स्वयं एक आनन्द है, जो उपयोगिता की परवाह नहीं करता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0521","text":"शिक्षा वह शस्त्र है जिससे हम समाज की बुराइयों का अंत कर सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0522","text":"अगर मूर्ख, लोभ और मोह के पंजे में फंस जाएं तो वे क्षम्य हैं, परन्तु विद्या और सभ्यता के उपासकों की स्वार्थांधता अत्यंत लज्जाजनक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0523","text":"अच्छे कामों की सिद्धि में बड़ी देर लगती है, पर बुरे कामों की सिद्धि में यह बात नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0524","text":"अज्ञान की भांति ज्ञान भी सरल, निष्कपट और सुनहले स्वप्न देखने वाला होता है। मानवता में उनका विश्वास इतना दृढ़,इतना सजीव होता है कि वह इसके विरुद्ध व्यवहार को अमानुषीय समझने लगता है। यह वह भूल जाता है की भेड़ियों ने भेडो को निरीहता का जवाब सदैव पंजों और दांतो से दिया है। वह अपना एक आदर्श संसार बनाकर आदर्श मानवता से अवसाद करता है और उसी में मग्न रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0525","text":"अज्ञान में सफाई है और हिम्मत है, उसके दिल और जुबान में पर्दा नहीं होता, ना कथनी और करनी में। क्या यह अफसोस की बात नहीं, ज्ञान अज्ञान के आगे सिर झुकाए?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0526","text":"अतीत चाहे जैसे भी हो उनकी स्मृतियां प्राय: सुखद होती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0527","text":"अनाथ बच्चों का हृदय उस चित्र की भांति होता है जिस पर एक बहुत ही साधारण परदा पड़ा हुआ हो। पवन का साधारण झकोरा भी उसे हटा देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0528","text":"अनाथों का क्रोध पटाखे की आवाज है, जिससे बच्चे डर जाते हैं और असर कुछ नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0529","text":"अनुराग, यौवन, रूप या धन से उत्पन्न नहीं होता। अनुराग, अनुराग से उत्पन्न होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0530","text":"नीचता किसी जाति में नहीं, मनुष्य के व्यवहार में होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0531","text":"अन्याय को बढ़ाने वाले कम अन्यायी नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0532","text":"अन्याय में सहयोग देना, अन्याय करने के ही समान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0533","text":"अपनी भूल अपने ही हाथों से सुधर जाए, तो यह उससे कहीं अच्छा है कि कोई दूसरा उसे सुधारे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0534","text":"अपने उत्तरदायित्व का ज्ञान बहुधा हमारे संकुचित व्यवहारों का सुधारक होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0535","text":"अपमान का भय क़ानून के भय से किसी तरह कम क्रियाशील नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0536","text":"आकाश में उड़ने वाले पंछी को भी अपने घर की याद आती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0537","text":"आत्म सम्मान की रक्षा, हमारा सबसे पहला धर्म है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0538","text":"आदमी का सबसे बड़ा दुश्मन गुरूर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0539","text":"आलस्य वह राजयोग है जिसका रोगी कभी संभल नहीं पाता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0540","text":"आलोचना और दूसरों की बुराइयां करने में बहुत फर्क है। आलोचना क़रीब लाती है और बुराई दूर करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0541","text":"आशा उत्साह की जननी है। आशा में तेज है, बल है, जीवन है। आशा ही संसार की संचालक शक्ति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0542","text":"इंसान का कोई मूल्य नहीं, केवल दहेज का मूल्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0543","text":"इंसान सब हैं पर इंसानियत विरलों में मिलती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0544","text":"इतना पुराना मित्रता रुपी वृक्ष सत्य का एक झोंका भी न सह सका। सचमुच वह बालू की ही जमीन पर खड़ा था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0545","text":"उपहास और विरोध तो किसी भी सुधारक के लिए पुरस्कार जैसे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0546","text":"ऐश की भूख रोटियों से कभी नहीं मिटती। उसके लिए दुनिया के एक से एक उम्दा पदार्थ चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0547","text":"कभी-कभी हमें उन लोगों से शिक्षा मिलती है, जिन्हें हम अभिमान वश अज्ञानी समझते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0548","text":"कर्तव्य कभी आग और पानी की परवाह नहीं करता, कर्तव्य पालन में ही चित्त की शांति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0549","text":"कर्तव्य-पालन में ही चित्त की शांति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0550","text":"धन से नहीं, चरित्र से मनुष्य महान बनता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0551","text":"कायरता की भांति वीरता भी संक्रामक होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0552","text":"कार्यकुशलता की व्यक्ति को हर जगह जरूरत पड़ती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0553","text":"किसी किश्ती पर अगर फर्ज का मल्लाह न हो तो फिर उसके लिए दरिया में डूब जाने के सिवाय और कोई चारा नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0554","text":"कुल की प्रतिष्ठा भी विनम्रता और सद्व्यवहार से होती है, हेकड़ी और रुआब दिखाने से नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0555","text":"केवल बुद्धि के द्वारा ही मानव का मनुष्यत्व प्रकट होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0556","text":"कोई वाद जब विवाद का रूप धारण कर लेता है तो वह अपने लक्ष्य से दूर हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0557","text":"क्रांति बैठे-ठालों का खेल नहीं है। वह नई सभ्यता को जन्म देती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0558","text":"क्रोध और ग्लानि से सद्भावनाएं विकृत हो जाती हैं। जैसे कोई मैली वस्तु निर्मल वस्तु को दूषित कर देती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0559","text":"क्रोध में मनुष्य अपने मन की बात नहीं कहता, वह केवल दूसरों का दिल दुखाना चाहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0560","text":"ख़तरा हमारी छिपी हुई हिम्मतों की कुंजी है। खतरे में पड़कर हम भय की सीमाओं से आगे बढ़ जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0561","text":"खाने और सोने का नाम जीवन नहीं है, जीवन नाम है, आगे बढ़ते रहने की लगन का।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0562","text":"ख्याति-प्रेम वह प्यास है जो कभी नहीं बुझती। वह अगस्त ऋषि की भांति सागर को पीकर भी शांत नहीं होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0563","text":"गरज वाले आदमी के साथ कठोरता करने में लाभ है लेकिन बेगरज वाले को दाव पर पाना जरा कठिन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0564","text":"गलती करना उतना ग़लत नहीं जितना उन्हें दोहराना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0565","text":"घर सेवा की सीढ़ी का पहला डंडा है। इसे छोड़कर तुम ऊपर नहीं जा सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0566","text":"चापलूसी का ज़हरीला प्याला आपको तब तक नुकसान नहीं पहुंचा सकता, जब तक कि आपके कान उसे अमृत समझकर पी न जाएं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0567","text":"चिंता एक काली दीवार की भांति चारों ओर से घेर लेती है, जिसमें से निकलने की फिर कोई गली नहीं सूझती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0568","text":"चिन्ता रोग का मूल है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0569","text":"चोर केवल दंड से नहीं बचना चाहता, वह अपमान से भी बचना चाहता है। वह दंड से उतना नहीं डरता है, जितना कि अपमान से।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0570","text":"जब दूसरों के पांवों तले अपनी गर्दन दबी हुई हो, तो उन पांवों को सहलाने में ही कुशल है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0571","text":"जब हम अपनी भूल पर लज्जित होते हैं, तो यथार्थ बात अपने आप ही मुंह से निकल पड़ती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0572","text":"जवानी जोश है, बल है, साहस है, दया है, आत्मविश्वास है, गौरव है और वह सब कुछ है जो जीवन को पवित्र, उज्ज्वल और पूर्ण बना देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0573","text":"जिस तरह सुखी लकड़ी जल्दी से जल उठती है, उसी तरह भूख से बावला मनुष्य जरा-जरा सी बात पर तिनक जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0574","text":"जिस प्रकार नेत्रहीन के लिए दर्पण बेकार है उसी प्रकार बुद्धिहीन के लिए विद्या बेकार है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0575","text":"जिस बंदे को पेट भर रोटी नहीं मिलती, उसके लिए मर्यादा और इज्जत ढोंग है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0576","text":"जिस साहित्य से हमारी सुरुचि न जागे, आध्यात्मिक और मानसिक तृप्ति न मिले, हममें गति और शक्ति न पैदा हो, हमारा सौंदर्य प्रेम न जागृत हो, जो हममें संकल्प और कठिनाइयों पर विजय प्राप्त करने की सच्ची दृढ़ता न उत्पन्न करें, वह हमारे लिए बेकार है वह साहित्य कहलाने का अधिकारी नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0577","text":"जिसके पास जितनी ही बड़ी डिग्री है, उसका स्वार्थ भी उतना ही बड़ा हुआ है मानो लोभ और स्वार्थ ही विद्वता के लक्षण हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0578","text":"जीवन एक दीर्घ पश्चाताप के सिवा और क्या है?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0579","text":"जीवन का वास्तविक सुख, दूसरों को सुख देने में है, उनका सुख लूटने में नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0580","text":"जीवन का सुख दूसरों को सुखी करने में है, उनको लूटने में नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0581","text":"जीवन की दुर्घटनाओं में अक्‍सर बड़े महत्‍व के नैतिक पहलू छिपे हुए होते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0582","text":"जीवन में सफल होने के लिए आपको शिक्षा की ज़रूरत है न की साक्षरता और डिग्री की।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0583","text":"जो प्रेम असहिष्णु हो, जो दूसरों के मनोभावों का तनिक भी विचार न करे, जो मिथ्या कलंक आरोपण करने में संकोच न करे, वह उन्माद है, प्रेम नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0584","text":"जो शिक्षा हमें निर्बलों को सताने के लिए तैयार करे, जो हमें धरती और धन का ग़ुलाम बनाए, जो हमें भोग-विलास में डुबाए, जो हमें दूसरों का ख़ून पीकर मोटा होने का इच्छुक बनाए, वह शिक्षा नहीं भ्रष्टता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0585","text":"डरपोक प्राणियों में सत्य भी गूंगा हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0586","text":"दया मनुष्य का स्वाभाविक गुण है।।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0587","text":"दुखियारों को हमदर्दी के आँसू भी कम प्यारे नहीं होते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0588","text":"दुनिया में विपत्ति से बढ़कर अनुभव सिखाने वाला कोई भी विद्यालय आज तक नहीं खुला है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0589","text":"देश का उद्धार विलासियों द्वारा नहीं हो सकता। उसके लिए सच्चा त्यागी होना आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0590","text":"दोस्ती के लिए कोई अपना ईमान नहीं बेचता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0591","text":"दौलत से आदमी को जो सम्मान मिलता है, वह उसका नहीं, उसकी दौलत का सम्‍मान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0592","text":"द्वेष का मायाजाल बड़ी-बड़ी मछलियों को ही फसाता है। छोटी मछलियां या तो उसमें फंसती ही नहीं या तुरंत निकल जाती हैं। उनके लिए वह घातक जाल क्रीडा की वस्तु है, भय का नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0593","text":"धन खोकर अगर हम अपनी आत्मा को पा सकें तो यह कोई महंगा सौदा नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0594","text":"धर्म सेवा का नाम है, लूट और कत्ल का नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0595","text":"नमस्कार करने वाला व्यक्ति विनम्रता को ग्रहण करता है और समाज में सभी के प्रेम का पात्र बन जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0596","text":"नाटक उस वक्त पसंद होता है, जब रसिक समाज उसे पसंद कर लेता है। बारात का नाटक उस वक्त पास होता है, जब राह चलते आदमी उसे पसंद कर लेते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0597","text":"नारी और सब कुछ बर्दाश्त कर लेगी, पर अपने मायके की बुराई कभी नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0598","text":"निराशा सम्भव को असम्भव बना देती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0599","text":"नीति चतुर प्राणी अवसर के अनुकूल काम करता है, जहाँ दबना चाहिए वहां दब जाता है, जहाँ गरम होना चाहिए वहां गरम होता है, उसे मान अपमान का, हर्ष या दुःख नहीं होता उसकी दृष्टि निरंतर अपने लक्ष्य पर रहती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0600","text":"नीतिज्ञ के लिए अपना लक्ष्य ही सब कुछ है। आत्मा का उसके सामने कुछ मूल्य नहीं। गौरव सम्‍पन्‍न प्राणियों के लिए चरित्र बल ही सर्वप्रधान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0601","text":"नौकरी में ओहदे की ओर ध्यान मत दो, यह तो पीर का मजार है। निगाह चढ़ावे और चादर पर रखनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0602","text":"न्याय और नीति लक्ष्मी के खिलौने हैं, वह जैसे चाहती है नचाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0603","text":"पंच के दिल में खुदा बसता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0604","text":"पहाड़ों की कंदराओं में बैठकर तप कर लेना सहज है, किन्तु परिवार में रहकर धीरज बनाये रखना सबके वश की बात नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0605","text":"प्रेम एक बीज है, जो एक बार जमकर फिर बड़ी मुश्किल से उखड़ता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0606","text":"बल की शिकायतें सब सुनते हैं, निर्बल की फरियाद कोई नहीं सुनता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0607","text":"बालकों पर प्रेम की भांति द्वेष का असर भी अधिक होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0608","text":"बुढ़ापा तृष्णा रोग का अंतिम समय है, जब संपूर्ण इच्छाएं एक ही केंद्र पर आ लगती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0609","text":"बूढो के लिए अतीत में सूखो और वर्तमान के दु:खो और भविष्य के सर्वनाश से ज्यादा मनोरंजक और कोई प्रसंग नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0610","text":"भरोसा प्यार करने के लिए पहला कदम है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0611","text":"भाग्य पर वह भरोसा करता है जिसमें पौरुष नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0612","text":"मन एक भीरु शत्रु है जो सदैव पीठ के पीछे से वार करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0613","text":"मनुष्य का उद्धार पुत्र से नहीं, अपने कर्मों से होता है। यश और कीर्ति भी कर्मों से प्राप्त होती है। संतान वह सबसे कठिन परीक्षा है, जो ईश्वर ने मनुष्य को परखने के लिए दी है। बड़ी~बड़ी आत्माएं, जो सभी परीक्षाओं में सफल हो जाती हैं, यहाँ ठोकर खाकर गिर पड़ती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0614","text":"मनुष्य का मन और मस्तिष्क पर भय का जितना प्रभाव होता है, उतना और किसी शक्ति का नहीं। प्रेम, चिंता, हानि यह सब मन को अवश्य दुखित करते हैं, पर यह हवा के हल्के झोंके हैं और भय प्रचंड आधी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0615","text":"मनुष्य कितना ही हृदयहीन हो, उसके ह्रदय के किसी न किसी कोने में पराग की भांति रस छिपा रहता है। जिस तरह पत्थर में आग छिपी रहती है, उसी तरह मनुष्य के ह्रदय में भी चाहे वह कितना ही क्रूर क्यों न हो, उत्कृष्ट और कोमल भाव छिपे रहते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0616","text":"मनुष्य को देखो, उसकी आवश्यकता को देखो तथा अवसर को देखो उसके उपरांत जो उचित समझा, करो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0617","text":"मनुष्य बराबर वालों की हंसी नहीं सह सकता, क्योंकि उनकी हंसी में ईर्ष्या, व्यंग्य और जलन होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0618","text":"मनुष्य बिगड़ता है या तो परिस्थितियों से अथवा पूर्व संस्कारों से। परिस्थितियों से गिरने वाला मनुष्य उन परिस्थितियों का त्याग करने से ही बच सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0619","text":"महान व्यक्ति महत्वाकांक्षा के प्रेम से बहुत अधिक आकर्षित होते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0620","text":"महिला सहानुभूति से हार को भी जीत बना सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0621","text":"माँ के बलिदानों का ऋण कोई बेटा नहीं चुका सकता, चाहे वह भूमंडल का स्वामी ही क्यों न हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0622","text":"मासिक वेतन पूरन मासी का चाँद है जो एक दिन दिखाई देता है और घटते-घटते लुप्त हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0623","text":"मुहब्बत रूह की खुराक है। यह वह अमृत की बूंद है जो मरे हुए भावों को जिंदा कर देती है। मुहब्बत आत्मिक वरदान है। यह ज़िंदगी की सबसे पाक, सबसे ऊंची, सबसे मुबारक बरकत है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0624","text":"मेरी ज़िन्दगी सादी व कठोर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0625","text":"मैं एक मज़दूर हूँ। जिस दिन कुछ लिख न लूँ, उस दिन मुझे रोटी खाने का कोई हक नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0626","text":"यदि झूठ बोलने से किसी की जान बचती हो तो, झूठ पाप नहीं पुण्य है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0627","text":"यश त्याग से मिलता है, धोखाधड़ी से नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0628","text":"युवावस्था आवेश मय होती है, वह क्रोध से आग हो जाती है तो करुणा से पानी भी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0629","text":"लगन को कांटों कि परवाह नहीं होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0630","text":"लिखते तो वह लोग हैं, जिनके अंदर कुछ दर्द है, अनुराग है, लगन है, विचार है। जिन्होंने धन और भोग विलास को जीवन का लक्ष्य बना लिया, वो क्या लिखेंगे?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0631","text":"लोकनिंदा का भय इसलिए है कि वह हमें बुरे कामों से बचाती है। अगर वह कर्तव्य मार्ग में बाधक हो तो उससे डरना कायरता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0632","text":"वर्तमान ही सब कुछ है। भविष्य की चिंता हमें कायर बना देती है और भूत का भार हमारी कमर तोड़ देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0633","text":"वही तलवार, जो केले को नहीं काट सकती। शान पर चढ़कर लोहे को काट देती है। मानव जीवन में आग बड़े महत्व की चीज है। जिसमें आग है वह बूढ़ा भी तो जवान है। जिसमे आग नहीं है, गैरत नहीं, वह भी मृतक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0634","text":"विचार और व्यवहार में सामंजस्य न होना ही धूर्तता है, मक्कारी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0635","text":"विजयी व्यक्ति स्वभाव से, बहिर्मुखी होता है। पराजय व्यक्ति को अन्तर्मुखी बनाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0636","text":"विपत्ति से बढ़कर अनुभव सिखाने वाला कोई विद्यालय आज तक नहीं खुला।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0637","text":"विलास सच्चे सुख की छाया मात्र है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0638","text":"विषय-भोग से धन का ही सर्वनाश नहीं होता, इससे कहीं अधिक बुद्धि और बल का भी नाश होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0639","text":"वीरात्माएं सत्कार्य में विरोध की परवाह नहीं करतीं और अंत में उस पर विजय ही पाती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0640","text":"व्यंग्य शाब्दिक कलह की चरम सीमा है उसका प्रतिकार मुंह से नहीं हाथ से होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0641","text":"शत्रु का अंत शत्रु के जीवन के साथ ही हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0642","text":"संतान वह सबसे कठिन परीक्षा है जो ईश्वर ने मनुष्य को परखने के लिए गढ़ी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0643","text":"संसार के सारे नाते स्नेह के नाते हैं, जहां स्नेह नहीं वहां कुछ नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0644","text":"संसार में गऊ बनने से काम नहीं चलता, जितना दबो, उतना ही दबाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0645","text":"सफलता दोषों को मिटाने की विलक्षण शक्ति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0646","text":"सफलता में अनंत सजीवता होती है, विफलता में असह्य अशक्ति।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0647","text":"समानता की बात तो बहुत से लोग करते हैं, लेकिन जब उसका अवसर आता है तो खामोश रह जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0648","text":"साक्षरता अच्छी चीज है और उससे जीवन की कुछ समस्याएं हल हो जाती है, लेकिन यह समझना कि किसान निरा मूर्ख है, उसके साथ अन्याय करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0649","text":"हम जिनके लिए त्याग करते हैं, उनसे किसी बदले की आशा ना रखकर भी उनके मन पर शासन करना चाहते हैं। चाहे वह शासन उन्हीं के हित के लिए हो। त्याग की मात्रा जितनी ज्यादा होती है, यह शासन भावना उतनी ही प्रबल होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0650","text":"हिम्मत और हौसला मुश्किल को आसान कर सकते हैं, आंधी और तूफ़ान से बचा सकते हैं, मगर चेहरे को खिला सकना उनके सामर्थ्य से बाहर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0651","text":"सोई हुई आत्मा को जगाने के लिए भूलें एक प्रकार की दैविक यंत्रणाएं जो हमें सदा के लिए सतर्क कर देती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0652","text":"सौंदर्य को गहने की जरूरत नहीं है। मृदुता गहनों का वजन सहन नहीं कर सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0653","text":"सौभाग्य उन्हीं को प्राप्त होता है जो अपने कर्तव्य पथ पर अविचल रहते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0654","text":"स्त्री गालियां सह लेती है, मार भी सह लेती है, पर मायके की निंदा उससे नहीं सही जाती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0655","text":"स्वार्थ में मनुष्य बावला हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0656","text":"जो वह ईश्वर और मोक्ष का चक्कर है इस पर तो मुझे हँसी आती है। यह मोक्ष और उपासना अहंकार की पराकाष्ठा है, जो हमारी मानवता को नष्ट किए डालती है। जहाँ जीवन है, क्रीड़ा है, चहक है, प्रेम है, वहीं ईश्वर है और जीवन को सुखी बनाना ही मोक्ष है और उपासना है। ज्ञानी कहता है, होंठों पर मुस्कुराहट न आए, आँखों में आँसू न आए। मैं कहता हूँ, गर तुम हँस नहीं सकते और रो नहीं सकते तो तुम मनुष्य नहीं पत्थर हो। वह ज्ञान जो मानवता को पीस डाले, ज्ञान नहीं कोल्हू है। -- प्रेमचन्द, 'गोदान' नामक अपने अंतिम उपन्यास में अपने एक पात्र के मुँह से","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0657","text":"कायरों को इसके सिवा और सूझ ही क्या सकता है? धन कमाना आसान नहीं है। व्यवसायियों को जितनी कठिनाइयों का सामना करना पड़ता है, वह अगर संन्यासियों को झेलनी पड़े, तो सारा संन्यास भूल जाएं। किसी भले आदमी के द्वार पर जाकर पड़े रहने के लिए बल, बुद्धि, विद्या, साहस किसी की भी जरूरत नहीं। धनोपार्जन के लिए खून जलाना पड़ता है। सहज काम नहीं है। धन कहीं पड़ा नहीं है कि जो चाहे बटोर लाए। -- प्रेमचन्द, 'कर्मभूमि' में सुखदा के मुंह से","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0658","text":"जिन वृक्षों की जड़ें गहरी होती हैं, उन्हें बार-बार सींचने की जरूरत नहीं होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0659","text":"रोने के लिए हम एकांत ढूंढते हैं, हसंने के लिए अनेकांत।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0660","text":"पुरुष में थोड़ी-सी पशुता होती है, जिसे वह इरादा करके भी हटा नहीं सकता। वही पशुता उसे पुरुष बनाती है। विकास के क्रम से वह स्त्री से पीछे है। जिस दिन वह पूर्ण विकास को पहुंचेगा, वह भी स्त्री हो जाएगा। वात्सल्य, स्नेह, कोमलता, दया, इन्हीं आधारों पर यह सृष्टि थमी हुई है और यह स्त्रियों के गुण हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0661","text":"हमारे शिक्षालयों में नर्मी को घुसने ही नहीं दिया जाता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0662","text":"हमारे शिक्षालयों में नर्मी को घुसने ही नहीं दिया जाता। वहां स्थायी रूप से मार्शल-लॉ का व्यवहार होता है। कचहरी में पैसे का राज है, हमारे स्कूलों में भी पैसे का राज है, उससे कहीं कठोर, कहीं निर्दय। देर में आइए तो जुर्माना न आइए तो जुर्माना सबक न याद हो तो जुर्माना किताबें न खरीद सकिए तो जुर्माना कोई अपराध हो जाए तो जुर्माना शिक्षालय क्या है, जुर्मानालय है। यही हमारी पश्चिमी शिक्षा का आदर्श है, जिसकी तारीफों के पुल बांधे जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0663","text":"दबा हुआ पुरुषार्थ ही स्त्रीत्व है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0664","text":"त्यागी दो प्रकार के होते हैं। एक वह जो त्याग में आनंद मानते हैं, जिनकी आत्मा को त्याग में संतोष और पूर्णता का अनुभव होता है, जिनके त्याग में उदारता और सौजन्य है। दूसरे वह, जो दिलजले त्यागी होते हैं, जिनका त्याग अपनी परिस्थितियों से विद्रोह-मात्र है, जो अपने न्यायपथ पर चलने का तावान संसार से लेते हैं, जो खुद जलते हैं इसलिए दूसरों को भी जलाते हैं। अमर इसी तरह का त्यागी था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0665","text":"कायरता की भांति वीरता भी संक्रामक होती है। एक क्षण में उड़ते हुए पत्तों की तरह भागने वाले आदमियों की एक दीवार-सी खड़ी हो गई। अब डंडे पडें।, या गोलियों की वर्षा हो, उन्हें भय नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0666","text":"मां में केवल वात्सल्य है। बहन में क्या है, नहीं कह सकती, पर वह वात्सल्य से कोमल अवश्य है। मां अपराध का दंड भी देती है। बहन क्षमा का रूप है। भाई न्याय करे, अन्याय करे, डांटे या प्यार करे, मान करे, अपमान करे, बहन के पास क्षमा के सिवा और कुछ नहीं है। वह केवल उसके स्नेह की भूखी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Premchand — कर्मभूमि से उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0667","text":"गरीबी बहुआयामी है। यह हमारी कमाई के अलावा स्वास्थ, राजनीतिक भागीदारी, और हमारी संस्कृति और सामाजिक संगठन की उन्नति पर भी असर डालती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0668","text":"भारत में भारी जन भावना थी कि पाकिस्तान के साथ तब तक कोई सार्थक बातचीत नहीं हो सकती जब तक कि वो आतंकवाद का प्रयोग अपनी विदेशी नीति के एक साधन के रूप में करना नहीं छोड़ देता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0669","text":"मैं हिन्दू परम्परा में गर्व महसूस करता हूँ लेकिन मुझे भारतीय परम्परा में और ज्यादा गर्व है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0670","text":"मुझे अपने हिंदुत्व पर अभिमान है, किन्तु इसका अर्थ यह नहीं है कि मैं मुस्लिम-विरोधी हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0671","text":"आप दोस्तों को बदल सकते हैं लेकिन पड़ोसियों को नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0672","text":"जलना होगा, गलना होगा। कदम मिलकर चलना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0673","text":"अगर परमात्मा भी आ जाए और कहे कि छुआ-छूत मानो, तो मैं ऐसे परमात्मा को भी मानने को तैयार नहीं हूँ किन्तु परमात्मा ऐसा कह ही नहीं सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0674","text":"एटम बम का जवाब क्या है? एटम बम का जवाब एटम बम है और कोई जवाब नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0675","text":"मनुष्य-मनुष्य के संबंध अच्छे रहें, सांप्रदायिक सद्‌भाव रहे, मजहब का शोषण न किया जाए, जाति के आधार पर लोगों की हीन-भावना को उत्तेजित न किया जाए, इसमें कोई मतभेद नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0676","text":"कोई इस बात से इंकार नहीं कर सकता है कि देश मूल्यों के संकट में फंसा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0677","text":"मुझे शिक्षकों का मान-सम्मान करने में गर्व की अनुभूति होती है। अध्यापकों को शासन द्वारा प्रोत्साहन मिलना चाहिए। प्राचीनकाल में अध्यापक का बहत सम्मान था। आज तो अध्यापक पिस रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0678","text":"सूर्य एक सत्य है, जिसे झुठलाया नहीं जा सकता। मगर ओस भी तो एक सच्चाई है, यह बात अलग है कि क्षणिक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0679","text":"निराशा की अमावस की गहन दिशा के अंधकार में हम अपना मस्तक आत्म-गौरव के साथ तनिक ऊँचा उठाकर देखें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0680","text":"हमें उम्मीद है कि दुनिया प्रबुद्ध स्वार्थ की भावना से कार्य करेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0681","text":"गरीबी बहुआयामी है। यह पैसे की आय से परे शिक्षा, स्वास्थ्य की देखरेख, राजनीतिक भागीदारी और व्यक्ति की अपनी संस्कृति और सामाजिक संगठन की उन्नति तक फैली हुई है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0682","text":"एक विरोधी के द्वारा हमारे परमाणु हथियारों को विशुद्ध रूप से परमाणु अभियान के विरुद्ध धमकाने के रूप में बताता हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0683","text":"जो लोग हमें पूछते हैं कि हम पाकिस्तान के साथ वार्ता कब करेंगे शायद वे यह नहीं जानते हैं की पिछले 55 सालों में, पाकिस्तान के साथ बातचीत के लिए हर पहल निरपवाद रूप से भारत ने ही की है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0684","text":"वैश्विक स्तर पर आज परस्पर निर्भरता का मतलब विकाशशील देशों में आर्थिक आपदाओं का विकसित देशों पर प्रतिघात करना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0685","text":"हमें विश्वास है कि संयुक्त राज्य अमेरिका और बाकि अंतर्राष्ट्रीय समुदाय अपने प्रभाव का इस्तेमाल कर पाकिस्तान के भारत के विरुद्ध सीमा पार आतंकवाद को स्थाई और पारदर्शी रूप से खत्म करने में महत्वपूर्ण भूमिका अदा कर सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0686","text":"वास्तविकता यह है कि संयुक्त राष्ट्र जैसी अंतर्राष्ट्रीय संस्थाएं भी केवल उतनी ही प्रभावी हो सकती है जितनी उसके सदस्यों की अनुमति है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0687","text":"एक सार्वभौमिक धारणा से संयुक्त राष्ट्र की अनोखी वैधता बह रही है कि यह एक देह या देशों के एक छोटे से समूह के हितों की तुलना में एक बड़े उद्देश्य को पाने की कोशिश करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0688","text":"एक अंतर्निहित दृढ विश्वास था की संयुक्त राष्ट्र अपने घटक सदस्य देशों के योग से अधिक मजबूत होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0689","text":"ऐसे किसी देश को आतंकवाद के खिलाफ वैश्विक गठबंधन के साथ साझेदारी की अनुमति नहीं दी जनी चाहिए जबकि वो आतंकवाद को सहायता करने, उकसाने और प्रायोजित करने लगा हुआ हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0690","text":"सेवा कार्यों की उम्मीद सरकार से नहीं की जा सकती। उसके लिए समाजसेवी संस्थाओं को ही आगे उठना पड़ेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0691","text":"भारत के ऋषिओं-महर्षियों ने जिस एकात्मक जीवन के ताने बने को बुना था, आज वह उपहास का विषय बनाया जा रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0692","text":"पेड़ के ऊपर चढ़ा आदमी, ऊँचा दिखाई देता है। जड़ में खड़ा आदमी, नीचा दिखाई देता है। न आदमी ऊँचा होता है, न नीचा होता है, न बड़ा होता है, न छोटा होता है। आदमी सिर्फ आदमी होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0693","text":"किसी संत कवि ने कहा है कि मनुष्य के ऊपर कोई नहीं होता, मुझे लगता है कि मनुष्य के ऊपर उसका मन होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0694","text":"इंसान बनो, केवल नाम से नहीं, रूप से नहीं, शक्ल से नहीं, हृदय से, बुद्धि से, सरकार से, ज्ञान से।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0695","text":"छोटे मन से कोई बड़ा नहीं होता, टूटे मन से कोई खड़ा नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0696","text":"पड़ोसी कहते हैं कि एक हाथ से ताली नहीं बजती, हमने कहा कि चुटकी तो बज सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0697","text":"मन हारकर मैदान नहीं जीते जाते, न मैदान जीतने से मन ही जीते जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0698","text":"आदमी को चाहिए कि वह परिस्थितियों से लादे, एक स्वप्न टूटे तो दूसरा गढ़े।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0699","text":"मनुष्य का जीवन अनमोल निधि है। पुण्‍य का प्रसाद है। हम सिर्फ अपने लिए न जिएं, ओरों के लिए भी जिएं, औरों के लिए भी जिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0700","text":"जीवन जीना एक कला है। एक विज्ञान है दोनों का समन्‍वय आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0701","text":"आदमी की पहचान उसके धन या आसन से नहीं होती, उसके मन से होती है। मन की फकीरी पर कुबेर की संपदा भी रोती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0702","text":"कपड़ों की दुधिया सफेदी जैसे मन की मलिनता को नहीं छिपा सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0703","text":"जो जितना ऊंचा होता है, उतना ही एकाकी होता है। हर बार को खुद ही ढोता है, चेहरे पर मुस्कान चिपका, मन ही मन में रोता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0704","text":"ऐसी खुशियां जो हमेशा हमारा साथ दें, कभी नहीं थीं, अभी नहीं हैं और कभी नहीं रहेंगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0705","text":"पृथ्वी पर मनुष्य ही एक ऐसा प्राणी है, जो भीड़ में अकेला और अकेले में भीड़ से घिरे होने का अनुभव करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0706","text":"टूट सकते हैं मगर झुक नहीं सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0707","text":"पौरुष, पराक्रम वीरता हमारे रक्त के रंग में मिली है। यह हमारी महान परम्परा का अंग है। यह संस्कारों द्वारा हमारे जीवन में ढाली जाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0708","text":"देश एक मन्दिर है, हम पुजारी हैं, राष्ट्रदेव की पूजा में हमने अपने को समर्पित कर देना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0709","text":"हम अहिंसा में आस्था रखते हैं और चाहते हैं कि वैश्विक के संघर्षों का समाधान शांति और समझौते के मार्ग से हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0710","text":"मानव और मानव के बिच में जो भेद की दीवारें कड़ी हैं, उनको ढहाना होगा, और इसके लिए एक राष्ट्रिय अभियान की आवश्यकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0711","text":"यह संघर्ष जितने बलिदान की मांग करेगा, वे बलिदान दिए जाएंगे, जितने अनुशासन का तकाजा होगा, यह देश उतने अनुशासन का परिचय देगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0712","text":"वर्तमान शिक्षा पद्धति की विकृतियों से, उसके दोषों से, कमियों से सारा देश परिचित है। मगर नई शिक्षा नीति कहां है?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0713","text":"शहीदों का रक्त अभी गीला है और चिता की रख में चिंगारियां बाकी हैं। उजड़े हुए सुहाग और जंजीरों में जकड़ी हुई जवानियाँ उन उग्त्याचारों की गवाह हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0714","text":"इतिहास ने, भूगोल ने, परंपरा ने, संस्कृति ने, धर्म ने, नदियों ने हमें आपस में बांधा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0715","text":"मनुष्य-मनुष्य के बीच में भेदभाव का व्यवहार चल रहा है। इस समस्या का हल करे के लिए हमें एक राष्ट्रित अभियान की आवश्यकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0716","text":"राष्ट्र कुछ संप्रदायों अथवा जनसमूहों का सम्मुचय मात्र नहीं, अपितु एक जीवमान ईकाई है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0717","text":"अगर परमात्मा भी आ जाए और कहे कि छूआछूत मनो, तो मैं ऐसे परमात्मा को भी मानने को तैयार नहीं हूँ लेकिन परमात्मा ऐसा कह ही नहीं सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0718","text":"हम एक विश्व के आदर्शों की प्राप्ति और मानव के कल्याण तथा उसकी कीर्ति के लिए त्याग और बलिदान की बेला में कभी पीछे पग नहीं हटाएंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0719","text":"इतिहास में हुई भूल के लिए आक किसी से बदला लेने का समय नहीं है, लेकिन उस भूल को ठीक करने का सवाल है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0720","text":"कंधों से कंधा लगाकर, कदम से कदम मिलकर हमें अपनी जीवन यात्रा को ध्येय सिद्धि के शिखर तक ले जाना है। भावी भारत हमारे प्रयत्नों और परिश्रम पर निर्भर करता है। हम अपना कर्तव्य पालन करें, हमारी सफलता सुनिश्चित है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0721","text":"हरिजनों के कल्याण के साथ गिरिजनों तत्गा अन्य कबीलों की दशा सुधरने का प्रश्न भी जुड़ा हुआ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0722","text":"भारत कोई इतना छोटा देश नहीं है कि कोई उसको जेब में रख ले और वह उसका पिछलग्गू हो जाए। हम अपनी आजादी के लिए लड़े, दुनिया की आजादी के लिए लड़े।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0723","text":"अमावस के अभेद्य अंधकार का अंतःकरण पूर्णिमा की उज्ज्वलता का स्मरण कर थर्रा उठता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0724","text":"जीवन के फूल को पूर्ण ताकत से खिलाएं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0725","text":"इस देश में पुरुषार्थी नवजवानों की कमी नहीं है, लेकिन उनमे से कोई कार बनाने का कारखाना नहीं खोल सकता, क्योंकि किसी को प्रधानमंत्री के घर में जन्म लेने का सौभाग्य प्राप्त नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0726","text":"देश को हमसे बड़ी आशाएं हैं। हम परिस्थिति की चुनौती को स्वीकार करें। आँखों में एक महान भारत के सपने, ह्रदय में उस सपने को सत्य सृष्टि में परिणत करने के लिए प्रयत्नों की पराकाष्ठा करने का संकल्प, भुजाओं में समूची भारतीय जनता जो समेटकर उसे सीने से लगाए रखने का सात्विक बल और पैरों में युग परिवर्तन की गति लेकर हमें चलना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0727","text":"अगर भारत को बहु राष्ट्रीय राज्य के रूप में वर्णित करने की प्रवृति को समय रहते नियंत्रित नहीं किया गया तो भारत के अनेक टुकड़ों में बंट जाने का खतरा पैदा हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0728","text":"इस देश में कभी मजहब के आधार पर, मत भिन्नता के उगधर पर उत्पीडन की बात नहीं उठी, न उठेगी, न उठनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0729","text":"भारत के प्रति अनन्य निष्ठा रखने वाले सभी भारतीय एक हैं, फिर उनका मजहब, भाषा तथा प्रदेश कोई भी क्यों न हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0730","text":"कश्मीर से लेकर कन्याकुमारी तक फैला हुआ यह भारत एक राष्ट्र है, अनेक राष्ट्रीयताओं का समूह नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0731","text":"देश एक रहेगा तो किसी एक पार्टी की वजह से एक नहीं रहेगा, किसी एक व्यक्ति की वजह से एक नहीं रहेगा, किसी एक परिवार की वजह से एक नहीं रहेगा। देश एक रहेगा तो देश की जनता की देशभक्ति की वजह से रहेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0732","text":"भारतीयकरण का एक ही अर्थ है भारत में रहने वाले सभी व्यक्ति, चाहे उनकी भाषा कुछ भी हो, वह भारत के प्रति अनन्य, अविभाज्य, अव्यभिचारी निष्ठा रखें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0733","text":"मजहब बदलने से न राष्ट्रीयता बदलती है और न संस्कृति में परिवर्तन होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0734","text":"सभ्यता कलेवर है, संस्कृति उसका अन्तरंग। सभ्यता सूल होती है, संस्कृति सूक्ष्म। सभ्यता समय के साथ बदलती है, किंतु संस्कृति अधिक स्थायी होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0735","text":"मनुष्य जीवन अनमोल निधि है, पुण्य का प्रसाद है। हम केवल अपने लिए न जिएं, औरों के लिए भी जिएं। जीवन जीना एक कला है, एक विज्ञान है। दोनों का समन्वय आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0736","text":"मैं अपनी सीमाओं से परिचित हूं। मुझे अपनी कमियों का अहसास है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0737","text":"नर को नारायण का रूप देने वाले भारत ने दरिद्र और लक्ष्मीवान, दोनों में एक ही परम तत्त्व का दर्शन किया है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0738","text":"समता के साथ ममता, अधिकार के साथ उगत्मीयता, वैभव के साथ सादगी-नवनिर्माण के प्राचीन स्तंभ हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0739","text":"भगवान जो कुछ करता है, वह भलाई के लिए ही करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0740","text":"जीवन को टुकड़ों में नहीं बांटा जा सकता, उसका पूर्णता में ही विचार किया जाना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0741","text":"साहित्य और राजनीति के कोई अलस-अलग खाने नहीं होते। जो राजनीति में रुचि लेता है, वह साहित्य के लिए समय नहीं निकाल पाता और साहित्यकार राजनीति के लिए समय नहीं दे पाता, लेकिन कुछ ऐसे लोग हैं, जो दोनों के लिए समय देते हैं। वे अभिनन्दनीय हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0742","text":"साहित्यकार का हृदय दया, क्षमा, करुणा और प्रेम से आपूरित रहता है। इसलिए वह खून की होली नहीं खेल सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0743","text":"मेरे भाषणों में मेरा लेखक ही बोलता है, पर ऐसा नहीं कि राजनेता मौन रहता है। मेरे लेखक और राजनेता का परस्पर समन्वय ही मेरे भाषणों में उतरता है। यह जरूर है कि राजनेता ने लेखक से बहुत कुछ पाया है। साहित्यकार को अपने प्रति सच्चा होना चाहिए। उसे समाज के लिए अपने दायित्व का सही अर्थों में निर्वाह करना चाहिए। उसके तर्क प्रामाणिक हो। उसकी दृष्टि रचनात्मक होनी चाहिए। वह समसामयिकता को साथ लेकर चले, पर आने वाले कल की चिंता जरूर करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0744","text":"निराशा की अमावस की गहन निशा के अंधकार में हम अपना मस्तक आत्म-गौरव के साथ तनिक ऊंचा उठाकर देखें। विश्व के गगनमंडल पर हमारी कलित कीर्ति के असंख्य दीपक जल रहे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0745","text":"सदा से ही हमारी धार्मिक और दार्शनिक विचारधारा का केन्द्र बिंदु व्यक्ति रहा है। हमारे धर्मग्रंथों और महाकाव्यों में सदैव यह संदेश निहित रहा है कि समस्त ब्रह्मांड और सृष्टि का मूल व्यक्ति और उसका संपूर्ण विकास है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0746","text":"शिक्षा आज व्यापार बन गई है। ऐसी दशा में उसमें प्राणवत्ता कहां रहेगी? उपनिषदों या अन्य प्राचीन ग्रंथों की उगेर हमारा ध्यान नहीं जाता। आज विद्यालयों में छात्र थोक में आते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0747","text":"शिक्षा के द्वारा व्यक्ति के व्यक्तित्व का विकास होता है। व्यक्तित्व के उत्तम विकास के लिए शिक्षा का स्वरूप आदर्शों से युक्त होना चाहिए। हमारी माटी में आदर्शों की कमी नहीं है। शिक्षा द्वारा ही हम नवयुवकों में राष्ट्रप्रेम की भावना जाग्रत कर सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0748","text":"निरक्षरता और निर्धनता का बड़ा गहरा संबंध है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0749","text":"शिक्षा का माध्यम मातृभाषा होनी चाहिए। ऊंची-से-ऊंची शिक्षा मातृभाषा के माध्यम से दी जानी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0750","text":"मोटे तौर पर शिक्षा रोजगार या धंधे से जुड़ी होनी चाहिए। वह राष्ट्रीय चरित्र के निर्माण में सहायक हो और व्यक्ति को सुसंस्कारित करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0751","text":"हिन्दी की कितनी दयनीय स्थिति है, यह उस दिन भली-भांति पता लग गया, जब भारत-पाक समझौते की हिन्दी प्रति न तो संसद सदस्यों को और न हिन्दी पत्रकारों को उपलब्ध कराई गई।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0752","text":"हिन्दी वालों को चाहिए कि हिन्दी प्रदेशों में हिन्दी को पूरी तरह जीवन के सभी क्षेत्रों में प्रतिष्ठित करें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0753","text":"हिन्दी को अपनाने का फैसला केवल हिन्दी वालों ने ही नहीं किया। हिन्दी की आवाज पहले अहिन्दी प्रान्तों से उठी। स्वामी दयानन्दजी, महात्मा गांधी या बंगाल के नेता हिन्दीभाषी नहीं थे। हिन्दी हमारी आजादी के आनंदोलन का एक कार्यक्रम बनी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0754","text":"भारत की जितनी भी भाषाएं हैं, वे हमारी भाषाएं हैं, वे हमारी अपनी हैं, उनमें हमारी आत्मा का प्रतिबिम्ब है, वे हमारी आत्माभिव्यक्ति का साधन हैं। उनमें कोई छोटी-बड़ी नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0755","text":"राष्ट्र की सच्ची एकता तब पैदा होगी, जब भारतीय भाषाएं अपना स्थान ग्रहण करेंगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0756","text":"हिन्दी का किसी भारतीय भाषा से झगड़ा नहीं है। हिन्दी सभी भारतीय भाषाओं को विकसित देखना चाहती है, लेकिन यह निर्णय संविधान सभा का है कि हिन्दी केन्द्र की भाषा बने।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0757","text":"हमारा लोकतंत्र संसार का सबसे बड़ा लोकतंत्र है। लोकतंत्र की परंपरा हमारे यहां बड़ी प्राचीन है। चालीस साल से ऊपर का मेरा संसद का अनुभव कभी-कभी मुझे बहुत पीड़ित कर देता है। हम किधर जा रहे हैं?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0758","text":"भारत के लोग जिस संविधान को आत्म समर्पित कर चुके हैं, उसे विकृत करने का अधिकार किसी को नहीं दिया जा सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0759","text":"लोकतंत्र बड़ा नाजुक पौधा है। लोकतंत्र को धीरे- धीरे विकसित करना होगा। केन्द्र को सबको साथ लेकर चलने की भावना से आगे बढ़ना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0760","text":"अगर किसी को दल बदलना है तो उसे जनता की नजर के सामने दल बदलना चाहिए। उसमें जनता का सामना करने का साहस होना चाहिए। हमारे लोकतंत्र को तभी शक्ति मिलेगी जब हम दल बदलने वालों को जनता का सामना करने का साहस जुटाने की सलाह देंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0761","text":"लोकतंत्र वह व्यवस्था है, जिसमें बिना मृणा जगाए विरोध किया जा सकता है और बिना हिंसा का आश्रय लिए शासन बदला जा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0762","text":"जातिवाद का जहर समाज के हर वर्ग में पहुंच रहा है। यह स्थिति सबके लिए चिंताजनक है। हमें सामाजिक समता भी चाहिए और सामाजिक समरसता भी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0763","text":"कुर्सी की मुझे कोई कामना नहीं है। मुझे उन पर दया आती है जो विरोधी दल में बैठने का सम्मान छोड्‌कर कुर्सी की कामना से लालायित होकर सरकारी पार्टी का पन्तु पकड़ने के लिए लालायित हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0764","text":"भारत की सुरक्षा की अवधारणा सैनिक शक्ति नहीं है। भारत अनुभव करता है सुरक्षा आन्तरिक शक्ति से आती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0765","text":"बिना हमको सफाई का मौका दिए फांसी पर चढ़ाने की कोशिश मत करिए, क्योंकि हम मरते-मरते भी लड़ेंगे और लड़ते-लड़ते भी मरने को तैयार हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0766","text":"राजनीति काजल की कोठरी है। जो इसमें जाता है, काला होकर ही निकलता है। ऐसी राजनीतिक व्यवस्था में ईमानदार होकर भी सक्रिय रहना, बेदाग छवि बनाए रखना, क्या कठिन नहीं हो गया है?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0767","text":"मेरा कहना है कि सबके साथ दोस्ती करें लेकिन राष्ट्र की शक्ति पर विश्वास रखें। राष्ट्र का हित इसी में है कि हम आर्थिक दृष्टि से सबल हों, सैन्य दृष्टि से स्वावलम्बी हों।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0768","text":"पाकिस्तान कश्मीर, कश्मीरियों के लिए नहीं चाहता। वह कश्मीर चाहता है पाकिस्तान के लिए। वह कश्मीरियों को बलि का बकरा बनाना चाहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0769","text":"मैं पाकिस्तान से दोस्ती करने के खिलाफ नहीं हूं। सारा देश पाकिस्तान से संबंधों को सुधारना चाहता है, लेकिन जब तक कश्मीर पर पाकिस्तान का दावा कायम है, तब तक शांति नहीं हो सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0770","text":"पाकिस्तान हमें बार-बार उलझन में डाल रहा है, पर वह स्वयं उलझ जाता है। वह भारत के किरीट कश्मीर की ओर वक्र दृष्टि लगाए है। कश्मीर भारत का अंग है और रहेगा। हमें पाकिस्तान से साफ-साफ कह देना चाहिए कि वह कश्मीर को हथियाने का इरादा छोड़ दे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0771","text":"दरिद्रता का सर्वथा उन्मूलन कर हमें प्रत्येक व्यक्ति से उसकी क्षमता के अनुसार कार्य लेना चाहिए और उसकी आवश्यकता के अनुसार उसे देना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0772","text":"संयुक्त परिवार की प्रणाली सामाजिक सुरक्षा का सुंदर प्रबंध था, जिसने मार्क्स को भी मात कर दिया था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0773","text":"समता के साथ ममता, अधिकार के साथ आत्मीयता, वैभव के साथ सादगी-नवनिर्माण के प्राचीन आधारस्तम्भ हैं। इन्हीं स्तम्भों पर हमें भावी भारत का भवन खड़ा करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0774","text":"अगर भ्रष्टाचार का मतलब यह है कि छोटी-छोटी मछलियों को फांसा जाए और बड़े-बड़े मगरमच्छ जाल में से निकल जाएं तो जनता में विश्वास पैदा नहीं हो सकता। हम अगर देश में राजनीतिक और सामाजिक अनुशासन पैदा करना चाहते हैं तो उसके लिए भ्रष्टाचार का निराकरण आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0775","text":"अन्न उत्पादन के द्वारा आत्मनिर्भरता के बिना हम न तो औद्योगिक विकास का सुदृढ़ ढांचा ही तैयार कर सकते है और न विदेशों पर अपनी खतरनाक निर्भरता ही समाप्त कर सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0776","text":"कृषि-विकास का एक चिंताजनक पहलू यह है कि पैदावार बढ़ते ही दामों में गिरावट आने लगती है। हम एक विश्व के आदर्शों की प्राप्ति और मानव के कल्याण तथा उसकी कीर्ति के लिए त्याग और बलिदान की बेला में कभी पीछे पग नहीं हटाएंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0777","text":"मानव और मानव के बीच में जो भेद की दीवारें खड़ी हैं, उनको ढहाना होगा, और इसके लिए एक राष्ट्रीय अभियान की आवश्यकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0778","text":"अस्पृश्यता कानून के विरुद्ध ही नहीं, वह परमात्मा तथा मानवता के विरुद्ध भी एक गंभीर अपराध है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0779","text":"इतिहास ने, भूगोल ने, परम्परा ने, संस्कृति ने, धर्म ने, नदियों ने हमें आपस में बांधा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Atal Bihari Vajpayee — अटल बिहारी वाजपेयी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0780","text":"यदि बहरों को सुनना है तो आवाज तेज करनी होगी। जब हमने बम फेका था तब हमारा इरादा किसी को जान से मारने नहीं था। हमने ब्रिटिश सरकार पर बम फेका था। ब्रिटिश सरकार को भारत छोड़ना होगा और उसे स्वतंत्र करना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0781","text":"मजिस्ट्रेट साहब, आप भाग्यशाली हैं कि आज आप अपनी आखों से यह देखने का अवसर पा रहे हैं कि भारत के क्रांतिकारी किस प्रकार प्रसन्नतापूर्वक अपने सर्वोच्च आदर्श के लिए मृत्यु का आलिंगन कर सकते हैं। (मृत्यु पूर्व)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0782","text":"मेरा धर्म सिर्फ देश की सेवा करना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0783","text":"मुझे उस (जिसे लोग सर्वशक्तिमान भगवान् कहते हैं) में बिलकुल भी विश्वास नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0784","text":"निष्ठुर आलोचना और स्वतंत्र विचार ये क्रांतिकारी सोच के दो अहम् लक्षण हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0785","text":"पागल, प्रेमी और कवि, ये तीनो एक ही मिट्टी या सामग्री के बने होते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0786","text":"बड़े बड़े साम्राज्य तहस नहस हो जाते हैं, पर विचारों को कोई ध्वस्त नहीं कर सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0787","text":"बम और पिस्तौल क्रांति नहीं लाते हैं। क्रान्ति की तलवार विचारों के धार बढ़ाने वाले पत्थर पर रगड़ी जाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0788","text":"…व्यक्तियो को कुचल कर , वे विचारों को नहीं मार सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0789","text":"क्रांति केवल हिंसा और तोड़-फोड़ नहीं होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0790","text":"क्रांति मनुष्य का जन्म सिद्ध आधिकार है साथ ही आजादी भी जन्म सिद्ध अधिकार है और परिश्रम समाज का वास्तव में वहन करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0791","text":"क्रांति मानव जाती का एक अपरिहार्य अधिकार है। स्वतंत्रता सभी का एक कभी न ख़त्म होने वाला जन्म-सिद्ध अधिकार है। श्रम समाज का वास्तविक निर्वाहक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0792","text":"क्रांति में सदैव संघर्ष हो यह जरुरी नहीं। यह बम और पिस्तौल की राह नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0793","text":"अगर अपने दुश्मन से बहस करनी है और उससे जीतना है तो इसके लिए अभ्यास करना जरूरी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0794","text":"अगर आपको मेरे (भगत सिंह के अनमोल वचन) प्रेरित करते हैं तो बदलाव लाने की हिम्मत करते समय बिलकुल मत सोचिये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0795","text":"अगर कोई आपके विकास की राह के बीच रोड़ा बने तो आपको उसकी आलोचना करनी चाहिए और इसे चुनौती देनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0796","text":"अगर बहरों को सुनना है तो आवाज को बहुत जोरदार होना होगा, जब हमने असेम्बली में बम गिराया तो हमारा मकसद किसी को मारना नहीं था हमने अंग्रेजी हुकूमत पर बम गिराया था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0797","text":"अगर हमें सरकार बनाने का मौका मिलेगा तो किसी के पास प्राइवेट प्रॉपर्टी नहीं मिलेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0798","text":"प्रेमी, पागल और कवि एक ही चीज से बने होते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0799","text":"अपने दुश्मन से बहस करने के लिये उसका अभ्यास करना बहोत जरुरी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0800","text":"अहिंसा को आत्म विश्वास का बल प्राप्त है जिसमे जीत की आशा से कष्ट वहन किया जाता है। लेकिन अगर यह प्रयत्न विफल हो जाए तब क्या होगा? तब हमें इस आत्म शक्ति को शारीरिक शक्ति से जोड़ना होता है ताकि हम अत्याचारी दुश्मन की दया पर न रहे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0801","text":"आज जो मै आगाज लिख रहा हूँ, उसका अंजाम कल आएगा। मेरे खून का एक एक कतरा कभी तो इन्कलाब लाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0802","text":"आज मेरी कमजोरियां लोगों के सामने नहीं हैं। अगर मैं फांसी से बच गया तो वे जाहिर हो जाएंगी और इंकलाब का निशान मद्धिम पड़ जाएगा या शायद मिट ही जाए, लेकिन मेरे दिलेराना ढंग से हंसते-हंसते फांसी पाने की सूरत में हिन्दुस्तानी माताएं अपने बच्चों के भगत सिंह बनने की आरजू किया करेंगी और देश की आजादी के लिए बलिदान होने वालों की तादाद इतनी बढ़ जाएगी कि इंकलाब को रोकना इम्पीरियलिज्म की तमाम सर (संपूर्ण) शैतानी कुबतों के बस की बात न रहेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0803","text":"आम तौर पर लोग जैसी चीजें हैं उसके आदी हो जाते हैं और बदलाव के विचार से ही कांपने लगते हैं। हमें इसी निष्क्रियता की भावना को क्रांतिकारी भावना से बदलने की जरूरत है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0804","text":"इंसान तभी कुछ करता है जब वो अपने काम के औचित्य को लेकर सुनिश्चित होता है , जैसाकि हम विधान सभा में बम फेंकने को लेकर थे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0805","text":"इंसान तभी कुछ करता है जब वो अपने काम के औचित्य को लेकर सुनिश्चित होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0806","text":"क़ानून की पवित्रता तभी तक बनी रह सकती है जब तक की वो लोगों की इच्छा की अभिव्यक्ति करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0807","text":"कानून में विश्वास और उसकी पवित्रता तब तक ही बनी रह सकती है जब तक वो लोगों को सही न्याय दिलाता रहे और उनकी इच्छाओं की अभिव्यक्ति करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0808","text":"किसी को ‘क्रांति’ शब्द की व्याख्या शाब्दिक अर्थ में नहीं करनी चाहिए। जो लोग इस शब्द का उपयोग या दुरूपयोग करते हैं उनके फायदे के हिसाब से इसे अलग अलग अर्थ और अभिप्राय दिए जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0809","text":"किसी ने सच ही कहा है, सुधार बूढ़े आदमी नहीं कर सकते। ते तो बहुत ही बुद्धिमान और समझदार होते हैं। सुधार तो होते हैं युवकों के परिश्रम, साहस, बलिदान और निष्ठा से, जिनको भयभीत होना आता ही नहीं और जो विचार कम और अनुभव अधिक करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0810","text":"किसी भी इंसान को मारना आसान है, परन्तु उसके विचारों को नहीं। महान साम्राज्य टूट जाते हैं, तबाह हो जाते हैं, जबकि उनके विचार बच जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0811","text":"किसी भी कीमत पर बल का प्रयोग ना करना काल्पनिक आदर्श है और नया आन्दोलन जो देश में शुरू हुआ है और जिसके आरम्भ की हम चेतावनी दे चुके हैं वो गुरु गोबिंद सिंह और शिवाजी, कमाल पाशा और राजा खान , वाशिंगटन और गैरीबाल्डी , लाफायेतटे और लेनिन के आदर्शों से प्रेरित है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0812","text":"कोई भी व्यक्ति कोई ख़ास कार्य तभी करता है जब वो उसके औचित्य को सुनिश्चित कर लेता है। जिस तरह से हमने विधान सभा में बम फेंका था, वो भी एक ऐसा ही कार्य था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0813","text":"कोई भी व्यक्ति जो जीवन में आगे बढ़ने के लिए तैयार खड़ा हो उसे हर एक रूढ़िवादी चीज की आलोचना करनी होगी, उसमे अविश्वास करना होगा और चुनौती भी देना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0814","text":"कोई भी व्यक्ति तब ही कुछ करता है जब वह अपने कार्य के परिणाम (औचित्य) को लेकर आश्व्स्त होता है जैसे हम असेम्बली में बम फेकने पर थे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0815","text":"कोई विद्रोह क्रांति नहीं होता, आखिर में आपका अंत हो सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0816","text":"क्या तुम्हें पता है कि दूनिया में सबसे बड़ा पाप गरीब होना है? गरीबी एक अभिशाप है यह एक सजा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0817","text":"क्रांति लाना किसी भी इंसान की ताकत के बाहर की बात है। क्रांति कभी भी अपनेआप नही आती। बल्कि किसी विशिष्ट वातावरण, सामाजिक और आर्थिक परिस्थितियों में ही क्रांति लाई जा सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0818","text":"क्रांति से हमारा अभिप्राय समाज की वर्तमान प्रणाली और वर्तमान संगठन को पूरी तरह उखाड़ फेंकना है। इस उद्‌देश्य के लिए हम पहले सरकार की ताकत को अपने हाथ में लेना चाहते हैं। इस समय शासन की मशीन धनिकों के हाथ में है। सामान्य जनता के हितों की रक्षा के लिए तथा उरपने आदर्शों को क्रियात्मक रूप देने के लिए अर्थात समाज का नए सिरे से संगठन कार्ल मार्क्स के सिद्धांतों के अनुसार करने के लिए हम सरकार की मशीन को उरपने हाथ में लेना चाहते हैं। हम इसी उद्‌देश्य के लिए लड़ रहे है, पंरतु इसके लिए हमें साधारण जनता को शिक्षित करना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0819","text":"क्रांतिकारी सोच के दो आवश्यक लक्षण है – बेरहम निंदा तथा स्वतंत्र सोच।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0820","text":"क्रान्ति के लिए हथियारों की जरुरत नहीं होती, क्रान्ति की तलवारें तो विचारों की धार पर तेज की जाती हैं। अगर आपको भगत सिंह के अनमोल विचार प्रेरित करते हैं तो अत्याचार के खिलाफ लड़िये, क्रांतिकारी बनिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0821","text":"क्रान्ति लाना हमारे बस की नहीं, क्रान्ति तो विशेष परिस्थतियों में अपने आप ही आती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0822","text":"चीजें जैसी है आम तौर पर लोग उसके आदि हो जाते है और बदलाव के विचार से ही कांपने लगते है हमें इसी निष्क्रियता को क्रांतिकारी भावना से बदलने कि जरुरत है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0823","text":"जरूरी नहीं था कि क्रांति में अभिशप्त संघर्ष शामिल हो। यह बम और पिस्तौल का पंथ नहीं था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0824","text":"मुझे अपने देश से बहुत प्रेम है, इसलिए मैं देश की भलाई के लिए कटिबद्ध हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0825","text":"जहां तक हमारे भाग्य का संबंध है, हम बड़े बलपूर्वक आपसे यह कहना चाहते हैं कि अपने हमें फांसी पर लटकाने का निर्णय कर लिया है, आप ऐसा करेंगे ही, आपके हाथों में शक्ति है और आपको अधिकार भी प्राप्त हैं, परंतु इस प्रकार आप ‘जिसकी लाठी उसकी भैंस वाला’ सिद्धांत ही अपना रहे हैं और आप उस पर कटिबद्ध है। हमारे अभियोग की सुनवाई इस वक्तव्य को सिद्ध करने के लिए पर्याप्त है कि हमने कभी कोई प्रार्थना नहीं की और अब भी हम आपसे किसी प्रकार की दया की प्रार्थना नहीं करते। हम केवल आपसे यह प्रार्थना करना चाहते हैं कि आपकी सरकार के ही एक न्यायालय के निर्णय के अनुसार हमारे विरुद्ध युद्ध जारी रखने का अभियोग है, इस स्थिति में हम युद्ध-बंदी हैं, अत: इस आधार पर हम आपसे मांग करते हैं कि हमारे साथ युद्ध-बंदियों जैसा ही बर्ताव किया जाए और हमें फांसी देने के बदले गोली से उड़ा दिया जाए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0826","text":"जिंदगी तो सिर्फ अपने कंधों पर जी जाती है, दूसरों के कंधे पर तो सिर्फ जनाजे उठाए जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0827","text":"जिंदा रहने की ख्वाहिश कुदरती तौर पर मुझमें भी होनी चाहिए। मैं इसे छिपाना नहीं चाहता, लेकिन मेरा जिंदा रहना एक शर्त पर है। मैं कैद होकर या पाबंद होकर जिंदा रहना नहीं चाहता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0828","text":"जिन्दा रहने की हसरत मेरी भी है, पर मै कैद रहकर अपना जीवन नहीं बिताना चाहता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0829","text":"जीवन अपने दम पर चलता है.... दूसरों के कन्धों पर तो अंतिम यात्रा पूरी होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0830","text":"जैसे पुराना कपड़ा उतारकर नया बदला जाता है, वैसे ही मृत्यु है। मैं उससे डरूंगा नहीं, भागूंगा नहीं। कोशिश करूंगा कि पकड़ा जाऊं पर यूं ही नहीं कि पुलिस आई और पकड़ ले गई। मेरे पास एक तरीका है कि कैसे पकड़ा जाऊं। मौत आएगी, आएगी ही पर मैं अपनी मौत को इतनी महंगी और भारी बना दूंगा कि ब्रिटिश सरकार रेत के ढेर की तरह उसके बोझ से ढक जाए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0831","text":"जो व्यक्ति विकास के लिए खड़ा है उसे हर एक रूढ़िवादी चीज की आलोचना करनी होगी, उसमें अविश्वास करना होगा तथा उसे चुनौती देनी होगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0832","text":"दिल से निकलेगी न मरकर भी वतन की उल्फत, मेरी मिट्ठी से भी खूशबू-ए-वतन आएगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0833","text":"देशभक्तों को अक्सर लोग पागल कहते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0834","text":"बाबाजी, मैंने जीवन में कभी वाहे गुरु को याद नहीं किया। कई बार तो मैंने देश की अवनति और लोगों के दुख के लिए उन्हें दोषी ठहराया है। अब जब मौत मेरे सामने खड़ी है वाहे गुरु की अरदास करूं तो वह कहेगा कि मैं बहुत डरपोक और बेइमान आदमी हूं। अब मुझे इस संसार से वैसे ही विदा होना जाने दो जैसा मैं हूं। मेरी क्रांति यह नहीं रहेगी कि भगत सिंह कायर था और उसने अपनी मौत से घबराकर वाहे गुरु को याद किया था।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0835","text":"बुराई बढ़ने का कारण बढ़ते हुए बुरे लोग नहीं हैं, बल्कि इसके लिए वो लोग जिम्मेदार हैं जो चुपचाप बुराई को सहन करते जा रहे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0836","text":"भारत की वर्तमान लड़ाई ज्यादातर मध्य श्रेणी के लोगों के बलबूते पर लड़ी जा रही है, जिसका लक्ष्य बहुत सीमित है। कांग्रेस दुकानदारों और पूंजीपतियों के जरिए इंग्लैंड पर आर्थिक दबाव डालकर कुछ अधिकार ले लेना चाहती है, परंतु जहां तक देश के करोड़ों मजदूरों और किसान जनता का ताल्लुक है, उनका उद्धार इतने से नहीं हो सकता। यदि देश की लड़ाई लड़नी हो, तो मजदूरों, किसानों और सामान्य जनता को आगे लाना होगा, इन्हें लड़ाई के लिए संगठित करना होगा। नेता उन्हें अभी तक आगे लाने के लिए कुछ नहीं करते, न कर ही सकते है। इन किसानों को विदेशी हुकूमत के जुए के साथ-साथ भूमिपतियों और पूंजीपतियों के जुए से भी उद्धार पाना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0837","text":"मनुष्य तभी कुछ करता है जब उसे अपने कार्य का उचित होना सुनिश्चित होता है, जैसा की हम विधान सभा में बम गिराते समय थे। जो मनुष्य इस शब्द का उपयोग या दुरुपयोग करते हैं उनके लाभ के हिसाब के अनुसार इसे अलग-अलग अर्थ और व्याख्या दिए जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0838","text":"मरकर भी मेरे दिल से वतन की उल्फत नहीं निकलेगी, मेरी मिट्टी से भी वतन की ही खुशबू आएगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0839","text":"महान साम्राज्य ध्वंस हो जाते हैं पर विचार जिंदा रहते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0840","text":"मुझे दंड सुना दिया गया है और फांसी का आदेश हुआ है। इन कोठरियों में मेरे अतिरिक्त फांसी की प्रतीक्षा करने वाले बहुत -से अपराधी हैं। ये यही प्रार्थना कर रहे हैं कि किसी तरह फांसी से बच जाएं, परंतु उनके बीच शायद मैं ही एक ऐसा आदमी हूं जो बड़ी बेताबी से उस दिन की प्रतीक्षा कर रहा हूं जब मुझे अपने आदर्श के लिए फांसी के फंदे पर धूलने का सौभाग्य प्राप्त होगा। मैं खुशी के साथ फांसी के तख्ते पर चढ़कर दुनिया को दिखा दूंगा कि क्रांतिकारी अपने आदर्शों के लिए कितनी वीरता से बलिदान दे सकते हैं। - भगत सिंह( बटुकेश्वर दत्त को लिखे गए पत्र का हिस्सा )","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0841","text":"मुझे फांसी का दंड मिला है, किंतु तुम्हें आजीवन कारावास दंड मिला है। तुम जीवित रहोगे और तुम्हें जीवित रहकर दुनिया को यह दिखाना है कि क्रांतिकारी अपने आदर्शों के लिए मर ही नहीं सकते, बल्कि जीवित रहकर हर मुसीबत का मुकाबला भी कर सकते हैं। मृत्यु सांसारिक कठिनाइयों से मुक्ति प्राप्त करने का साधन नहीं बननी चाहिए, बल्कि जो क्रांतिकारी संयोगवश फांसी के फंदे से बच गए हैं उन्हें जीवित रहकर दुनिया को यह दिखा देना चाहिए कि वे न केवल अपने आदर्शों के लिए फांसी पर चढ़ सकते हैं, जेलों की अंधकारपूर्ण छोटी कोठरियों में पुल-घुलकर निकृष्टतम दरजे के अत्याचार को सहन भी कर सकते हैं। - भगत सिंह ( बटुकेश्वर दत्त को लिखे गए पत्र का हिस्सा )","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0842","text":"मुसीबतें इंसान को पूर्ण बनाने का काम करती हैं, हर स्थिति में धैर्य बनाकर रखें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0843","text":"मेरा जीवन एक महान लक्ष्य के प्रति समर्पित है – देश की आज़ादी। दुनिया की अन्य कोई आकषिर्त वस्तु मुझे लुभा नहीं सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0844","text":"मेरा नाम हिन्दुस्तानी इंकलाब पार्टी का निशान बन चुका है और इंकलाब पसंद पार्टी के आदर्शों और बलिदानों ने मुझे बहुत ऊंचा कर दिया है। इतना ऊंचा कि जिंदा रहने की सूरत में इससे ऊंचा मैं हरगिज नहीं हो सकता। इसके सिवा कोई लालच मेरे दिल में फांसी से बचे रहने के लिए कभी नहीं आया, मुझसे ज्यादा खुशकिस्मत कौन होगा। मुझे आज तक अपने आप पर बहुत नाज है। मुझमें अब कोई ख्वाहिश बाकी नहीं है। अब तो बड़ी बेताबी से आखिरी इम्तहां का इंतजार है। आरजू है कि यह और करीब हो जाए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0845","text":"मेरी कलम मेरे जज्बातों को इस कदर समझती है की मै \"इश्क\" लिखने की कोशिश करूँ तो भी इन्कलाब ही लिखा जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0846","text":"मेरी गर्मी के कारण राख का एक एक कण चलायमान हैं में ऐसा पागल हूँ जो जेल में भी स्वतंत्र हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0847","text":"मेरे जीवन का केवल एक ही लक्ष्य है और वो है देश की आज़ादी। इसके अलावा कोई और लक्ष्य मुझे लुभा नहीं सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0848","text":"मेरे सीने पर जो जख्म हैं, वो सब फूलों के गुच्छे हैं, हमको पागल रहने दो, हम पागल ही अच्छे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0849","text":"मैं इस बात पर जोर देता हूँ कि मैं महत्त्वाकांक्षा , आशा और जीवन के प्रति आकर्षण से भरा हुआ हूँ। पर मैं ज़रुरत पड़ने पर ये सब त्याग सकता हूँ, और वही सच्चा बलिदान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0850","text":"मै एक इंसान हूँ और मानवता को प्रभावित करने वाली हर चीज़ से मतलब रखता हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0851","text":"मै खुद भी जीना चाहता हूँ और मेरी भी इच्छाएं हैं, पर देश के लिए इन सब का त्याग करने को हमेशा तैयार हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0852","text":"मैं यह मानता हूँ की मह्त्वकांक्षी, आशावादी एवम जीवन के प्रति उत्साही हूँ लेकिन आवश्यकता अनुसार मैं इस सबका परित्याग कर सकता हूँ सही सच्चा त्याग होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0853","text":"यदि आप सोलह उगने के लिए लड़ रहे हैं और एक आना मिल जाता है, तो वह एक आना जेब में डालकर बाकी पंद्रह उगने के लिए फिर जंग छेड़ दीजिए। हिन्दुस्तान के माडरेटों की जिस बात से हमें नफरत है, वह यही है कि उनका आदर्श कुछ नहीं है। वे एक आने के लिए ही लड़ते हैं और उन्हें मिलता कुछ भी नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0854","text":"यदि हमारे नौजवान इसी प्रकार प्रयत्न करते जाएंगे, तब जाकर एक साल में स्वराज्य तो नहीं, किंतु भारी कुर्बानी और त्याग की कठिन परीक्षा में से गुजरने के बाद वे अवश्य विजयी होंगे। क्रांति चिरंजीवी हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0855","text":"यह बात प्रसिद्ध है कि मैं एक आतंककारी (टेररिस्ट) रहा हूं परंतु मैं आतंककारी नहीं हूं। मैं एक क्रांतिकारी हूं जिसके कुछ निश्चित विचार और निश्चित आदर्श हैं और जिसके सामने एक लंबा प्रोग्राम है। मुझे यह दोष दिया जाएगा, जैसा कि लोग रामप्रसाद बिस्मिल को भी देते थे कि फांसी की काल कोठारी में पड़े रहने से मेरे विचारों में भी कोई परिवर्तन उग गया है, परंतु ऐसी बात नहीं। मेरे विचार अब भी वही हैं, मेरे हृदय में अब भी उतना ही और वैसा ही उत्साह और वही लक्ष्य है जो जेल से बाहर था, पर मेरा यह दृढ़-विश्वास है कि हम बम से कोई लाभ प्राप्त नहीं कर सकते। यह बात हिन्दुस्तान सोशलिस्ट रिपब्लिकन आर्मी के इतिहास से भी आसानी से मालूम पड़ती है। बम फेंकना न सिर्फ व्यर्थ है, अपितु बहुत बार हानिकारक भी है। उसकी आवश्यकता किन्हीं विशेष परिस्थितियों में ही पड़ती है, हमारा मुख्य लक्ष्य मजदूर और किसानों का संगठन होना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0856","text":"राख का हर कण मेरी गर्मी से गतिमान है, मैं एक ऐसा पागल हूँ जो जेल में भी आजाद है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0857","text":"लिख रह हूँ मैं अंजाम जिसका कल आगाज़ आएगा… मेरे लहू का हर एक कतरा इंकलाब लाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0858","text":"लोग जैसा चल रहा है उसे ही अपनाने को तैयार हैं। बदलाव लाने की सोच मात्र से ही उनके हाथ पैर कांपने लगते हैं। हमें अपनी इसी भावना को बदलना है और क्रांतिकारी बनना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0859","text":"व्यक्तियों को कुचल कर, वे विचारों को नही मार सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0860","text":"सच कहूं तो खुद को बचाने के बारे में मैंने कभी सोचा ही नहीं, मेरे दिमाग में हमेशा एक ही चीज़ रहती है और वो है इन्कलाब।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0861","text":"समझौता कोई ऐसी हेय और निंदा योग्य वस्तु नहीं, जैसा कि साधारणत: हम लोग समझते है, बल्कि समझौता राजनीतिक संग्रामों का एक अत्यावश्यक अंग है। कोई भी कौम जो किसी अत्याचारी शासन के विरुद्ध खड़ी होती है, यह जरूरी है कि वह आरंभ में असफल हो और अपनी लंबी जद्‌दोजहद के मध्यकाल में इस प्रकार के समझौते के जरिए कुछ राजनीतिक सुधार हासिल करती जाए, परंतु पहुंचते-पहुंचते अपनी ताकतों को इतना संगठित और दृढ़ कर लेती है और उसका दुश्मन पर आखिरी हमला इतना जोरदार होता है कि शासक लोगों की ताकतें उस वक्त तक यह चाहती हैं कि उसे दुश्मन के साथ कोई समझौता कर लेना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0862","text":"समझौता भी ऐसा हथियार है, जिसे राजनीतिक जद्‌दोजहद के बीच में पग-पग पर इस्तेमाल करना आवश्यक हो जाता है जिससे एक कठिन लड़ाई से थकी हुई कौम को थोड़ी देर के लिए आराम मिल सके और वह आगे के युद्ध के लिए अधिक ताकत के साथ तैयार हो सके, परंतु इन सारे समझौतों के बावजूद जिस चीज को हमें भूलना न चाहिए वह हमारा आदर्श है जो हमेशा हमारे सामने रहना चाहिए। जिस लक्ष्य के लिए हम लड़ रहे हैं उनके संबंध में हमारे विचार बिल्कुल स्पष्ट और दृढ़ होने चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0863","text":"सर्वगत भाईचारा तभी हासिल हो सकता है जब समानताएं हों – सामाजिक, राजनैतिक एवं व्यक्तिगत समानताएं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0864","text":"सामान्यत: लोग परिस्थिति के आदि हो जाते है और उनमें बदलाव करने की सोच मात्र से डर जाते है। अत: हमें इस भावना को क्रांति की भावना से बदलने की जरूरत है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0865","text":"सिने पर जो ज़ख्म है, सब फूलों के गुच्छे हैं, हमें पागल ही रहने दो, हम पागल ही अच्छे हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0866","text":"सूर्य विश्व में हर किसी देश पर उज्ज्वल हो कर गुजरता है परन्तु उस समय ऐसा कोई देश नहीं होगा जो भारत देश के सामान इतना स्वतंत्र, इतना खुशहाल, इतना प्यारा हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0867","text":"स्वतंत्रता हर व्यक्ति का जन्मसिद्ध अधिकार है और अगर कोई इसके बीच रोड़ा बने तो आदमी को क्रांतिकारी बनने का भी अधिकार है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0868","text":"हम नौजवानों को बम और पिस्तौल उठाने की सलाह नहीं दे सकते। विद्यार्थियों के लिए और भी महत्त्वपूर्ण काम हैं। राष्ट्रीय इतिहास के नाजुक समय में नौजवानों पर बहुत बड़े दायित्व का भार है और सबसे ज्यादा विद्यार्थी ही तो आजादी की लड़ाई में अगली पांतों में लड़ते हुए शहीद हुए है। क्या भारतीय नौजवान इस परीक्षा के समय में वही संजीदा इरादा दिखाने में झिझक दिखाएंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0869","text":"हम यह कहना चाहते हैं कि युद्ध छिड़ा हुआ है और यह लड़ाई तब तक चलती रहेगी, जब तक कि शक्तिशाली व्यक्तियों ने भारतीय जनता और श्रमिकों की आय के साधनों पर अपना एकाधिकार कर रखा है। चाहे ऐसे व्यक्ति अंग्रेज पूंजीपति हों या अंग्रेजी शासक या सर्वथा भारतीय ही हों, उन्होंने आपस में मिलकर एक लूट जारी रखी हुई है। चाहे शुद्ध भारतीय पूंजी-पतियों के द्वारा ही निर्धनों का खून चूसा जा रहा हो, तो भी इस स्थिति में कोई अंतर नहीं पड़ता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0870","text":"हमारा लक्ष्य शासन शक्ति को उन हाथों के सुपुर्द करना है, जिनका लक्ष्य समाजवाद हो, इसके लिए मजदूरों और किसानों को संगठित करना आवश्यक होगा, क्योंकि उन लोगों के लिए लॉर्ड रीडिंग या इर्विन की जगह तेजबहादुर या पुरुषोत्तम दास, ठाकुर दास के उग जाने से कोई भारी फर्क न पड़ सकेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0871","text":"हमारे दल को नेताओं की आवश्यकता नहीं है। अगर आप दुनियादार हैं, बाल-बच्चों और गृहस्थी में फंसे है, तो हमारे मार्ग पर मत आइए। ‘आप हमारे उद्‌देश्य में सहानुभूति रखते हैं तो और तरीकों से हमें सहायता दीजिए। नियंत्रण में रह सकने वाले कार्यकर्ता ही इस आदोलन को आगे ले जा सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0872","text":"हमें धैर्यपूर्वक फांसी की प्रतीक्षा करनी चाहिए। यह मृत्यु सुंदर होगी, परंतु आत्महत्या करना, केवल कुछ दुखों से बचने के लिए अपने जीवन को समाप्त कर देना तो कायरता है। मैं आपको बताना चाहता हूं कि आपत्तियां व्यक्ति को पूर्ण बनाने वाली हैं। (सुखदेव को लिखे एक पत्र से)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0873","text":"मैं नास्तिक हूँ क्योंकि मैंने ईश्वर को गरीबों का दु:ख मिटाते नहीं देखा (स्रोत: क्यों मैं नास्तिक हूँ, भगत सिंह, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0874","text":"कानून अंधा होता है, लेकिन हम आँखों वाले हैं — हमें उसे बदलना होगा (स्रोत: अदालत में वक्तव्य, भगत सिंह, 1929)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0875","text":"यदि बहरों को सुनाना है, तो आवाज़ बहुत ज़ोर की होनी चाहिए (स्रोत: असेम्बली बम प्रकरण, भगत सिंह, 1929)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0876","text":"देशभक्ति का अर्थ सरकार की अंधी भक्ति नहीं, बल्कि सच्चाई के पक्ष में खड़ा होना है (स्रोत: जेल डायरी, भगत सिंह, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0877","text":"किसी भी बलिदान की सार्थकता तभी है जब वह जन-कल्याण की ओर ले जाए (स्रोत: जेल पत्र, भगत सिंह, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0878","text":"प्रेम और बलिदान की भावना से बढ़कर कोई शक्ति नहीं हो सकती (स्रोत: जेल डायरी, भगत सिंह, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0879","text":"यदि आप अन्याय का विरोध नहीं करते, तो आप अन्याय के पक्ष में खड़े हैं (स्रोत: पत्र भाई किशोरीलाल को, भगत सिंह, 1929)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0880","text":"असली आज़ादी तब है जब समाज से हर प्रकार का शोषण समाप्त हो जाए (स्रोत: समाजवाद पर लेख, भगत सिंह, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Bhagat Singh — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0881","text":"इस मिट्टी में कुछ अनूठा है, जो कई बाधाओं के बावजूद हमेशा महान आत्माओं का निवास रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0882","text":"आपकी अच्छाई आपके मार्ग में बाधक है, इसलिए अपनी आँखों को क्रोध से लाल होने दीजिये, और अन्याय का मजबूत हाथों से सामना कीजिये।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0883","text":"एकता के बिना जनशक्ति शक्ति नहीं है जबतक उसे ठीक तरह से सामंजस्य में ना लाया जाए और एकजुट ना किया जाए, और तब यह आध्यात्मिक शक्ति बन जाती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0884","text":"बेशक कर्म पूजा है किन्तु हास्य जीवन है।जो कोई भी अपना जीवन बहुत गंभीरता से लेता है उसे एक तुच्छ जीवन के लिए तैयार रहना चाहिए। जो कोई भी सुख और दुःख का समान रूप से स्वागत करता है वास्तव में वही सबसे अच्छी तरह से जीता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0885","text":"चर्चिल से कहो कि भारत को बचाने से पहले इंग्लैण्ड को बचाए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0886","text":"शक्ति के अभाव में विश्वास किसी काम का नहीं है। विश्वास और शक्ति, दोनों किसी महान काम को करने के लिए अनिवार्य हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0887","text":"सत्ताधीशों की सत्ता उनकी मृत्यु के साथ ही समाप्त हो जाती है, पर महान देशभक्तों की सत्ता मरने के बाद काम करती है, अतः देशभक्ति अर्थात् देश-सेवा में जो मिठास है, वह और किसी चीज में नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0888","text":"सैनिक लड़ने के लिए तो तैयार हो, किन्तु सेनापति द्वारा बताए गये शस्त्रास्त्र न रखे, तो वह युद्ध नहीं जीत सकता, क्योंकि उसमें अनुशासन नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0889","text":"जिसने भगवान को पहचान लिया, उसके लिए तो संसार में कोई अस्पृश्य नहीं है, उसके मन में ऊँच-नीच का भेद कहाँ ! अस्पृश्य तो वह प्राणी है जिसके प्राण निकल गए हों अर्थात वह शव बन गया हो। अस्पृश्यता एक वहम है। जब कुत्ते को छूकर, बिल्ली को छूकर नहाना नहीं पड़ता तो अपने समान मनुष्य को छूकर हम अपवित्र कैसे हुए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0890","text":"जो तलवार चलाना जानते हुए भी तलवार को म्यान में रखता है, उसी की अहिंसा सच्ची अहिंसा कही जाएगी। कायरों की अहिंसा का मूल्य ही क्या। और जब तक अहिंसा को स्वीकार नहीं जाता, तब तक शांति कहाँ!","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0891","text":"आत्मा को गोली या लाठी नहीं मार सकती। दिल के भीतर की असली चीज इस आत्मा को कोई हथियार नहीं छू सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0892","text":"कर्तव्यनिष्ठ व्यक्ति सदैव आशावान रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0893","text":"पड़ोसी का महल देखकर अपनी झोपडी तोड़ डालनेवाला महल तो बना नहीं सकता, अपनी झोपडी भी खो बैठता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0894","text":"ईश्वर का नाम ही (रामवाण) दवा है। दूसरी सब दवाएं बेकार हैं। वह जब तक हमें एस संसार में रखे, तब तक हम अपना कर्तव्य करते रहें। जानेवाले का शोक न करें, क्योंकि जीवन की डोर तो उसी के हाथ में है। फिर चिंता की क्या बात। याद रहे कि सबसे दुखी मनुष्य में भगवान का वास होता है। वह महलों में नहीं रहता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0895","text":"जब जनता एक हो जाती है, तब उसके सामने क्रूर से क्रूर शासन भी नहीं टिक सकता। अतः जात-पांत के ऊँच-नीच के भेदभाव को भुलाकर सब एक हो जाइए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0896","text":"कठिनाई दूर करने का प्रयत्न ही न हो तो कठिनाई कैसे मिटे। इसे देखते ही हाथ-पैर बाँधकर बैठ जाना और उसे दूर करने का कोई भी प्रयास न करना निरी कायरता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0897","text":"कर्तव्यनिष्ठ पुरूष कभी निराश नहीं होता। अतः जब तक जीवित रहें और कर्तव्य करते रहें तो इसमें पूरा आनन्द मिलेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0898","text":"कल किये जानेवाले कर्म का विचार करते-करते आज का कर्म भी बिगड़ जाएगा। और आज के कर्म के बिना कल का कर्म भी नहीं होगा, अतः आज का कर्म कर लिया जाये तो कल का कर्म स्वत: हो जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0899","text":"जैसे प्रसव-वेदना के बाद राहत मिलती है, उसी प्रकार ज्यादती के बाद ही विजय होती है। समाज की बुराइयों को दूर करने के लिए इससे अधिक शक्तिशाली कोई हथियार नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0900","text":"कायरता का बोझा दूसरे पड़ोसियों पर रहता है। अतः हमें मजबूत बनना चाहिए ताकि पड़ोसियों का काम सरल हो जाए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0901","text":"मनुष्य को ठंडा रहना चाहिए, क्रोध नहीं करना चाहिए। लोहा भले ही गर्म हो जाए, हथौड़े को तो ठंडा ही रहना चाहिए अन्यथा वह स्वयं अपना हत्था जला डालेगा। कोई भी राज्य प्रजा पर कितना ही गर्म क्यों न हो जाये, अंत में तो उसे ठंडा होना ही पड़ेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0902","text":"चरित्र के विकास से बुद्धि का विकास तो हो ही जाएगा। लोगों पर छाप तो हमारे चरित्र की ही पडती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0903","text":"जितना दुःख भाग्य में लिखा है, उसे भोगना ही पड़ेगा-फिर चिंता क्यों?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0904","text":"त्याग के मूल्य का तभी पता चलता है, जब अपनी कोई मूल्यवान वस्तु छोडनी पडती है। जिसने कभी त्याग नहीं किया, वह इसका मूल्य क्या जाने।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0905","text":"भगवान किसी को दूसरे के दोषों का धनद नहीं देता, हर व्यक्ति अपने ही दोषों से दुखी होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0906","text":"दुःख उठाने के कारण प्राय: हममें कटुता आ जाती है, दृष्टी संकुचित हो जाती है और हम स्वार्थी तथा दूसरों की कमियों के प्रति असहिष्णु बन जाते हैं। शारीरिक दुःख से मानसिक दुःख अधिक बुरा होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0907","text":"अधिकार मनुष्य को अँधा बना देता है। इसे हजम करने के लिए जब तक पूरा मूल्य न चुकाया जाये, तब तक मिले हुए अधिकारों को भी हम गंवा बैठेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0908","text":"जो व्यक्ति अपना दोष जनता है उसे स्वीकार करता है, वही ऊँचा उठता है। हमारा प्रयत्न होना चाहिए कि हम अपने दोषों को त्याग दें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0909","text":"अपने धर्म का पालन करते हुए जैसी भी स्थिति आ पड़े, उसी में सुख मानना चाहिए और ईश्वर में विश्वास रखकर सभी कर्तव्यों का पालन करते हुए आनन्दपूर्वक दिन बिताने चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0910","text":"पर हथौड़ा तो ठंडा रहकर ही काम दे सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0911","text":"जीतने के बाद नम्रता और निरभिमानता आनी चाहिए, और वह यदि न आए तो वह घमंड कहलाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0912","text":"सेवा करनेवाले मनुष्य को विन्रमता सीखनी चाहिए, वर्दी पहन कर अभिमान नहीं, विनम्रता आनी चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0913","text":"सारी उन्नति की कुंजी ही स्त्री की उन्नति में है। स्त्री यह समझ ले तो स्वयं को अबला न कहे। वह तो शक्ति-रूप है। माता के बिना कौन पुरूष पृथ्वी पर पैदा हुआ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0914","text":"किसी तन्त्र या संस्थान की पुनपुर्न: निंदा की जाए तो वह ढीठ बन जाता है और फिर सुधरने की बजाय निंदक की ही निंदा करने लगता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0915","text":"प्राण लेने का अधिकार तो ईश्वर को है। सरकार की तोप या बंदूकें हमारा कुछ नहीं कर सकतीं। हमारी निर्भयता ही हमारा कवच है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0916","text":"नेतापन तो सेवा में है, पर जो सीधा बन जाता है, वह किसी-न-किसी दिन लुढक अवश्य जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0917","text":"हर जाति या राष्ट्र खाली तलवार से वीर नहीं बनता। तलवार तो रक्षा-हेतु आवश्यक है, पर राष्ट्र की प्रगति को तो उसकी नैतिकता से ही मापा जा सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0918","text":"आपके घर का प्रबंध दूसरों को सौंपा गया हो तो यह कैसा लगता है- यह आपको सोचना है। जब तक प्रबंध दूसरों के हाथ में है, तब तक परतन्त्रता है, तब तक सुख नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0919","text":"चूँकि पाप का भार बढ़ गया है, अतः संसार विनाश के मार्ग पर अग्रसर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0920","text":"कठोर-से-कठोर हृदय को भी प्रेम से वश में किया जा सकता है। प्रेम तो प्रेम है। माता को भी अपना काना-कुबड़ा बच्चा सुंदर लगता है और वह उससे असीम प्रेम करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0921","text":"मानव ईश्वरप्रदत्त बुद्धि का उपयोग नहीं करता, आँखें होते हुए भी नहीं देखता, इसीलिए वह दुखी रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0922","text":"हिंसा के बल पर ही जो सारी तैयारी करते हैं। उनके दिल में भी के सिवाय और कुछ नहीं होता। भी तो ईश्वर से होना चाहिए,किसी मनुष्य या सत्ता से नहीं और भी को मिटाकर हम दूसरों को भयभीत करें तो इस जैसा कोई पाप नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0923","text":"भारत की एक बड़ी विशेषता है, वह यह कि चाहे कितने ही उतर-चढ़ाव आएँ, किन्तु पुण्यशाली आत्माएँ यहाँ जन्म लेती ही रहती हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0924","text":"प्राणियों के इस शरीर की रक्षा का दायित्व बहुत-कुछ हमारे मन पर भी निर्भर करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0925","text":"प्रत्येक मनुष्य में प्रकृति ने चेतना का अंश रख दिया है जिसका विकास करके मनुष्य उन्नति कर सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0926","text":"मृत्यु ईश्वर-निर्मित है, कोई किसी को प्राण न दे सकता है, न ले सकता है। सरकार की तोपें और बंदूकें हमारा कुछ भी नहीं कर सकतीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0927","text":"विश्वास का न होना ही का कारण है। प्रज्ञा का विश्वास राज्य की निर्भयता की निशानी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0928","text":"शक्ति के बिना बोलने से लाभ नहीं। गोला-बारूद के बिना बत्ती लगाने से धडाका नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0929","text":"संस्कृति समझ-बूझकर शांति पर रची गयी है। मरना होगा तो वे अपने पापों से मरेंगे। जो काम प्रेम, शांति से होता है, वह वैर-भाव से नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0930","text":"शारीरिक और मानसिक शिक्षा साथ –साथ दी जाये, ऐसी व्यवस्था होनी चाहिए। शिक्षा इसी हो जो छात्र के मन का, शरीर का, और आत्मा का विकास करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0931","text":"शक्ति के बिना श्रद्धा व्यर्थ है। किसी भी महान कार्य को पूरा करने में श्रद्धा और शक्ति दोनों की आवश्यकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0932","text":"वह इन्सान कभी सुख प्राप्त नहीं कर सकता जिसने कभी किसी संत को दुःख पहुंचाया हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0933","text":"देश में अनेक धर्म, अनेक भाषाएँ हैं, तो भी इसकी संस्कृति एक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0934","text":"सत्य के मार्ग पर चलने हेतु बुरे का त्याग अवश्यक है, चरित्र का सुधार आवश्यक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0935","text":"जल्दी करने से आम नहीं पकता। आम की कच्ची कैरी तोड़ेंगे तो दांत खट्टे होंगे। फल को पकने दें, पकेगा तो स्वयं गिरेगा और रसीला होगा। इसी भांति समझौते का समय आएगा, तब सच्चा लाभ मिलेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0936","text":"जो मनुष्य सम्मान प्राप्त करने योग्य होता है, वह हर जगह सम्मान प्राप्त कर लेता है, पर अपने जन्म-स्थान पर उसके लिए सम्मान प्राप्त करना कठिन ही है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0937","text":"सुख और दुःख मन के कारण ही पैदा होते हैं और वे मात्र कागज के गोले हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0938","text":"सेवा-धर्म बहुत कठिन है। यह तो काँटों की सेज पर सोने के समान ही है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0939","text":"किसी राष्ट्र के अंतर में स्वतन्त्रता की अग्नि जल जाने के बाद वह दमन से नहीं बुझाई जा सकती। स्वतन्त्रता-प्राप्ति के बाद भी यदि परतन्त्रता की दुर्गन्ध आती रहे तो स्वतन्त्रता की सुगंध नहीं फैल सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0940","text":"सच्चे त्याग और आत्मशुद्धि के बिना स्वराज नहीं आएगा। आलसी, ऐश-आराम में लिप्त के लिए स्वराज कहाँ! आत्मबल के आधार पर खड़े रहने को ही स्वराज कहते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0941","text":"स्वार्थ के हेतु राजद्रोह करनेवालों से नरककुंड भरा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0942","text":"हम कभी हिंसा न करें, किसी को कष्ट न दें और इसी उद्देश्य से हिंसा के विरूद्ध गांधीजी ने अहिंसा का हथियार आजमा कर संसार को चकित कर दिया।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0943","text":"कुछ सत्ता पर काबिज कांग्रेसी सोचते हैं कि वे अपनी ताक़त के बल पर आरएसएस को कुचल सकते हैं। आप किसी संगठन को सत्ता के बल पर नहीं कुचल सकते। राष्ट्रीय स्वयंसेवक संघ के लोग चोर और लुटेरे नहीं हैं। वे देशभक्त हैं। वे अपने देश से प्यार करते हैं लेकिन उनके विचार गुमराह हैं।  -- सरदार पटेल, लखनऊ में दिए एक भाषण में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0944","text":"एकता के बिना आज़ादी का मूल्य नहीं होता (स्रोत: कांग्रेस अधिवेशन, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1936)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0945","text":"अगर हम भारतीय हैं तो हमें भारत की एकता के लिए अपने प्रांत, भाषा और धर्म से ऊपर उठना होगा (स्रोत: संविधान सभा भाषण, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1947)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0946","text":"लोहे को लोहा काटता है, पर लोहे की जंजीर को केवल सत्य काटता है (स्रोत: जेल भाषण, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1932)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0947","text":"एकता की असली परीक्षा तब होती है जब संकट सामने हो (स्रोत: दिल्ली रैली भाषण, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1947)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0948","text":"अब हमें आज़ादी मिली है, लेकिन इसके साथ जिम्मेदारी भी आई है (स्रोत: बड़ौदा सार्वजनिक सभा, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1948)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0949","text":"यदि कोई सरकार जनता के हित में काम न करे, तो उसे बदलना जनता का अधिकार है (स्रोत: नागपुर जनसभा, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1939)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0950","text":"संविधान केवल कागज़ नहीं है, वह एक जीवित दस्तावेज़ है जो भारत को जोड़ेगा (स्रोत: संविधान सभा वक्तव्य, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1947)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0951","text":"देश सेवा का मार्ग कठिन है, लेकिन वही सच्चा मार्ग है (स्रोत: स्वतंत्रता सेनानियों को संबोधन, वल्लभभाई पटेल, 1946)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0952","text":"मैं मुसलमानों का सच्चा दोस्त हूं लेकिन मुझे उनका सबसे बड़ा दुश्मन माना जाता है। मैं अपनी बात स्पष्ट रूप से कहने में विश्वास रखता हूँ। मैं उन्हें स्पष्ट करना चाहता हूं कि ऐसी स्थिति में भारतीय संघ के प्रति देशभक्ति की घोषणा मात्र से उन्हें मदद नहीं मिलेगी। उनकी घोषणा का व्यावहारिक प्रमाण भी उन्हें प्रस्तुत करना चाहिए। --  ०६ जनवरी, १९४८ को लखनऊ में दिये गये भाषण में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — मुसलमानों पर उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0953","text":"मैं भारतीय मुसलमानों से एक सवाल पूछना चाहता हूं कि हाल ही में संपन्न अखिल भारतीय मुस्लिम सम्मेलन में उन्होंने कश्मीर मुद्दे पर पाकिस्तान की आक्रामकता की निन्दा क्यों नहीं की? यह लोगों के मन में संदेह पैदा करता है। अब आपको एक साथ तैरना होगा या एक साथ डूबना होगा। एक ही नाव में, आप दो घोड़ों की सवारी नहीं कर सकते। --  ०६ जनवरी, १९४८ को लखनऊ में दिये गये भाषण में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — मुसलमानों पर उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0954","text":"जो लोग पाकिस्तान जाना चाहते हैं उन्हें वहां जाना चाहिए और शांति से रहना चाहिए, लेकिन यहां के लोगों को भी शांति से रहना चाहिए और प्रगति के काम में योगदान देना चाहिए। --  ०६ जनवरी, १९४८ को लखनऊ में दिये गये भाषण में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — मुसलमानों पर उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0955","text":"तुम जो भी करो, शांति और प्रेम के साथ करो और तुम सफल हो जाओगे, लेकिन तलवार का जवाब तलवार से दिया जाएगा। -- नवम्बर, 1946 के चौथे सप्ताह में कांग्रेस का वार्षिक अधिवेशन मेरठ में भाषण में पाकिस्तान की मांग करने वालों से  (राजमोहन गांधी द्वारा ‘पटेल, ए लाइफ’ में उद्धृत)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — मुसलमानों पर उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0956","text":"मुसलमान कहते हैं कि उनकी निष्ठा पर सवाल क्यों उठाया जाता है। मैं कहता हूं कि आप अपनी अंतरात्मा से क्यों नहीं पूछते?-- 5 जनवरी, 1948 को कलकत्ता में अपने भाषण में सरदार पटेल","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — मुसलमानों पर उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0957","text":"भारत में केवल एक ही ‘राष्ट्रवादी मुस्लिम’ है और वह ‘नेहरू’ हैं। -- ज़कारिया द्वारा उद्धृत पटेल का कथन (यह बात इतनी फैल गई कि गांधीजी को सरदार से कहना पड़ा कि ‘वह अपनी हाज़िर जवाबी को अपने विवेक पर हावी न होने दें।)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — मुसलमानों पर उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0958","text":"मैंने मौलाना की आलोचना से सरदार को बचाने की कोशिश की है। उनमें कोई दोष न हो, ऐसा नहीं है, पर मौलाना का हमला सही नहीं है। मैंने सिर्फ ऐतिहासिक रिकार्ड को सही करने की कोशिश की है। पर मौलाना ने जो कुछ लिखा है, उससे यह धारणा बनती है कि सरदार अगर मुसलमानों के दुश्‍मन नहीं तो दिल से सांप्रदायिक व्यक्ति तो थे ही, जबकि यह सच्चाई नहीं है। --  मौलाना अबुल कलाम आजाद द्वारा 'इंडिया विन्स फ्रीडम' में सरदार पटेल को दोषी ठहराने पर आचार्य कृपलानी की प्रतिक्रिया","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — वल्लभभाई पटेल के बारे में अन्य लोगों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0959","text":"देश के विभाजन के दौरान हिंदू शरणार्थियों की हालत देखकर सरदार के मन में हिंदू समर्थक रवैया भले देखा जा सकता है लेकिन उनमें भारतीय मुसलमानों के साथ अन्याय करने की कोई प्रवृत्ति देखी नहीं जा सकती थी। -- रफ़ीक़ ज़कारिया, अपनी किताब ‘सरदार पटेल तथा भारतीय मुसलमान’ में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — वल्लभभाई पटेल के बारे में अन्य लोगों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0960","text":"वे बिना सोचे-समझे नहीं बोलते थे। संदर्भों में देखें तो, यह कहना ग़लत नहीं होगा कि जिस धर्म ने देश को विभाजित किया, उसके अनुयायी देश के प्रति वफ़ादार रहेंगे। -- रिज़वान कादरी, पटेल के सम्बन्ध में, बीबीसी गुजराती से","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — वल्लभभाई पटेल के बारे में अन्य लोगों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0961","text":"जब दिल्ली में मुसलमान कुत्ते-बिल्लियों की तरह मर रहे थे, तब मैं, जवाहर और सरदार गांधीजी के साथ बैठे थे। जब जवाहरलाल ने दिल्ली में हिंसा को रोकने के लिए प्रशासन के काम करने के तरीके पर नाराजगी व्यक्त की, तो सरदार ने उनसे कहा कि मुसलमानों को डरने की जरूरत नहीं है। सरकार मुसलमानों की जान-माल बचाने की पूरी कोशिश कर रही है, लेकिन और कुछ नहीं किया जा सकता। -- मौलाना अबुल कलाम आज़ाद, अपनी पुस्तक 'इंडिया विन्स फ्रीडम' में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — वल्लभभाई पटेल के बारे में अन्य लोगों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0962","text":"पीड़ितों की संख्या इतनी अधिक थी कि पुराने किले में उनके लिए एक राहत शिविर स्थापित करना पड़ा। गांधीजी मुझसे, सरदार पटेल और नेहरू से मामले पर विवरण देने के लिए कहते थे। सरदार का दृष्टिकोण अलग था. हम दोनों के बीच मतभेद बढ़े। एक तरफ मैं और जवाहरलाल थे जबकि दूसरी तरफ सरदार थे। प्रशासन में दो गुट हो गए। लोग सरदार की ओर देखते थे क्योंकि वह देश के गृह मंत्री थे। उन्होंने ऐसा काम किया कि बहुसंख्यक गुट उनसे खुश था। अल्पसंख्यक गुट मुझसे और जवाहरलाल से उम्मीद कर रहा था। -- मौलाना अबुल कलाम आज़ाद, अपनी पुस्तक 'इंडिया विन्स फ्रीडम' में","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — वल्लभभाई पटेल के बारे में अन्य लोगों के विचार","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0963","text":"मिट्टी से मुक्त हो जाना पेड़ के लिए आजादी नही होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0964","text":"यदि आप गलतियों के लिए अपने दरवाजे बंद करते है तो सत्य अपने आप बाहर आ जायेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0965","text":"फूल को तोड़कर आप उनकी खूबसूरती को इक्कठा नही कर सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0966","text":"जो दूसरो की भलाई के लिए हमेसा व्यस्त रहते है वे अक्सर अपने लिए समय नही निकाल पाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0967","text":"उच्च शिक्षा के जरिये सिर्फ जानकारी ही नही प्राप्त कर सकते है बल्कि जीवन कैसे आसान हो और कैसे सफल बने इसका मार्ग प्रशस्त्र करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0968","text":"कर्म करते हुए हमेसा आगे बढ़ते रहिये और फल के लिए व्यर्थ चिंता नही करिए और किया हुआ परिश्रम कभी व्यर्थ नही जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0969","text":"हम हमेसा यह प्रार्थना ना करे की हमारे ऊपर कभी भी किसी प्रकार की कोई बाधा या दिक्कत आये बल्कि हमे ईश्वर से यही प्रार्थना करें कि हम उन दुखों का निडरता से उनका सामना करें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0970","text":"हमें आजादी तभी मिलती है जब हम इसकी कीमत चुका देते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0971","text":"प्रसन्न रहना सरल है लेकिन सरल रहना यह बहुत ही कठिन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0972","text":"खड़े होकर सिर्फ समुद्र के पानी को देखने से आप समुद्र पार नही करते हैं। इसके लिए हमे खुद को आगे बढ़ाना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0973","text":"मनुष्य की सेवा भी ईश्वर की सेवा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0974","text":"तथ्य अनेक हो सकते है लेकिन सच्चाई हमेसा एक ही होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0975","text":"कला के जरिये व्यक्ति खुद की पहचान उजागर करता है वस्तुओं की नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0976","text":"आस्था वह पक्षी है जो अँधेरे में भी उजाले की शक्ति महसूस करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0977","text":"प्रत्येक शिशु जन्म लेकर यही संदेश लेकर आता है की ईश्वर अभी भी मनुष्यों से निराश नही हुआ है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0978","text":"मित्रता की गहराई सिर्फ उसके परिचय पर निर्भर नही करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0979","text":"फूल भले ही अकेला होता है लेकिन काँटों से कभी भी इर्ष्या नही करता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0980","text":"मूर्ति का टूटकर धूल में मिल जाना यह दिखलाता है ईश्वर के धूल की कीमत आपके मूर्ति से कही अधिक है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0981","text":"हम दुनिया में तभी जीते हैं जब दुनिया से प्रेम करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0982","text":"जब खुद पर हसता हु तो मेरे ऊपर का बोझ कम हो जाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0983","text":"यदि आप कठिनाई से मुह मोडकर भागते हैं तो यही स्वप्न बनकर आपके नीद में बाधा डालती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0984","text":"किसी बच्चे की शिक्षा सिर्फ अपने समय तक मत रखिये क्योंकि उसका जन्मकाल और आपका जन्मकाल दोनों में बहुत अन्तर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0985","text":"पृथ्वी द्वारा स्वर्ग से बातचीत करने का माध्यम होते हैं ये पेड़।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0986","text":"तितली महीने नही बल्कि प्रति क्षण की गिनती करती है जिसके कारण उसके पास पर्याप्त समय होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0987","text":"हम महानता के सबसे नजदीक तब होते है जब हम विनम्र होते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0988","text":"मौत प्रकाश को खत्म नही करता बल्कि यह दिखलाता है सुबह हो गयी है अब दीपक बुझाना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0989","text":"प्रेम का स्वप्न आने के बाद भी आप की नीद नही खुलती तो आपका जीवन धिक्कार है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0990","text":"जो पत्तियों से वृक्ष लदा होता है उसमे फल मुश्किल से ही आते है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0991","text":"जीवन हमे ईश्वर द्वारा दिया गया है जिसे हम कमाते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0992","text":"प्रेम कभी भी अधिकार नही जताता है बल्कि यह जीने की स्वतंत्रता देता है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0993","text":"संगीत दो आत्माओ के बीच की दुरी को खत्म कर देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0994","text":"उपदेश देना तो बहुत आसान है लेकिन उपाय बताना बहुत ही कठिन।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0995","text":"जो कुछ भी हमारा होता है वह हमारे पास जरुर आता है क्युकी हम उसे ग्रहण करने की क्षमता रखते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0996","text":"जो मन की पीड़ा को दुसरो से नही बता पाते उन्हें ही गुस्सा सबसे अधिक आता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0997","text":"जिस तरह घोसला सोते हुए पक्षी को आश्रय देता है ठीक उसी तरह मौन हमारी वाणी को आश्रय देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0998","text":"विद्यालय वह कारखाने है जिनमे महापुरुषों का निर्माण होता है जिनमे अध्यापक कारीगर होते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-0999","text":"बर्तन में रखा पानी चमकता है जबकि समुद्र का पानी अस्पष्ट होता है यानी छोटे सत्य तो आसानी से बताये जा सकते है जबकि महान सदैव मौन ही रहता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1000","text":"ईश्वर भले ही बड़े बड़े साम्राज्य से उब जाता है लेकिन छोटे छोटे फूलो से कभी रुष्ट नही होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1001","text":"धूल अपना अपमान सहने की क्षमता रखती है और बदले में फूलो का उपहार देती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1002","text":"यदि हमारे अन्दर प्रेम नही हो तो यह दुनिया हमे कारागार ही लगती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1003","text":"आयु सोचती है, जवानी करती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1004","text":"पंखुडियां तोड़ कर आप फूल की खूबसूरती नहीं इकठ्ठा करते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1005","text":"मिटटी के बंधन से मुक्ति पेड़ के लिए आज़ादी नहीं है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1006","text":"जो कुछ हमारा है वो हम तक आता है; यदि हम उसे ग्रहण करने की क्षमता रखते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1007","text":"मंदिर की गंभीर उदासी से बाहर भागकर बच्चे धूल में बैठते हैं, भगवान् उन्हें खेलता देखते हैं और पुजारी को भूल जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1008","text":"मौत प्रकाश को ख़त्म करना नहीं है; ये सिर्फ दीपक को बुझाना है क्योंकि सुबह हो गयी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1009","text":"हर बच्चा इसी सन्देश के साथ आता है कि भगवान अभी तक मनुष्यों से हतोत्साहित नहीं हुआ है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1010","text":"मित्रता की गहराई परिचय की लम्बाई पर निर्भर नहीं करती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1011","text":"जो कुछ हमारा है वो हम तक तभी पहुचता है जब हम उसे ग्रहण करने की क्षमता विकसित करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1012","text":"वे लोग जो अच्छाई करने में बहुत ज्यादा व्यस्त होते है, स्वयं अच्छा होने के लिए समय नहीं निकाल पाते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Rabindranath Tagore (Hindi) — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1013","text":"एक ऐसा क्षण जो इतिहास में बहुत ही कम आता है, जब हम पुराने के छोड़ नए की तरफ जाते हैं, जब एक युग का अंत होता है, और जब वर्षों से शोषित एक देश की आत्मा, अपनी बात कह सकती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1014","text":"जब तक मैं स्वयं में आश्वस्त हूँ की किया गया काम सही काम है तब तक मुझे संतुष्टि रहती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1015","text":"संस्कृति मन और आत्मा का विस्तार है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1016","text":"तथ्य तथ्य हैं और आपके नापसंद करने से गायब नहीं हो जायेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1017","text":"सुझाव देना और बाद में हमने जो कहा उसके नतीजे से बचने की कोशिश करना बेहद आसान है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1018","text":"नागरिकता देश की सेवा में निहित है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1019","text":"संकट के समय हर छोटी चीज मायने रखती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1020","text":"संकट और गतिरोध जब वे होते हैं तो कम से कम उनका एक फायदा होता है कि वे हमें सोचने पर मजबूर करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1021","text":"महान कार्य और छोटे लोग साथ नहीं चल सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1022","text":"हर एक हमलावर राष्ट्र की यह दावा करने की आदत होती है कि वह अपनी रक्षा के लिए कार्य कर रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1023","text":"एक नेता या कर्मठ व्यक्ति संकट के समय लगभग हमेशा ही अवचेतन रूप में कार्य करता है और फिर अपने किये गए कार्यों के लिए तर्क सोचता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1024","text":"अज्ञानता बदलाव से हमेशा डरती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1025","text":"केवल भाषणों से देश नहीं बनते, उन्हें बनाने के लिए खून, पसीना और मेहनत लगती है (स्रोत: लाल किले से भाषण, जवाहरलाल नेहरू, 1953)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1026","text":"भविष्य उन्हीं का है जो अपने सपनों की सुंदरता में विश्वास करते हैं (स्रोत: यूनिवर्सिटी कन्वोकेशन, जवाहरलाल नेहरू, 1958)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1027","text":"लोकतंत्र केवल प्रणाली नहीं, यह एक विश्वास है (स्रोत: संविधान सभा अंतिम सत्र, जवाहरलाल नेहरू, 1949)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1028","text":"जीवन ताश की तरह है; आपके हाथ में जो पत्ते हैं, वह नियति है, और जिस तरह आप खेलते हैं वह आपकी स्वतंत्र इच्छा है (स्रोत: glimpses of world history, जवाहरलाल नेहरू, 1933)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Jawaharlal Nehru — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1029","text":"मेरा नाम आजाद है, मेरे पिता का नाम स्वाधीनता है और मेरा घर जेलखाना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1030","text":"मैं आज़ाद था, आज़ाद हूँ और आज़ाद ही रहूँगा (स्रोत: झांसी में क्रांतिकारियों से संवाद, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1931","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1031","text":"शेर की तरह जीना बेहतर है, गीदड़ की तरह सौ साल।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1032","text":"दुश्मन की गोलियों का हम सामना करेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1033","text":"किसी भी एक भारतवासी के जख्म का बदला हजारों जख्मों से लिया जाएगा। यह चेतावनी नहीं घोषणा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1034","text":"सूरज पश्चिम में निकल सकता है परन्तु ये आजाद अपने देश को कभी अकेला नहीं छोड़ सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1035","text":"“दीवारों के भी कुछ कान होते हैं… आइना तोडने से डर लगता है।”","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1036","text":"किसी क्रांतिकारी का सबसे बड़ा हथियार नहीं होती हैं बंदूकें, बम या तोप। क्रांतिकारी विचारों से बनते हैं जो नैतिकता से, सत्य से, प्रेम से और किताबों से आते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1037","text":"जो दुश्मन हमारी धन-संपदा और संस्कृति को लूट रहे हैं, उन्हें लूटना और उनसे अपने धन-संपदा का रक्षा करना कोई गुनाह नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1038","text":"देश अगर हाथ जोड़ने से आजाद हो जाता तो यह जान लें कि भारत कभी गुलाम नहीं होता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1039","text":"खैरात में मिली खुशी हमें अच्छी नहीं लगती क्योंकि हम अपने गमों में भी नवाब की तरह जीते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1040","text":"जीवित रहते मैं अपनी मातृभूमि की रक्षा के लिए निरन्तर संघर्ष करता रहूँगा। किसी भी क्षण मैं मातृभूमि की खातिर अपने प्राण न्योछावर करने से पीछे नहीं हटूंगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1041","text":"किसी भी भारतवासी के जख्म का बदला हजारों जख्मों से लिया जाएगा। यह चेतावनी नहीं घोषणा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1042","text":"जो दुश्मन हमारे धन संपदा और संस्कृति को लूट रहे हैं, उन्हें लूटना और उनसे अपने धन संपदा की रक्षा करना कोई गुनाह नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1043","text":"अगर आपके लहू में रोष नहीं है, तो यह पानी है जो आपकी रगों में बह रहा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1044","text":"मातृभूमि की इस दुर्दशा को देखकर अभी तक यदि आपका रक्त क्रोध नहीं करता है, तो यह आपकी रगों में बहता खून नहीं है ये तो पानी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1045","text":"ऐसी जवानी का क्या मतलब अगर वह मातृभूमि के काम ना आए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1046","text":"मातृभूमि की इस दुर्दशा को देखकर जो तुम चुप बैठे रहे तो तुम्हारा मान-सम्मान और स्वाभिमान दुश्मनों के अधीन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1047","text":"दूसरे अपने से बेहतर कर रहे हैं यह नहीं देखना चाहिए। हर दिन अपने ही नए कीर्तिमान स्थापित करने चाहिए क्योंकि लड़ाई खुद से होती है दूसरों से नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1048","text":"अगर इश्क करना ही है तो वतन से करो। मरना ही है तो वतन की खातिर मारो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1049","text":"आज का युवा संगठित हो रहा है। यह मेरा देश की शक्ति का संगठन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1050","text":"मेरा यह छोटा सा संघर्ष ही कल महान बन जाएगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1051","text":"मौत तो एक दिन सबको आनी है। कुछ लोग डर-डर के जीते है, कुछ लोग मर कर भी अमर हो जाते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1052","text":"भले ही मेरा प्राम्भिक जीवन आदिवासी इलाके में बीता है लेकिन मेरे हृदय में मातृभूमि ही बसती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1053","text":"शत्रु के साथ कैसी नम्रता? हमारी नम्रता का ही फल है कि आज हमारी मातृभूमि संकट में है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1054","text":"मैं ऐसे धर्म और संस्कार का पालन करता हूँ जो स्वतंत्रता, समानता और भाईचारा सिखता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1055","text":"गालों पर थप्पड़ खाने से स्वतंत्रता नहीं मिलती। गोलियां मारनी पड़ती हैं दुश्मनों को।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1056","text":"सच्चा धर्म वही है जो स्वतंत्रता को परम मूल्य की तरह स्थापित करे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1057","text":"कोई विमान जमीन पर सदा सुरक्षित रहता है, लेकिन यह इसके लिए नहीं बनाया जाता। महान ऊंचाई प्राप्त करने के लिए हमेशा जीवन में कुछ सार्थक जोखिम लेना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1058","text":"देश मेरा गुलाम नहीं है, लोगों की सोच गुलाम है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1059","text":"अगर मातृभूमि को आजाद करना है तो अंग्रेजों की बोली बोलना छोड़ दो, उनका आचरण करना छोड़ दो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1060","text":"मेरे जज्बातों से इस कदर वाकिफ है , मेरी कलम","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1061","text":"मां हम विदा हो जाते हैं, हम विजय केतु फहराने आज,","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1062","text":"चिन्गारी आजादी की सुलगती मेरे जिस्‍म में है,","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1063","text":"जो युवा अपनी मातृभूमि की खातिर संघर्ष नहीं कर सकते, वे अपनी जननी की खातिर समर्पित नहीं हो सकते।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1064","text":"आजाद की कलाई में हथकड़ी लगाना बिलकुल असंभव है। एक बार सरकार लगा चुकी, अब तो शरीर के टुकड़े-टुकड़े हो जाएँगे लेकिन जीवित रहते पुलिस बंदी नहीं बना सकती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1065","text":"दुश्मन की गोलियों का, हम सामना करेंगे,","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1066","text":"जब तक यह बमतुल बुखारा (आजाद की पिस्तौल का नाम) मेरे पास है, किसने माँ का दूध पीया है जो मुझे जीवित पकड़ के ले जाए?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1067","text":"गिरफ्तार हो कर अदालत में हाथ बांध मुझे बंदरिया का नाच नहीं नाचना है। आठ गोली पिस्तौल में है और आठ का दूसरा मैगजीन है। पंद्रह दुश्मन पर चलाऊंगा और सोलहवी यंहा… (और आजाद अपनी पिस्तौल अपनी कनपटी पर छुआ देते)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1068","text":"मैं जीवन की अंतिम सांस तक देश के लिए शत्रु से लड़ता रहूँगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1069","text":"जब तक मेरे शरीर में प्राण है मैं अंग्रेजों की गुलामी नहीं करूंगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1070","text":"मैं देश की सेवा के लिए पैदा हुआ हूँ, मरूँगा भी देश के लिए (स्रोत: बंबई में भाषण, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1071","text":"क्रांति कभी भी समझौते से नहीं आती, वह साहस और बलिदान से आती है (स्रोत: साथियों को संबोधन, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1072","text":"हम मर सकते हैं लेकिन झुकेंगे नहीं (स्रोत: क्रांतिकारी पत्र व्यवहार, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1930)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1073","text":"डरपोक गुलामी करते हैं, बहादुर क्रांति करते हैं (स्रोत: झांसी ट्रेनिंग कैम्प, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1929)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1074","text":"मेरा नाम ही आज़ाद है — मुझे कोई पकड़ नहीं सकता (स्रोत: पुलिस पूछताछ में जवाब, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1921)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1075","text":"झुककर जीने से अच्छा है सिर उठाकर मर जाना (स्रोत: क्रांतिकारी सभा संवाद, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1928)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1076","text":"गोली खा लूंगा, पर कभी गिरफ्तारी नहीं दूँगा (स्रोत: अंतिम प्रण, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1931)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1077","text":"मैं देश की सेवा के लिए पैदा हुआ हूँ, मरूँगा भी देश के लिए (स्रोत: बंबई में भाषण, चंद्रशेखर आज़ाद, 1930","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1078","text":"आजाद सी वो आन हो और वैरियों से वैर हो","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chandrashekhar Azad — चन्द्रशेखर आजाद के बारे में","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1079","text":"कृत्रिम सुख के स्थान पर  के पीछे समर्पित रहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1080","text":"सपने वो नहीं जो हम सोते समय देखते हैं, सपने वो हैं जो हमें सोने नहीं देते (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1081","text":"बिहार के विकास के बिना भारत का विकास संभव नहीं है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1082","text":"शिक्षण एक बहुत ही महान पेशा है जो किसी व्यक्ति के चरित्र, क्षमता, और भविष्य को आकार देता हैं। अगर लोग मुझे एक अच्छे शिक्षक के रूप में याद रखते हैं, तो मेरे लिए ये सबसे बड़ा सम्मान होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1083","text":"जो व्यक्ति समय पर बोलने में या सुनने में समर्थ नहीं है,वही वास्तव में मूक एंव वधिर है अर्थात् असमर्थ और असफल है","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1084","text":"यदि हम स्वतंत्र नहीं हैं तो कोई भी हमारा आदर नहीं करेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1085","text":"अगर मरने के बाद भी जीना है तो एक काम जरूर करना पढने लायक कुछ लिख जाना या फिर लिखने लायक कुछ कर जाना.","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1086","text":"क्या हम यह नहीं जानते कि आत्म सम्मान आत्म निर्भरता के साथ आता है ?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1087","text":"मैं हमेशा इस बात को स्वीकार करने के लिए तैयार था कि मैं कुछ चीजें नहीं बदल सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1088","text":"भारत में हम बस मौत, बीमारी, आतंकवाद और अपराध के बारे में पढ़ते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1089","text":"महान सपने देखने वालों के महान सपने हमेशा पूरे होते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1090","text":"शिक्षा मानव की सोच को उजाला देने का साधन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1091","text":"शिक्षा वह नींव है जिस पर किसी राष्ट्र का भविष्य खड़ा होता है (स्रोत: प्रज्वलित मन, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2002)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1092","text":"अंग्रेजी आवश्यक है क्योंकि वर्तमान में विज्ञान के मूल काम अंग्रेजी में हैं. मेरा विश्वास है कि अगले दो दशक में विज्ञान के मूल काम हमारी भाषाओँ में आने शुरू हो जायेंगे, तब हम जापानियों की तरह आगे बढ़ सकेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1093","text":"मुझे बताइए , यहाँ का मीडिया इतना नकारात्मक क्यों है? भारत में हम अपनी अच्छाइयों, अपनी उपलब्धियों को दर्शाने में इतना शर्मिंदा क्यों होते हैं? हम एक माहान राष्ट्र हैं. हमारे पास ढेरों सफलता की गाथाएँ हैं, लेकिन हम उन्हें नहीं स्वीकारते. क्यों?","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1094","text":"एक अच्छी पुस्तक हज़ार दोस्तों के बराबर होती है जबकि एक अच्छा दोस्त एक लाइब्रेरी (पुस्तकालय) के बराबर होता है |","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1095","text":"जीवन में कठिनाइयाँ हमे बर्बाद करने नहीं आती है, बल्कि यह हमारी छुपी हुई सामर्थ्य और शक्तियों को बाहर निकलने में हमारी मदद करने आती है, कठिनाइयों को यह जान लेने दो की आप उससे भी ज्यादा कठिन हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1096","text":"अपनी पहली सफलता के बाद आराम मत करो क्योकि अगर आप दूसरी बार में असफल हो गए तो बहुत से होंठ यह कहने के इंतज़ार में होंगे की आपकी पहली सफलता केवल एक तुक्का थी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1097","text":"अपने काम से प्यार करो पर अपनी कार्यस्थल से प्यार मत करो क्योकि आप नहीं जानते की कब आपकी कम्पनी आपको प्यार करना बंद कर दे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1098","text":"सफलता की कहानियां मत पढ़ो उससे आपको केवल एक सन्देश मिलेगा। असफलता की कहानियां पढ़ो उससे आपको सफल होने के कुछ विचार मिलेंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1099","text":"एक मुर्ख जीनियस बन सकता है, यदि वो समझता है कि वो मूर्ख है लेकिन एक जीनियस मूर्ख बन सकता है जब वो समझता है कि वो जीनियस है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1100","text":"बारिश की दौरान सारे पक्षी आश्रय की खोज करते है लेकिन बाज़ बादलों के ऊपर उडकर बारिश को ही अवॉयड कर देते है। समस्याएँ कॉमन है, लेकिन आपका एटीट्यूड इनमे डिफरेंस पैदा करता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1101","text":"कभी कभी कक्षा से बंक मारकर मित्रोँ के साथ मस्ती करना अच्छा होता है, क्योंकि आज जब मैं पीछे मुड़कर देखता हूँ तो ये सिर्फ हंसाता ही नहीं है, बल्कि अच्छी यादें भी देता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1102","text":"जिंदगी और समय, विश्व के दो सबसे बड़े अध्यापक है। ज़िंदगी हमे समय का सही उपयोग करना सिखाती है जबकि समय हमे ज़िंदगी की उपयोगिता बताता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1103","text":"किसकी को हराना बहुत आसान है पर किसी को जितना बहुत कठिन है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1104","text":"देश का सबसे अच्छा दिमाग, क्लास रूम की आखरी बेंचो पर मिल सकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1105","text":"जीवन में कठिनाइयाँ हमें आत्मविश्लेषण का अवसर देती हैं (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1106","text":"महान सपने देखने वालों के महान सपने हमेशा पूरे होते हैं (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1107","text":"जब तुम्हारा सिग्नेचर ऑटोग्राफ में बदल जाए, तब समझो तुम सफल हो (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1108","text":"यदि हम भारत को विकसित बनाना चाहते हैं, तो हमें अपने मन को प्रज्वलित करना होगा (स्रोत: प्रज्वलित मन, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2002)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1109","text":"विफलता केवल एक अवसर है, फिर से शुरुआत करने का, इस बार और बुद्धिमत्ता से (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1110","text":"सोच को बदलना, सफलता की पहली शर्त है (स्रोत: प्रज्वलित मन, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2002)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1111","text":"जो लोग अपने दिल में ईमानदारी रखते हैं, उन्हें रास्ता स्वयं मिल जाता है (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1112","text":"भारत के हर कोने में प्रतिभा है, बस उसे प्रज्वलित करने की ज़रूरत है (स्रोत: प्रज्वलित मन, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2002)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1113","text":"मुझे असफलता से डर नहीं लगता, मुझे डर लगता है कि मैं प्रयास करना छोड़ दूँ (स्रोत: इंडिया टुडे यूथ कॉन्क्लेव, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2008)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1114","text":"अगर तुम देश के लिए कुछ नहीं कर रहे, तो तुम देश के विकास में बाधा हो (स्रोत: इंडिया टुडे माइंडरॉक्स, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2009)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1115","text":"आत्म-विश्वास और कड़ी मेहनत से असंभव भी संभव होता है (स्रोत: प्रज्वलित मन, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2002)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1116","text":"अगर तुम सूरज की तरह चमकना चाहते हो, तो पहले सूरज की तरह जलो (स्रोत: अग्नि की उड़ान, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 1999)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1117","text":"यदि आप कुछ बड़ा सपना देख सकते हैं, तो उसे हासिल भी कर सकते हैं (स्रोत: प्रज्वलित मन, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2002)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1118","text":"भारत को विकसित राष्ट्र बनाना सिर्फ सपना नहीं, ये हमारा संकल्प होना चाहिए (स्रोत: एनडीटीवी इंटरव्यू, ए. पी. जे. अब्दुल कलाम, 2005)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — A.P.J. Abdul Kalam — उक्तियाँ","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1119","text":"जय जवान, जय किसान।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1120","text":"अगर एक आदमी भी बोल दे की वो छुआछूत से पीड़ित है, तो भारत को शर्म से सर झुका देना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1121","text":"अनुशासन और एकता ही किसी देश की ताकत होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1122","text":"आज़ादी की रक्षा केवल सैनिकों का काम नहीं है। पूरे देश को मजबूत होना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1123","text":"आजादी की रक्षा सिर्फ हमारे देश के सैनिको का काम नहीं है इसकी रक्षा के लिए पूरे देश को मजबूत होना पड़ेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1124","text":"आर्थिक मुद्दे हमारे लिए सबसे जरूरी हैं, जिससे हम अपने सबसे बड़े दुश्मन 'गरीबी' और 'बेरोजगारी' से लड़ सकें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1125","text":"इसमें कोई संदेह नहीं है कि हमारे पास बड़ी परियोजनाएं, बड़े उद्योग, बुनियादी उद्योग हैं, लेकिन यह सबसे महत्वपूर्ण है कि हम आम आदमी को देखें, जो समाज का सबसे कमजोर तत्व है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1126","text":"उसकी जाति, रंग या नस्ल जो भी हो, हम एक व्यक्ति के रूप में मनुष्य की गरिमा में और उसके बेहतर, संपूर्ण और समृद्ध जीवन के लिए उसके अधिकार पर विश्वास करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1127","text":"कानून का सम्मान किया जाना चाहिए ताकि हमारे लोकतंत्र की बुनियादी संरचना बरकरार रहे और हमारा लोकतंत्र भी मजबूत बने।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1128","text":"जब स्वतंत्रता और देश की अखंडता खतरे में हो तो पूरी शक्ति से उस चुनौती का मुकाबला करना सभी का एकमात्र कर्तव्य होता है और इसके लिए किसी भी प्रकार के बलिदान के लिए भी एक साथ मिलकर तैयार रहना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1129","text":"जो शासन करते हैं, उन्हे देखना चाहिए कि लोग प्रशासन पर किस तरह प्रतिक्रिया करते हैं। अंततः जनता ही मुखिया होती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1130","text":"देश की तरक्की के लिए हमें आपस में लड़ने के बजाय गरीबी, बिमारी और अज्ञानता से लड़ना होगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1131","text":"देश की ताकत और मजबूती के लिए सबसे जरूरी काम है लोगों में एकता स्थापित करना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1132","text":"देश के प्रति निष्ठा सभी निष्ठाओं से पहले आती है और यह पूर्ण निष्ठा है क्योंकि इसमें कोई प्रतीक्षा नहीं कर सकता कि बदले में उसे क्या मिलता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1133","text":"दोनों देशों की आम जनता की समस्याएं, आशाएं और आकांक्षाएं एक समान है। उन्हे लड़ाई-झगड़ा और गोला-बारूद नहीं , बल्कि रोटी, कपड़ा और मकान की आवश्यकता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1134","text":"भ्रष्टाचार को पकड़ना बहुत कठिन काम है लेकिन मैं पूरे जोर के साथ कहता हूं कि यदि हम इस समस्या से गंभीरता और दृढ़ संकल्प के साथ नहीं निपटते हैं तो हम अपने कर्तव्यों का निर्वाह करने में असफल होंगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1135","text":"मुझे ग्रामीण क्षेत्रों में एक मामूली कार्यकर्ता के रूप में लगभग पचास वर्ष तक कार्य करना पड़ा है, इसलिए मेरा ध्यान स्वत: ही उन लोगों की ओर तथा उन क्षेत्रों के हालात पर चला जाता है। मेरे दिमाग में यह बात आती है कि सर्वप्रथम उन लोगों को राहत दी जाए । हर रोज हर समय मैं यही सोचता हूं कि उन्हे किस प्रकार से राहत पहुंचाई जाए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1136","text":"मेरी समझ से प्रशासन का मूल विचार यह है कि समाज को एकजुट रखा जाये ताकि वह विकास कर सके और अपने लक्ष्‍यों की तरफ बढ़ सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1137","text":"मैं किसी दूसरे को सलाह दूं और मैं खुद उस पर अमल ना करू तो मैं असहज महसूस करता हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1138","text":"मैं स्पष्ट रूप से कहना चाहता हूँ कि बल का बल से सामना होगा और हमारे खिलाफ़ आक्रामकता कभी भी सफ़ल नहीं होने दी जायेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1139","text":"यदि कोई भी व्यक्ति हमारे देश में अछूत कहा जाता है तो भारत को अपना सर शर्म से झुकाना पड़ेगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1140","text":"यदि पाकिस्तान का हमारे देश के किसी भी हिस्से को हड़पने का इरादा है, तो उसे नए सिरे से सोचना चाहिए। मैं स्पष्ट रूप से कहना चाहता हूँ कि बल का बल से सामना होगा और हमारे खिलाफ़ आक्रामकता कभी भी सफ़ल नहीं होने दी जायेगी।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1141","text":"यदि मैं एक तानाशाह होता तो धर्म और राष्ट्र अलग-अलग होते। मैं धर्म के लिए जान तक दे दूंगा, लेकिन यह मेरा निजी मामला है राज्य का इससे कुछ लेना देना नहीं है। राष्ट्र धर्मनिरपेक्ष, कल्याण, स्वास्थ्य, संसार, विदेशी संबंधों, मुद्रा इत्यादि का ध्यान रखेगा। लेकिन मेरे या आपके धर्म का नहीं, वो सबका निजी मामला है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1142","text":"यदि हम लगातार लड़ते रहेगे तो हमारी ही जनता को भारी परेशानियों का सामना करना पड़ेगा, हमे लड़ने के बजाय गरीबी, बीमारी और अशिक्षा से लड़ना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1143","text":"लोगों को सच्चा लोकतंत्र और स्वराज कभी भी हिंसा और असत्य से प्राप्त नहीं हो सकता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1144","text":"विज्ञान और वैज्ञानिक कार्यों में सफलता असीमित या बड़े संसाधनों का प्रावधान करने से नहीं मिलती बल्कि यह समस्याओं और उद्दश्यों को बुद्धिमानी और सतर्कता से चुनने से मिलती है और सबसे बढ़कर जो चीज चाहिए वो है निरंतर कठोर परिश्रम।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1145","text":"शासन के मूल विचार, जैसा कि मैंने इसे देखा है, समाज में एकता रखनी है ताकि वह अपने लक्ष्यों की ओर बढ़ सके और आगे बढ़ सके।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1146","text":"सच्चा लोकतंत्र या स्वराज कभी भी असत्य और हिंसक साधनों से नहीं आ सकते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1147","text":"हम उपनिवेशवाद और साम्राज्यवाद के अंत के लिए पूर्ण समर्थन देना अपना नैतिक कर्तव्य समझेंगे, ताकि हर जगह लोग अपने भाग्यनिर्माण के लिए स्वतंत्र हों।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1148","text":"हम केवल दुनिया में केवल तभी सम्मान पा सकते हैं अगर हम आंतरिक रूप से मजबूत हैं और हमारे देश से गरीबी और बेरोजगारी को खत्म कर दे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1149","text":"हम न केवल अपने लिए बल्कि दुनिया भर के लोगों के लिए शांति और शांतिपूर्ण विकास में विश्वास करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1150","text":"हम भले ही अपने देश की आजादी चाहते हैं, लेकिन उसके लिए ना ही हम किसी का शोषण करेंगे और ना ही दूसरे देशों को नीचा दिखाएंगे। मैं अपने देश की स्वतंत्रता कुछ इस प्रकार चाहता हूं कि दूसरे देश उससे कुछ सीख सकें और देश के संसाधनों को मानवता के लाभ के लिए प्रयोग में ले सकें।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1151","text":"हम सभी को अपने-अपने क्षेत्रों में उसी समर्पण, उसी उत्साह और उसी संकल्प तथा उसी भावना के साथ काम करना होगा जो रणभूमि में एक योद्धा को प्रेरित और उत्साहित करती है। और यह सिर्फ बोलना नहीं है, बल्कि वास्तविकता में कर के दिखाना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1152","text":"हम स्वतंत्रता में विश्वास करते हैं, प्रत्येक देश के लोगों के लिए आजादी, बाहरी हस्तक्षेप के बिना, अपने खुद की नियति बनाने के लिए स्वतंत्रता।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1153","text":"हमारा रास्ता सीधा और स्पष्ट है। अपने देश में सबके लिए स्वतंत्रता और संपन्नता के साथ समाजवादी लोकतंत्र की स्थापना और अन्य सभी देशों के साथ विश्व शांति और मित्रता का संबंध रखना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1154","text":"हमारी ताकत और मजबूती के लिए सबसे जरूरी काम है, लोगों में एकता स्थापित करना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1155","text":"हमारे देश की अनोखी बात यह है कि हमारे यहाँ हिंदू, मुस्लिम, ईसाई, सिख, पारसी और अन्य सभी धर्मों के लोग रहते हैं। हमारे यहाँ मंदिर और मस्जिद, गुरुद्वारे और चर्च हैं। लेकिन हम यह सब राजनीति में नहीं लाते हैं। भारत और पाकिस्तान के बीच यही अंतर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1156","text":"हमें उन कठिनाइयों पर विजय पानी है जो हमारे सामने आती हैं और हमारे देश की खुशी और समृद्धि के लिए दृढ़ता से काम करना चाहिए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1157","text":"हमें एक साथ मिलकर किसी भी प्रकार के अपेक्षित बलिदान के लिए दृढ़तापूर्वक तत्पर रहना है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1158","text":"हमें शांति के लिए उतनी ही बहादुरी से लड़ना चाहिए, जितना हम युद्ध में लड़ते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1159","text":"हर कार्य की अपनी एक गरिमा है और हर कार्य को अपनी पूरी क्षमता से करने में ही संतोष प्राप्त होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1160","text":"हर राष्ट्र के जीवन में एक समय आता है जब वह इतिहास के क्रॉस-रोड पर खड़ा होता है और उसे चुनना होता है कि किस रास्ते पर जाना है। लेकिन हमारे लिए कोई कठिनाई या झिझक की आवश्यकता नहीं है, कोई दाईं या बाईं ओर नहीं है। हमारा रास्ता सीधा और स्पष्ट है – सभी के लिए स्वतंत्रता और समृद्धि के साथ-साथ एक समाजवादी लोकतंत्र का निर्माण, और विश्व के सभी देशों के साथ शांति और दोस्ती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Lal Bahadur Shastri — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1161","text":"हारना तब आवश्यक हो जाता है, जब लड़ाई अपनों से हो, और जीतना तब आवश्यक हो जाता है, जब लड़ाई अपने आप से हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1162","text":"लहरों से डर कर नौका पार नहीं होती, कोशिश करने वालों की कभी हार नहीं होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1163","text":"मंजिल मिले ये तो मुकद्दर की बात है, हम कोशिश न करे ये तो गलत बात है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1164","text":"आज अपने ख़्वाब को मैं सच बनाना चाहता हु, दूर की इस कल्पना के पास जाना चाहता हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1165","text":"मन का हो जाए तो अच्छा, न हो तो और भी अच्छा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1166","text":"तू न थकेंगा कभी, तू न थमेंगा कभी, तू न मुड़ेगा कभी, कर शपथ कर शपथ कर शपथ, अग्निपथ अग्निपथ, अग्निपथ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1167","text":"किसी ने बर्फ से पूछा की आप इतने ठंडे क्यों हो? बर्फ ने कहा मेरा अतीत भी पानी है, मेरा भविष्य भी पानी है फिर मैं घमड़ किस बात का रखू।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1168","text":"गिरना भी अच्छा है, औकात का पता चल जाता है। बढ़ते है जब हाथ उठाने को अपनो का पता चलता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1169","text":"रब ने नवाजा हमे जिंदगी देकर, हम शौहरत मांगते रह गए।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1170","text":"क्या बात करे इस दुनिया की हर शख्स के अपने अफ़साने है जो सामने है उसे बुरा कहते है और जिसको कभी देखा नहीं उसे सभी खुदा कहते है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1171","text":"जब मुसीबत आये तो समझ जाना जनाब जिंदगी हमें कुछ नया सिखाने वाली है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1172","text":"जिंदगी में इतने व्यस्त हो जाओ की उदास होने का वक्त ही न मिले।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1173","text":"मजबूरियां देर रात तक जागती है और जिम्मेदारियां आपको सुबह जल्दी उठा देती है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1174","text":"सोचा था घर बनाकर बैठूँगा सुकून से पर घर की जरूरत ने मुसाफिर बना डाला।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1175","text":"संघर्ष इंसान को मजबूत बनाता है, फिर चाहे वो कितना ही कमजोर क्यों ना हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1176","text":"आज अपने ख्वाब को मैं सच बनाना चाहता हूं, दूर की इस कल्पना के पास जाना चाहता हूं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1177","text":"जो लहरों से डरता है वह कभी भी नौका पार नहीं कर पाता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1178","text":"सीख रहा हूँ अब मैं भी इंसानों को पढ़ने का हुनर, सुना है चेहरे पर किताबों से ज्यादा लिखा होता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1179","text":"ये समंदर भी तेरी तरह खुदगर्ज निकला, जिंदा थे तो तैरने ने दिया और मर गए तो डूबने न दिया।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1180","text":"कभी फूलों की तरह मत जीना जिस दिन खिलोगे बिखर जाओगे,जीना है तो पत्थर बन के जियो, किसी दिन तराशे गए तो खुदा बन जाओगे।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1181","text":"जो बीत गयी सो बात गयी जीवन एक सितारा था। माना वह बेहद प्यारा था, वह डूब गया तो डूब गया, अंबर के आनन को देखो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1182","text":"बैठ जाता हूं, मिट्टी पर अक्सर क्योंकि मुझे मेरी औकात अच्छी लगती है। मैंने समंदर से सीखा है, जीने का सलीका, चुपचाप से बहना और मौज में रहना।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1183","text":"मैं छुपाना जानता तो जग मुझे साधु समझता, शत्रु बन गया है छल रहित व्यवहार मेरा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1184","text":"प्यार किसी को करना, लेकिन कहकर उसे बताना क्या, अपने को अर्पण करना पर औरों को अपनाना क्या।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1185","text":"मैं यादों का किस्सा खोलूं, तो कुछ दोस्त बहुत याद करते हैं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1186","text":"हो जाए न पथ में रात कहीं, मंजिल भी तो है दूर नहीं। यह सोच थका दिन का पंथी भी जल्दी जल्दी चलता है, दिन जल्दी जल्दी ढलता है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1187","text":"संघर्ष का मैदान छोड़ मत भागो तुम, कुछ किये बिना ही जय जयकार नहीं होती। कोशिश करने वालों की कभी हार नही होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1188","text":"एक बरस में एक बार ही जलती होली की ज्वाला, एक बार ही लगती बाजी, जलती दीपों की माला। दुनिया वालों किंतु किसी दिन आ मंदिरालय में देखो,दिन को होली रात को दिवाली, रोज मनाती मधुशाला।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1189","text":"जग भव सागर तरने को नाव बनाए, मैं भव मौजों में मस्त बहा करता हूं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1190","text":"मैं जग जीवन का भार लिए फिरता हूं, फिर भी जीवन में प्यार लिए फिरता हूं। कर दिया किसी ने झंकृत जिनको छूकर, मैं सांसों में दो तार लिए फिरता हूं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1191","text":"गुजरते वक्त के साथ एक दिन यूं ही गुजर जाऊंगा, करके कुछ आँखों को नम कुछ दिलों में यादे बन कर बस जाऊँगा।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1192","text":"जो छूट गए फिर कहाँ मिले पर बोलो टूटे तारों पर, कब अम्बर शोक मनाता है, जो बीत गई सो बात गई।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1193","text":"असफलता एक चुनौती हैं, स्वीकार करो क्या कमी रह गयी, देखो और सुधार करो जब तक न सफल हो, नींद चैन को त्यागो तुम संघर्ष का मैदान छोड़ मत भागो तुम, कुछ किये बिना ही जय जय कर नहीं होती कोशिश करनेवालों की हर नहीं होती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1194","text":"उतर नशा जब उसका जाता, आती है संध्या बाला, बड़ी पुरानी, बड़ी नशीली नित्य ढला जाती हाला। जीवन की संताप शोक सब इसको पीकर मिट जाते, सुरा-सुप्त होते मद-लोभी जागृत रहती मधुशाला।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1195","text":"मैं जग-जीवन का भार लिए फिरता हूँ, फिर भी जीवन में प्यार लिए फिरता हूँ।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Harivansh Rai Bachchan — उद्धरण","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1196","text":"भारतीय भक्ति मार्ग सरलता और स्पष्टता का पक्षधर है क्योंकि उसके अनुसार भक्ति का संबंध भावना से है, कठिन योग साधना से नहीं।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1197","text":"भक्ति रस का पूर्ण परिपाक जैसा विनयपत्रिका में देखा जा सकता है, वैसा अन्यत्र नहीं। भक्ति में प्रेम के अतिरिक्त आलंबन के महत्त्व और अपने दैन्य का अनुभव परमावश्यक अंग है। तुलसी के हृदय से इन दोनों अनुभवों के ऐसे निर्मल शब्द स्रोत निकले हैं, जिसमें अवगाहन करने से मन की मैल करती है और अत्यंत पवित्र प्रफुल्लता आती है। -- रामचंद्र शुक्ल","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1198","text":"हम निःसंकोच कह सकते हैं कि यह एक कवि ही हिन्दी की एक प्रौढ़ साहित्यिक भाषा सिद्ध करने के लिए काफी है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1199","text":"तुलसीदास जी अपने ही तक दृष्टि रखने वाले भक्त न थे, संसार को भी दृष्टि फैलाकर देखने वाले भक्त थे। जिस व्यक्त जगत के बीच उन्हें भगवान के रामरुप की कला का दर्शन कराना था, पहले चारों ओर दृष्टि दौङाकर उसके अनेक रूपात्मक स्वरूप को उन्होंने सामने रखा है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1200","text":"शील और शील का, स्नेह और स्नेह का, नीति और नीति का मिलन है। (राम-भरत मिलन)","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1201","text":"यदि कहीं सौन्दर्य है तो प्रफुल्लता, शक्ति है तो प्रणति, शील है तो हर्ष पुलक, गुण है तो आदर, पाप है तो घृणा, अत्याचार है तो क्रोध, अलौकिकता है तो विस्मय, पाखंड है तो कुढ़न, शोक है तो करुणा, आनंदोत्सव है तो उल्लास, उपकार है तो कृतज्ञता, महत्त्व है तो दीनता, तुलसीदास के हृदय में बिम्ब-प्रतिबिंब भाव से विद्यमान है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1202","text":"अनुप्रास के तो वह बादशाह थे। अनुप्रास किस ढंग से लाना चाहिए, उनसे यह सीखकर यदि बहुत से पिछले फुटकर कवियों ने अपने कवित सवैये लिखे होते तो उनमें भद्दापन और अर्थन्यूनता न आने पाती।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — रामचन्द्र शुक्ल","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1203","text":"तुलसीदास को जो अभूतपूर्व सफलता मिली उसका कारण यह था कि वे समन्वय की विशाल बुद्धि लेकर उत्पन्न हुए थे। भारतवर्ष का लोकनायक वही हो सकता है जो समन्वय करने का अपार धैर्य लेकर सामने आया हो।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — हजारी प्रसाद द्विवेदी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"hindi-motiv-1204","text":"तुलसीदास जी की कविता में लोकजीवन को बहुत दूर तक प्रभावित किया है। उत्तर भारत में जन्म से लेकर मरण काल तक के सभी अनुष्ठानों और उत्सवों में तुलसीदास की रामभक्ति का कुछ न कुछ असर जरुर है।","author":"Hindi Motivational — Indian Leaders & Thinkers","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Tulsidas — हजारी प्रसाद द्विवेदी","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:hindi","theme:inspiration","theme:leadership","audience:morning"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."}]}